\h Yehezkel
\toc1 Yehezkel
\toc2 Yehezkel
\toc3 Yehez.
\mt1 Yehezkel
\mt1 (Ezekiel)
\is1 Introduction
\ip Yehezkel (or more properly вҖҳYehezk'elвҖҷ which means вҖҳGod/El will strengthenвҖҷ, but called вҖҳEzekielвҖҷ in older English translations because Greek has no вҖҳyвҖҷ or вҖҳhвҖҷ) was a priest in Yerushalem (Jerusalem). He was one of the many people who were captured by the Babylonian army and marched off to Babylon before Yerushalem was defeated in 586 B.C. So he lived in Babylon and became a prophet five years after he'd been exiled. His message was directed to the people exiled to Babylon as well as those back in Yerushalem. Yehezkel's account can be divided into six parts: 1. God's calling Yehezkel as a prophet; 2. warnings to the people there about God's coming punishment of them, and of the coming destruction of Yerushalem; 3. God's messages about the punishment of various nations who'd attacked Israel; 4. comforting Yisrael when enemies defeated Yerushalem, and a promise of a future, better life; 5. the defeat of all of Yisrael's enemies; 6. Yehezkel's description of a restored temple and of a nation that would return to living there.
\ip Yehezkel demonstrated a lot of faith, and his messages came as visionsвҖ”many of which he had to act out. Yehezkel explained the importance of a new heart and spirit, and how it's necessary for each person to individually repent from their sins. He reveals Yisrael's hope of a new life. Then as prophet and priest, he greatly looks forward to a new temple with all the rooms that are necessary for the sacred services.
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 The calling of Yehezkel as a prophet \ior 1:1вҖ“3:27\ior*
\io1 The speeches concerning the destruction of Yerushalem \ior 4:1вҖ“24:27\ior*
\io1 God's judgement of nations \ior 25:1вҖ“32:32\ior*
\io1 God's promise to his people \ior 33:1вҖ“37:27\ior*
\io1 The bad prophecies concerning Gog \ior 38:1вҖ“39:29\ior*
\io1 The revelation concerning the coming temple and nation \ior 40:1вҖ“48:35\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\ms1 Yehezkel's calling to be a prophet
\mr (1:1вҖ“3:27)
\s1 Yahweh reveals himself
\rem /s1 The Living Creatures and the Glory of the Lord; The calling of Ezekiel; A Vision of Living Beings; The Vision of the Chariot; God's Throne
\p
\v 1 \add WhenВҰ333469 I was\add* thirtyВҰ333471 years \add old\add*, onВҰ333471 July 5th, as I was \add вүҲliving withВҰ333471 the other captives\add* by the KebarВҰ333484 Canal, the skiesВҰ333486 openedВҰ333485 andВҰ333469 I sawВҰ333487 visionsВҰ333488 from GodВҰ333489.\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Rev 19:11.\x*
\p
\v 2 That was the fifthВҰ333495 yearВҰ333494 since KingВҰ333497 Yoyakin \add (Jehoiachin)\add* had been taken captive.\x + \xo 1:2: \xt 2Ki 24:10-16; 2Ch 36:9-10.\x*
\v 3 Yahweh gave \add me\add*, the priestВҰ333511 Yehezkel (son of BuziВҰ333510), this messageВҰ333502 in the land of the Chaldeans \add (often known better as Babylonians)\add* by the KebarВҰ333518 Canal, and Yahweh \add вүҲrevealed his strength to me\add* thereВҰ333521.
\v 4 ThenВҰ333526 I lookedВҰ333526, and there was a windstorm comingВҰ333530 from the northВҰ333533вҖ”a hugeВҰ333535 cloud with \add вүҲlightning\add* flashingВҰ333537 inside it and \add вүҲbrilliant light\add* inside it and surrounding it, and fire inside the cloud \add вүҲmade it look\add* amberВҰ333543 coloured.
\v 5 In the middleВҰ333547 \add вүҲwas what seemed to be\add* fourВҰ333549 livingВҰ333550 creaturesВҰ333550 resembling humansВҰ333554,\x + \xo 1:5: \xt Rev 4:6.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲbutВҰ333557\add* each of them had four facesВҰ333558 andВҰ333557 four wingsВҰ333561.
\v 7 Their legs were straightВҰ333567, butВҰ333565 theyВҰ333573 had hooves like calves' hooves that gleamedВҰ333574 like polished bronzeВҰ333575.
\v 8 They had humanВҰ333580 handsВҰ333578 underВҰ333581 their wings on each of their four sidesВҰ333585. For each of the four of them,
\v 9 theirВҰ333595 wings were touchingВҰ333590 the wings of the next creature, and they didn'tВҰ333596 turn as they wentвҖ”rather each one went straight forward.
\p
\v 10 Each one's \add frontВҰ333609\add* faceВҰ333608 was like a humanВҰ333610 face, thenВҰ333607 they each had a lion's face on the rightВҰ333615, a calf's face on the left, andВҰ333607 the fourth \add face\add* was an eagle'sВҰ333624 face.\x + \xo 1:10: \xt Ezr 1:5,10; 10:4; Eze 10:14; Rev 4:7.\x*
\v 11 Their facesВҰ333627 were like that, and their wings were spreadВҰ333629 out aboveВҰ333630, so that each creature had a pair of wings that touchedВҰ333633 another creature's wings, and also a pair that coveredВҰ333636 their bodiesВҰ333638.
\v 12 Each went straight forward, so that whereverВҰ333648 the spiritВҰ333652 directed them to goВҰ333653, they went without turning.
\p
\v 13 The living creatures \add вүҲresembled\add* burningВҰ333665 coalsВҰ333662 \add вүҲor\add* torchesВҰ333667. Bright fire also moved around among the creatures, andВҰ333659 there were flashes of lightningВҰ333678.\x + \xo 1:13: \xt Rev 4:5.\x*
\v 14 The livingВҰ333680 creaturesВҰ333680 moved rapidly swiftly back and forth, and theyВҰ333681 \add вүҲlooked a bit like\add* lightningВҰ333684.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ333686 I lookedВҰ333686 \add вүҲmore closely\add* andВҰ333686 saw a wheelВҰ333689 on the ground besideВҰ333692 each of the living creatures with its four facesВҰ333695.\x + \xo 1:15-21: \xt Eze 10:9-13.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲEach of the wheels was the same, and they all shone like\add* chrysoliteВҰ333701. \add вүҲEach wheel seemed to have one wheel inside another\add* wheel.
\v 17 \add When\add* they moved, \add вүҲthey didn'tВҰ333719 have to turn to change directionВҰ333716\add*.
\v 18 The rims \add @of the wheels\add* were \add вүҲawesomelyВҰ333726 tall\add*, andВҰ333723 all fourВҰ333732 of them were full of eyesВҰ333730 aroundВҰ333731 the rim.\x + \xo 1:18: \xt Rev 4:8.\x*
\v 19 Whenever the living creatures moved, the wheels moved besideВҰ333738 them. WhenВҰ333734 the living creatures \add вүҲwent upwards\add*, the wheels also went up.
\v 20 Wherever the spirit would go, they went, and the wheels went up beside them, because the spirit of the livingВҰ333762 creature was inВҰ333763 the wheels.
\v 21 Whenever the creatures moved, the wheels also moved, and when the creatures stood still, the wheels stood still. When the creatures \add вүҲwent upwards\add*, the wheels went up beside them, because the spiritВҰ333776 of the livingВҰ333777 creature was inВҰ333767 the wheels.
\p
\v 22 Above the livingВҰ333784 creatures was \add вүҲsomething like an awesomeВҰ333788 crystalВҰ333787 dome stretched out over theirВҰ333792 heads\add*.\x + \xo 1:22: \xt Rev 4:6.\x*
\v 23 Beneath the dome, each of the creatures' wings stretched out straightВҰ333798 andВҰ333807 touched another creature's wings. Each \add *one\add* also had a pair to cover theirВҰ333797 own bodyВҰ333812 with.
\v 24 ThenВҰ333814 I heardВҰ333814 the sound of their wings, \add which was\add* like the noise of a lot of waterВҰ333820. WhenВҰ333814 they movedВҰ333825, it was like the voiceВҰ333822 of the powerful \add one\add*вҖ”like the sound of a rainstormВҰ333827 \add or\add* an army. Whenever they stoodВҰ333830 stillВҰ333830, they lowered their wings.\x + \xo 1:24: \xt Rev 1:4-15; 19:6.\x*
\v 25 Whenever they stoppedВҰ333843 andВҰ333834 lowered their wingsВҰ333845, a voice came from underВҰ333837 the dome thatВҰ333839 was aboveВҰ333840 their headsВҰ333842.
\s1 God's throne
\p
\v 26 Above the dome over theirВҰ333852 headsВҰ333852 was \add вүҲwhat looked like a sapphireВҰ333856 stoneВҰ333854 that had been made into\add* a throne, andВҰ333847 on the thing like a throne was \add вүҲsomething that looked like\add* a man.\x + \xo 1:26: \xt Eze 10:1; Rev 4:2-3.\x*
\v 27 I saw a figure \add вүҲthat appeared to have\add* glowing metal with fire in it from his hips upwardsВҰ333881, and \add вүҲlooking downwardsВҰ333884 from\add* his hips, I saw the appearance of fire and brightnessВҰ333889 all around.\x + \xo 1:27: \xt Eze 8:2.\x*
\v 28 The brightВҰ333902 light surrounding \add @the throne\add* \add вүҲlooked like\add* a rainbowВҰ333894 inВҰ333897 the cloudsВҰ333897 onВҰ333897 a rainyВҰ333899 dayВҰ333898вҖ”it was the appearance of the likenessВҰ333906 of Yahweh's splendour. When I sawВҰ333910 itВҰ333896, I \add вүҲquickly knelt down and bowed my head to the ground\add*, and I heardВҰ333915 a voiceВҰ333916 speaking.
\c 2
\s1 Yehezkel sent as a prophet to Yisrael
\rem /s1 Ezekiel's Call and Commission; Ezekiel's Call; The Vision of the Scroll
\p
\v 1 He saidВҰ333920 to me, вҖңHumanity's child, standВҰ333925 up and then I'll speakВҰ333929 to youВҰ333930.вҖқ
\v 2 ThenВҰ333932 as he spoke to me, the spiritВҰ333934 enteredВҰ333932 into me and \add вүҲstood me up\add*, and IВҰ333942 heardВҰ333942 him speaking to me.
\v 3 He told me, вҖңHumanity's child, I'm sendingВҰ333953 youВҰ333955 to Yisrael's peopleВҰ333958вҖ”\add two\add* rebellious nationsВҰ333962 thatВҰ333964 have rebelled against me. Both they and theirВҰ333969 ancestorsВҰ333969 have been sinning against me \add вүҲright up to this very moment\add*.
\v 4 Their descendantsВҰ333978 \add вүҲare very stubbornВҰ333981 and hardheaded\add*. I'm sendingВҰ333985 you to them, and you'll tell them that this is what the masterВҰ333992 YahwehВҰ333992 is saying to them.
\v 5 They might listenВҰ333998 or might not. They're a rebelliousВҰ334004 \add вүҲbunch\add*, butВҰ333995 they'll atВҰ334010 least knowВҰ334006 that a prophetВҰ334008's been amongВҰ334010 them.
\p
\v 6 And you, humanity'sВҰ334016 child, don'tВҰ334017 be afraid of them or their words. Don't be afraid, even though you'reВҰ334032 among briersВҰ334027 and thornsВҰ334027, and although you live with scorpionsВҰ334031. Don't fear their words or be dismayedВҰ334041 by their facesВҰ334038, since they're a rebelliousВҰ334044 \add вүҲbunch\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲPass my\add* messagesВҰ334050 on to them, whetherВҰ334052 they listenВҰ334054 or not, because they're \add quite\add* rebelliousВҰ334059.
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ334063\add* you, humanity'sВҰ334066 child, listenВҰ334067 to what I'm telling you. Don't become rebellious like thatВҰ334069 rebellious \add вүҲbunch\add*. Open your mouthВҰ334082 and eatВҰ334083 what I'm \add about to\add* give you.вҖқ
\v 9 ThenВҰ334091 I lookedВҰ334091 and sawВҰ334091 a handВҰ334094 extended out to me, and \add вүҲit was holding a scrollВҰ334100 with writing on it\add*.\x + \xo 2:9-10: \xt Rev 5:1.\x*
\v 10 He spreadВҰ334104 it out \add вүҲin front of\add* meвҖ”there was writing on both the front and the back, \add вүҲand it was full of messages about grief, mourningВҰ334114, and sad endings\add*.
\c 3
\p
\v 1 He said to me, вҖңHumanity's child, eat what you've found. Eat this scrollВҰ334131, then go speakВҰ334134 to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ334137 people\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 3:1-3: \xt Rev 10:9-10.\x*
\v 2 SoВҰ334140 I openedВҰ334140 my mouthВҰ334143, andВҰ334140 he gaveВҰ334144 me the scrollВҰ334146 to eatВҰ334144.
\p
\v 3 He told me, вҖңHumanity's child, feed your bellyВҰ334154 and fillВҰ334157 your stomach withВҰ334167 this scrollВҰ334159 thatВҰ334161 I've given you.вҖқ SoВҰ334149 I ateВҰ334165 it, and it \add вүҲtasted\add* as sweetВҰ334169 as honeyВҰ334168.
\p
\v 4 Then he told me, вҖңHumanity's child, go to the \add вүҲpeople\add* of YisraelВҰ334183 \add (IsraelВҰ334183)\add* and \add вүҲpass\add* my messagesВҰ334185 onВҰ334185 to them,
\v 5 because you aren'tВҰ334189 beingВҰ334198 sent to a people group \add вүҲwho speak\add* a strange or difficultВҰ334195 language, butВҰ334195 to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ334202 people\add*вҖ”
\v 6 not to many peopleВҰ334208 groups \add вүҲwho speak\add* strange or difficultВҰ334212 languages whose wordsВҰ334218 you wouldn't be able to understandВҰ334217. \add вүҲI'm sure that if it was them that\add* I sentВҰ334223 you to, they would've listenedВҰ334225 to you.
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ334228\add* the \add вүҲIsraeli people\add* won'tВҰ334230 be willing to listen to you, because they're not willing to listen to me. All the \add вүҲIsraeli people\add* are \add вүҲhardheaded\add* andВҰ334228 hardhearted.
\v 8 \add вүҲListen, I'll enable you to be as stubborn andВҰ334261 tough as they are\add*.
\v 9 I'll make \add вүҲyou hard\add* like a diamondВҰ334268вҖ”harder than flintВҰ334270. Don't \add вүҲbe scared by\add* them or discouraged by \add вүҲthe looks they give you\add*, because they're rebelliousВҰ334284 \add вүҲpeople\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 He \add вүҲalso\add* told me, вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲlistenВҰ334304 very carefully to what I say\add*, and \add вүҲkeep thinking about it\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ334306 goВҰ334307 to \add вүҲany of yourВҰ334314 peopleВҰ334314 who were brought here as\add* captives, andВҰ334306 tell them, вҖҳThisВҰ334322 is what the masterВҰ334321 YahwehВҰ334321 saysВҰ334320,вҖҷ whetherВҰ334323 they'll listenВҰ334325 or not.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Ezekiel at the River Chebar
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ334330 the spiritВҰ334331 liftedВҰ334330 me up, andВҰ334332 I heardВҰ334332 rumblingВҰ334335 like a large earthquake behindВҰ334333 me. (May Yahweh's \add вүҲhonour\add* in his placeВҰ334341 be blessedВҰ334337.)
\v 13 It was the sound of the livingВҰ334346 creaturesВҰ334346' wingsВҰ334345 as they touchedВҰ334347 one another, and the sound of the wheelsВҰ334353 that were with them, and the sound of a large earthquake.
\v 14 ThenВҰ334359 the spirit liftedВҰ334360 me up and tookВҰ334361 me away, and I wentВҰ334362 withВҰ334364 bitternessВҰ334363 and rage inВҰ334364 my spiritВҰ334359, because Yahweh's handВҰ334366 was pressing down firmly onВҰ334364 me.
\v 15 ThenВҰ334372 I wentВҰ334372 to the captives atВҰ334394 TelВҰ334376-Abib who livedВҰ334378 along the KebarВҰ334383 Canal, andВҰ334372 I stayed amongВҰ334394 them there for sevenВҰ334391 daysВҰ334392, overwhelmed inВҰ334394 amazement.
\rem /s1 A Watchman for Israel; The Lord Appoints Ezekiel as a Lookout; Warning to Israel
\rem /r (Ezekiel 33.1-9)
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲAfter those sevenВҰ334398 daysВҰ334399 were over\add*, YahwehВҰ334404 \add gave\add* me this messageВҰ334402:\f + \fr 3:16 \ft This formula occurs around fifty times in Ezekiel's account.\f*
\v 17 вҖңHumanity's child, I've made youВҰ334412 a \add вүҲguard over the IsraeliВҰ334413 people\add*, so listenВҰ334415 to \add вүҲthis messageВҰ334417 of mine\add* and giveВҰ334418 them my warningВҰ334418.
\v 18 When I tell the wicked, вҖҳYou'll certainly dieвҖҷ and you don'tВҰ334426 warn them \add about that\add* or give them a warning about their evil actions so they might liveвҖ”the wicked will die for their sin, butВҰ334426 I'llВҰ334441 \add вүҲhold you responsible for their death\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ334443\add* if you do warn the wicked, andВҰ334443 they don'tВҰ334448 turn from their wickedness or from their wicked actions, thenВҰ334443 they'll dieВҰ334456 for their sin, butВҰ334443 you will have saved your own lifeВҰ334460.
\p
\v 20 If a godlyВҰ334465 person turnsВҰ334464 from their righteousness and behaves unjustly, and I put a stumblingВҰ334470 blockВҰ334470 in frontВҰ334471 of thatВҰ334483 person, they'll die. Because you didn'tВҰ334475 warn them, they'll die in their sin, and I won'tВҰ334475 consider the righteous things they did, butВҰ334464 I'llВҰ334487 \add вүҲhold you responsible for their death\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ334489\add* if you warn the godlyВҰ334492 person to stop sinning so that they no longer sin, \add @that person\add* will surely live, since they were warnedВҰ334503, andВҰ334489 you will have saved your own lifeВҰ334507.вҖқ
\s1 Yehezkel's calling
\rem /s1 Ezekiel Will Be Unable to Talk; Ezekiel Isolated and Silenced; The coming ruin of Jerusalem
\p
\v 22 Then Yahweh's handВҰ334514 was on me there, and he told me, вҖң\add вүҲGet ready\add* \add and\add* goВҰ334520 out into the plainВҰ334523, and I'llВҰ334525 speakВҰ334525 with you there.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 I \add вүҲgot up\add* and wentВҰ334529 out into the plainВҰ334532 where Yahweh's glory was staying, like the glory I'd seenВҰ334542 beside the KebarВҰ334547 Canal, so I fell \add вүҲto my knees and bowed low to the ground\add*.
\v 24 ThenВҰ334553 the spiritВҰ334556 enteredВҰ334553 me and stood me up onВҰ334555 my feetВҰ334560, and spokeВҰ334561 withВҰ334555 me, telling me: Go and shut yourselfВҰ334566 up inВҰ334555 yourВҰ334568 houseВҰ334568.
\v 25 Humanity'sВҰ334571 child, \add @people\add* will \add вүҲtie you up withВҰ334582 ropesВҰ334577\add* so that you'll be unable to goВҰ334581 \add вүҲoutside\add*.
\v 26 ThenВҰ334584 I'llВҰ334585 make your tongueВҰ334584 stickВҰ334585 to the roofВҰ334588 of your mouthВҰ334588, so you'll becomeВҰ334592 mute, andВҰ334584 although they're rebelliousВҰ334598 \add вүҲpeople\add*, you won'tВҰ334590 be able to \add вүҲtell them off\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲButВҰ334601\add* when I speakВҰ334601 to you, I'llВҰ334603 open your mouthВҰ334606 so you'll be able to tell them, вҖҳThis is what the masterВҰ334611 YahwehВҰ334611 says.вҖҷ The ones who will hear will hear, \add butВҰ334601\add* the ones who won't listen won't listen, because they're rebelliousВҰ334621 \add вүҲpeople\add*.
\c 4
\ms1 Messages about Yerushalem's destruction
\mr (4:1вҖ“24:27)
\s1 Yehezkel models Yerushalem's invasion
\rem /s1 A Sign of the Coming Siege; The Siege of Jerusalem Portrayed; Ezekiel Acts Out the Siege of Jerusalem; Siege of Jerusalem Symbolized
\p
\v 1 ButВҰ334625 you, humanity'sВҰ334628 child, get yourselfВҰ334631 a brickВҰ334632 and place it \add вүҲin frontВҰ334635 of\add* you and carve YerushalemВҰ334641 CityВҰ334626 on it.
\v 2 ThenВҰ334643 lay siegeВҰ334645 against it, and buildВҰ334646 forts against it. \add вүҲBuild\add* an assault ramp up against it and make camps around it. Place batteringВҰ334658 rams all around it.
\v 3 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* get yourself an iron pan and use it as an iron wall between yourself and \add your representation of\add* the cityВҰ334673, and \add keep looking inВҰ334680 that directionВҰ334674\add*, because it'll be under siege and you're to put the siege against it. That will be a signВҰ334683 to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ334685 people\add*.
\p
\v 4 Then lie on your left side and put the sin of the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ334701 people\add* on it. You'll carry theirВҰ334711 sin for the numberВҰ334703 of daysВҰ334704 you lie down \add as a sign\add* against them.
\v 5 I myself am assigningВҰ334714 to you one day to represent each year of theirВҰ334719 punishment: 390 daysВҰ334721 \add lying on your left side\add*. In that way, you'll carry the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ334729 people's\add* sin.
\v 6 WhenВҰ334733 \add вүҲthat period is over\add*, thenВҰ334733 lie down a secondВҰ334744 time on your rightВҰ334741 side, because you'll carry the sin of \add вүҲYehudah'sВҰ334751 people\add* for fortyВҰ334752 days. I'mВҰ334758 assigningВҰ334758 one day to you for each year.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲKeep looking\add* towards YerushalemВҰ334764, which is under siegeВҰ334763, andВҰ334761 with your arm baredВҰ334768 \add like a warrior\add*, prophesyВҰ334769 againstВҰ334770 itВҰ334770.
\v 8 \add вүҲListen,\add* I'llВҰ334773 \add have you\add* tied with ropesВҰ334775 so you won'tВҰ334776 be able to turnВҰ334778 from one side to the other untilВҰ334783 the daysВҰ334786 \add representing the years\add* of yourВҰ334779 siegeВҰ334787 are over.
\p
\v 9 Take wheatВҰ334793, barleyВҰ334794, beansВҰ334795, lentilsВҰ334796, milletВҰ334797, and speltВҰ334798 for yourself, \add and\add* put them into a single container, and make breadВҰ334806 for yourself according to the numberВҰ334807 of days you'll lie onВҰ334801 your sideвҖ”\add yes,\add* you'll eat it for 390 days.
\v 10 You'll measure 250g by weightВҰ334827 to eat each day, andВҰ334824 you'll eat it during the day atВҰ334827 set times.
\v 11 ThenВҰ334837 you'll measureВҰ334838 out half a litre of waterВҰ334837 to drink each day, andВҰ334837 you'll drink it atВҰ334838 set times.
\v 12 You'll \add cook andВҰ334851\add* eatВҰ334850 \add @that breadВҰ334848\add* as barleyВҰ334849 cakes, butВҰ334848 \add burn sun-dried\add* humanВҰ334854 excrementВҰ334853 to bake itВҰ334855 over \add вүҲwhile they're watching\add*.
\p
\v 13 YahwehВҰ334860 says that that means that the breadВҰ334868 that the IsraeliВҰ334865 peopleВҰ334863 will eatВҰ334862 thereВҰ334873 amongВҰ334870 the \add other\add* nationsВҰ334870 that I'llВҰ334872 banishВҰ334872 them to will be ceremonially uncleanВҰ334869.
