\v 14 They've blown the trumpetВҰ335768 and gotten everythingВҰ335770 readyВҰ335769, butВҰ335769 there'sВҰ335771 no one marching to battleВҰ335773, since my angerВҰ335775 is onВҰ335768 the entireВҰ335778 large group.
\rem /s1 Punishment for Israel's Sins
\p
\v 15 вҖңThe sword is onВҰ335783 the outsideВҰ335783, and plague and famine are insideВҰ335786 the building. People who are in the countrysideВҰ335788 will die by the sword, while famine and plague will consumeВҰ335795 those in the cityВҰ335792.
\v 16 ButВҰ335797 some survivorsВҰ335798 will escapeВҰ335797 from among them, andВҰ335799 will go up into the hills. Like the dovesВҰ335803 \add that live inВҰ335808\add* the valleysВҰ335804, all of them will moanвҖ”each person for theirВҰ335798 \add own\add* disobedience.
\v 17 \add вүҲThey won't be able to use their trembling handsВҰ335812\add*, andВҰ335814 \add вүҲtheir kneesВҰ335816 will feel like liquid\add*.
\v 18 They'll wear sackclothВҰ335821, \add вүҲbutВҰ335820 will be coveredВҰ335822 in\add* terror. \add вүҲTheir faces will display their shameВҰ335829, andВҰ335820 they'll shave their headsВҰ335832\add* \add as a sign of sorrow\add*.
\v 19 They'll throwВҰ335837 their silver into the streetsВҰ335836, and their gold will be like rubbish. Their silver and gold won't be able to rescue them inВҰ335836 the dayВҰ335847 of Yahweh's rage. Their lives won't be saved, and their hungerВҰ335850 won't be satisfiedВҰ335852, because their \add вүҲdisobedience\add* has become a stumblingВҰ335858 blockВҰ335858.
\v 20 In their prideВҰ335864 they took his beautifulВҰ335862 jewelled ornamentsВҰ335863 and made them into their idolatrous figures and detestableВҰ335868 things. Therefore, I'm going to defile those things.
\v 21 I'llВҰ335878 handВҰ335879 those things over to strangersВҰ335881 and to the earthВҰ335884's wickedВҰ335883 people as plunderВҰ335882, and they'll defile them.
\v 22 ThenВҰ335889 I'llВҰ335889 \add вүҲput my hand over my eyes\add* when they defile my cherished placeВҰ335895вҖ”bandits will enterВҰ335896 it andВҰ335889 defile it.
\p
\v 23 вҖңMake a chainВҰ335904, because the \add вүҲcountry\add* is filled with judgementВҰ335908 \add вүҲfor murder\add*, and \add now\add* the cityВҰ335910 is full of violenceВҰ335912.
\v 24 I'll bring the most wicked foreignersВҰ335916 \add here\add*, and they'll \add вүҲtake over\add* \add @the people's\add* housesВҰ335920, and I'll bring the prideВҰ335922 of the powerful \add >people\add* to an end, because their sacredВҰ335925 placesВҰ335925 will be defiled.
\v 25 AnguishВҰ335927 will \add вүҲbe the order of the day\add*, and they'll \add вүҲwish for peaceВҰ335931, butВҰ335930 thereВҰ335932 won'tВҰ335932 be any\add*.
\v 26 DisasterВҰ335934 \add вүҲwill follow\add* disasterВҰ335937 and there'll be rumour after rumour. Then they'll \add вүҲbe wanting\add* a visionВҰ335945 from the prophetВҰ335946, butВҰ335939 the priestВҰ335949 will \add вүҲno longer teach\add* \add God's\add* \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ335947\add*, and advice from the eldersВҰ335951 \add вүЎwill be useless\add*.
\v 27 The kingВҰ335953 will mournВҰ335954 and the princeВҰ335955 will \add вүҲbe overcome by\add* despair, while the handsВҰ335958 of the country's peopleВҰ335959 will tremble inВҰ335966 fear. \add вүҲI'll do that to them just like they did to others\add*. I'll judgeВҰ335967 them by their own standards until they knowВҰ335968 that I am YahwehВҰ335972.вҖқ
\c 8
\ms1 Yahweh's second revelation to Yehezkel (8:1вҖ“10:22)
\s1 Yerushalem's disgusting idol worship
