\p
\v 1 Then in \add вүҲthe middle of\add* the sixthВҰ335978 yearВҰ335977,\f + \fr 8:1 \ft About fourteen months laterвҖ”around mid-September 592 B.C.\f* as I sat in my houseВҰ335984, and Yehudah'sВҰ335986 eldersВҰ335985 sat \add вүҲin frontВҰ335988 of\add* me, my masterВҰ335993 Yahweh's hands fell onВҰ335977 me thereВҰ335991 again.
\v 2 I looked, and wowвҖ”there was \add вүҲsomething that looked a bit like\add* a man. From his hips downwardВҰ336004 there appeared to be fire, and from his hips upwardВҰ336007 there appeared to be something shiningВҰ336012 like glowing metal.\x + \xo 8:2: \xt Eze 1:27.\x*
\v 3 ThenВҰ336014 he reached out something in the shape of a handВҰ336016 and took me by my hairвҖ”the Spirit liftedВҰ336020 me up between earthВҰ336026 and the heavensВҰ336028, and in visionsВҰ336032 from GodВҰ336033, he took me to YerushalemВҰ336031, to the entrance of the innerВҰ336038 northernВҰ336040 gateВҰ336037, whereВҰ336041 the idol was thatВҰ336039 made \add Yahweh\add* very \add вүҲjealous\add*.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ336049 wow, the \add вүҲbrilliant light\add* of Yisrael's godВҰ336053 was thereВҰ336051, just like the visionВҰ336055 thatВҰ336056 I'd seenВҰ336057 onВҰ336058 the plainВҰ336058.\x + \xo 8:4: \xt Eze 1:28.\x*
\v 5 ThenВҰ336060 he told me, вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲlook towards\add* the north.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ336060\add* I \add вүҲlooked towards\add* the north, andВҰ336060 to the north of the gateВҰ336077 leading to the altarВҰ336078вҖ”there inВҰ336082 the entranceВҰ336082вҖ”was the idol \add that caused the\add* jealousyВҰ336080.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ336084\add* he told me, вҖңHumanity's child, do you see what they're doing? Those are \add вүҲhorribly disgusting things\add* thatВҰ336096 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ336097 people\add* are doing here to \add вүҲdriveВҰ336103\add* me far from my own sanctuaryВҰ336105. \add вүҲButВҰ336084\add* you'll see even more disgusting \add things\add* \add soon\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 Then he took me to the courtyardВҰ336118 doorway, and I lookedВҰ336119, and \add вүҲthere was\add* a hole inВҰ336124 the wall.
\v 8 He told me, вҖңHumanity's child, dig into this wall.вҖқ SoВҰ336126 I dug into the wall, andВҰ336126 \add вүҲdiscovered\add* a doorway.
\v 9 ThenВҰ336141 he told me, вҖңGo andВҰ336141 seeВҰ336144 the \add вүҲdisgustingly wickedВҰ336148 things\add* thatВҰ336149 they're doingВҰ336151 there.вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ336154\add* I went through and lookedВҰ336155, and oh dear, there were shapes of everyВҰ336157 creepingВҰ336160 thing and detestableВҰ336162 creature. \add Pictures of\add* all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ336166 people's\add* idolsВҰ336165 were carvedВҰ336168 into the wall all around.
\v 11 Seventy eldersВҰ336178 from the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ336179 people\add* were there, and Shafan'sВҰ336185 son YaazanyahВҰ336182 was standing in the middle of them. They were standing in frontВҰ336189 of the images, and each manВҰ336177 \add вүҲwas holding\add* his incense burner so that the smell of the cloudВҰ336194 of incense went up.
\v 12 ThenВҰ336199 he \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңHumanity's child, do you see what the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ336207\add* eldersВҰ336206 are doingВҰ336210 in the dark? Each one does this in his idolВҰ336214's hidden roomВҰ336213, because they say, вҖҳYahweh doesn't \add even\add* \add вүҲnotice\add* us. Yahweh's \add вүҲabandonedВҰ336221 this country\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ336227 he told me, вҖңTurn againВҰ336229 andВҰ336227 seeВҰ336231 the other \add вүҲterribly disgusting things\add* thatВҰ336234 they're doingВҰ336237,вҖқ
\v 14 and he took me to the gateВҰ336244 at the northernВҰ336251 entranceВҰ336243 of Yahweh's temple, and oh dearвҖ”there were some womenВҰ336255 sittingВҰ336256 there mourning for the \add Babylonian\add* TammuzВҰ336260 \add deity\add*.
