\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ337400 \add вүҲgave me this\add* messageВҰ337398:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, you live among a rebellious \add вүҲpeople group\add* who have eyesВҰ337414 to see, yet they don't see, and who have earsВҰ337419 to hear, butВҰ337417 don't listenВҰ337421, because they're a rebellious \add вүҲpeople group\add*.\x + \xo 12:2: \xt Isa 6:9-10; Jer 5:21; Mrk 8:18.\x*
\p
\v 3 вҖңTherefore, humanity'sВҰ337432 child, \add вүҲpack up your stuff ready to go into\add* exile, andВҰ337429 \add вүҲeach dayВҰ337438 while they're watching\add*, start going out \add somewhere\add*, because \add вүҲwhile they're watching\add*, I'll exile you from your place to anotherВҰ337445 place. Perhaps they'll begin to see, even though they're \add such\add* rebelliousВҰ337451 \add вүҲpeople\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲEach dayВҰ337458 while they're watching,\add* bringВҰ337454 out yourВҰ337455 things for an exile, \add thenВҰ337454\add* as they watch in the eveningВҰ337462, goВҰ337461 out in the way that \add вүҲpeople do\add* when goingВҰ337464 into exile.
\v 5 Dig a hole through the \add city\add* wall \add вүҲwhere they'll see you do it\add*, andВҰ337472 go out through it.
\v 6 \add вүҲWhile they're watching\add*, lift your things up onto your shoulderВҰ337478, and bringВҰ337481 them out inВҰ337480 the darknessВҰ337480. Cover your faceВҰ337482, because you mustn't seeВҰ337485 \add &this\add* land, since I'veВҰ337492 \add вүҲmade you into\add* a signВҰ337491 for the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ337493 people\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 SoВҰ337496 I did just as I was instructedВҰ337499: I brought my things for an exileВҰ337503 out in the daytime, and in the eveningВҰ337505 I dug a hole through the wall by handВҰ337510. I brought my things out in the dark, and liftedВҰ337516 them up onto my shoulderВҰ337515 \add вүҲas they watched\add*.
\rem Need to make next verse style consistent throughout the document: Yahweh GAVE ME a message, vs Yahweh's message CAME TO ME.
\p
\v 8 The \add next\add* morningВҰ337525, YahwehВҰ337523 \add вүҲgave me this\add* messageВҰ337521:
\v 9 вҖңHumanity'sВҰ337535 child, haven't those rebelliousВҰ337537 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ337534 people\add* asked you what you're doingВҰ337540?
\v 10 Tell them that the masterВҰ337546 YahwehВҰ337546 saysВҰ337545 this: вҖҳthis prophetic action concerns the ruler inВҰ337551 YerushalemВҰ337551 andВҰ337553 all the \add other\add* \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ337555 people\add* who are there.вҖҷ
\v 11 Tell them that you're a signВҰ337564 to them, and that everything you've done will happen to themвҖ”they'll be \add вүҲcaptured and taken into exileВҰ337570\add* \add inВҰ337570 another country\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲTheirВҰ337577 leader\add* will lift his things up onto his shoulderВҰ337580 inВҰ337577 the dark, and will goВҰ337583 out through the wall. They'll dig through the wall and take theirВҰ337577 things out. He'll coverВҰ337589 his face, so he won'tВҰ337592 seeВҰ337594 the \add вүҲplace\add* \add he's leaving\add*.
\v 13 I'll spreadВҰ337602 my netВҰ337605 out over him and he'll be caughtВҰ337607 inВҰ337608 my trap, thenВҰ337602 I'll take him \add away\add* to BabylonВҰ337611 (the land of the Chaldeans), butВҰ337602 he won'tВҰ337615 seeВҰ337617 it, and he'll dieВҰ337619 thereВҰ337618.\x + \xo 12:13: \xt 2Ki 25:7; Jer 52:11.\x*
\v 14 I'll also scatter all of his assistants in every direction, andВҰ337621 I'll send out a swordВҰ337633 afterВҰ337635 his entireВҰ337626 army.
\v 15 WhenВҰ337637 I scatterВҰ337645 them among the nationsВҰ337644 andВҰ337645 disperseВҰ337642 them throughout the landsВҰ337647, thenВҰ337637 they'll knowВҰ337637 that I am YahwehВҰ337641.
\v 16 \add вүҲButВҰ337649\add* I'llВҰ337649 spareВҰ337649 a few of them from the swordВҰ337653, famineВҰ337654, and plagueВҰ337655, so they'll be able to record all theirВҰ337662 \add вүҲhardships and ungodly practices\add* inВҰ337663 the \add вүҲcountriesВҰ337663\add* that I take them to, so they'll knowВҰ337668 that I am YahwehВҰ337672.вҖқ
\s1 Portraying the peoples' trembling
\rem /s1 The Sign of the Trembling Prophet; Judgment Not Postponed
\p
\v 17 Then YahwehВҰ337678 \add вүҲgave me\add* \add another\add* messageВҰ337676:
\v 18 вҖңHumanity's child, eatВҰ337687 your food \add вүҲwhile tremblingВҰ337689 withВҰ337686 fear\add*, and drinkВҰ337691 your waterВҰ337688 \add вүҲwhile shaking anxiously\add*,
\v 19 and tell the peopleВҰ337696 inВҰ337710 \add вүҲthis country\add*, вҖҳMy masterВҰ337701 YahwehВҰ337701 saysВҰ337700 this about the inhabitantsВҰ337703 of YerushalemВҰ337704, and the \add вүҲcountry\add* of YisraelВҰ337708, вҖңThey'll anxiously eatВҰ337711 their food and fearfully drinkВҰ337714 their waterВҰ337712, since \add вүҲall the abundance from the land will be devastated\add* becauseВҰ337719 of the violenceВҰ337719 of all \add the people\add* who liveВҰ337722 there.
\v 20 The inhabitedВҰ337726 citiesВҰ337725 will become desolateВҰ337729, andВҰ337725 the land \add itself\add* will become a wastelandВҰ337727. ThenВҰ337725 you'll know that I am YahwehВҰ337735.вҖқ вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Just because it never came true beforeвҖҰ
\rem /s1 A Popular Proverb and an Unpopular Message; A New Proverb for Israel
\p
\v 21 Then YahwehВҰ337741 \add вүҲgave me\add* \add another\add* messageВҰ337739:
\v 22 вҖңHumanity's child, what's that saying that youВҰ337752 have in YisraelВҰ337756? It goes, вҖҳThe daysВҰ337759 \add вүҲseem to go on and on, yet no prophecy ever comesВҰ337760 true.\add*вҖҷ
\v 23 So tell them, вҖҳThis is what the masterВҰ337771 YahwehВҰ337771 saysВҰ337770: I'm going to prove that what they say isn'tВҰ337778 correct, then they'll never say it againВҰ337782 inВҰ337783 YisraelВҰ337783.вҖҷ Tell them, вҖҳIt'll soon be the time when everythingВҰ337792 that the prophets have predicted will happen,
\v 24 because there'll no longer be any false visionsВҰ337802 or \add вүҲpeople-pleasing prophecies\add* within YisraelВҰ337808.
\v 25 I speak, and I \add вүҲput the words thatВҰ337816 I speak into action\add*, because I am Yahweh. The matter will no longer be delayed, because I'll speak this messageВҰ337818 inВҰ337824 your \add вүҲlifetimes\add*, \add you\add* rebelliousВҰ337826 \add вүҲpeople\add*, and then I'll carry it out!вҖҷ That's the masterВҰ337831 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 Then YahwehВҰ337838 \add вүҲgave me\add* \add another\add* messageВҰ337836:
\v 27 вҖңListen, humanity'sВҰ337844 child, the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ337846 people\add* have said, вҖҳThe visionВҰ337850 thatВҰ337851 \add @the prophet\add* sees is for many yearsВҰ337855 from now, and he prophesies about far-off timesВҰ337857,вҖҷ
\v 28 so tell them, вҖҳThe master YahwehВҰ337867 says this: вҖҳMy wordsВҰ337875 won'tВҰ337869 be delayed any longer, butВҰ337879 the messageВҰ337878 thatВҰ337876 I've given will be \add вүҲput into effect\add*. That's the master Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 Condemning the false prophets
\rem /s1 Prophecy against False Male Prophets; False Prophets Condemned; Judgment against False Prophets
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ337888 \add вүҲgave me\add* \add another\add* messageВҰ337886:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, prophesy againstВҰ337896 the prophets who are prophesying in YisraelВҰ337899, andВҰ337901 tell those who are prophesying out of theirВҰ337903 own imaginationsВҰ337903, вҖҳListen to Yahweh's messageВҰ337905.
\v 3 My masterВҰ337911 YahwehВҰ337911 saysВҰ337910 this: вҖҳFoolish prophetsВҰ337916 who follow theirВҰ337921 own spiritВҰ337921 andВҰ337922 haven't \add actually\add* seenВҰ337923 any \add vision\add* \add вүҲwon'tВҰ337922 end well\add*.
\v 4 YisraelВҰ337928, yourВҰ337927 prophetsВҰ337927 have been like jackalsВҰ337925 inВҰ337926 the wastelands.
\v 5 You haven't gone to the breaks in the \add #walls\add* around the IsraeliВҰ337938 \add cities\add* and repairedВҰ337934 them, in order to \add вүҲbe able to defend yourselves well during\add* the battleВҰ337941 onВҰ337933 Yahweh's \add chosen\add* dayВҰ337942.
\v 6 The people have false visions and make false predictions. Yahweh hasn't sentВҰ337955 thoseВҰ337949 who sayВҰ337949 that they're bringing Yahweh's declaration, \add вүҲbutВҰ337947 nevertheless they've made people hope that their messagesВҰ337958 would come true\add*.
\v 7 Haven't you had false visionsВҰ337961 and made false predictionsвҖ”all of you who say that you're bringing Yahweh's declaration when I myself haven't spokenВҰ337974?вҖҷ
\p
\v 8 Therefore the master Yahweh says this, вҖҳBecause you \add people\add* have \add вүҲpresented\add* falseВҰ337986 visions and have told lies, this is the master Yahweh's declaration againstВҰ337989 you:
\v 9 \add вүҲI'll punish\add* the prophetsВҰ337998 who have lying visionsВҰ337999 andВҰ337994 who make falseВҰ338002 predictions. They won'tВҰ338005 be \add allowed\add* in the assembly of my peopleВҰ338004, or enrolled in the record of Yisrael's \add вүҲdescendants\add*. They mustn't goВҰ338019 to the land of YisraelВҰ338011вҖ”\add вүҲthat's how\add* you \add people\add* will knowВҰ338020 that I am the masterВҰ338023 YahwehВҰ338023.
\p
\v 10 Also becauseВҰ338027 they led my peopleВҰ338031 astrayВҰ338028 and said, вҖңPeace,вҖқ when there'sВҰ338034 no peace, \add it's as if\add* they're buildingВҰ338037 a wall and then whitewashingВҰ338042 it.вҖҷ\x + \xo 13:10: \xt Jer 6:14; 8:11.\x*
\v 11 Tell the ones who are whitewashingВҰ338048 the wall that it'll fall down. There'll be a downpour, then I'll send hailstones to make it fall down, and a strong wind to breakВҰ338060 it down.
\v 12 See, the wall will fall down. Haven't others \add вүҲasked\add* you whereВҰ338068 the whiteВҰ338069 coating \add went\add* thatВҰ338070 you put on it?
\p
\v 13 Therefore my masterВҰ338077 YahwehВҰ338077 says this: вҖҳIn my rage, I'llВҰ338079 bring a storm, and inВҰ338083 my angerВҰ338086, there'll be \add вүҲheavy rain causing floods\add*. In my rage, hailstones will completelyВҰ338091 destroyВҰ338091 \add @Yerushalem\add*.
\v 14 I'll tear down the wall that you covered withВҰ338109 whitewashВҰ338100, and I'll demolish it to ground level and expose itsВҰ338109 foundationsВҰ338106. SoВҰ338093 it'll fall, and you'll be annihilated inВҰ338109 the middle of it all. ThenВҰ338093 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ338110 that I am YahwehВҰ338114.
\p
\v 15 In my rageВҰ338119 I'll annihilate the wall andВҰ338116 thoseВҰ338129 who whitewashed it. I'll tell you, вҖңThe wall doesn't exist anymore, nor do the people who whitewashed itвҖ”
\v 16 those IsraeliВҰ338132 prophets who prophesied about YerushalemВҰ338138 and had visionsВҰ338141 of peace for it. ButВҰ338139 thereВҰ338143 isn'tВҰ338143 any peace! That's the masterВҰ338146 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ вҖҷ
\rem /s1 Prophecy against False Female Prophets; Judgment against False Women Prophets
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ338151\add*, humanity'sВҰ338153 child, \add вүҲturn your attention to\add* your people'sВҰ338159 daughtersВҰ338158 and prophesy againstВҰ338156 them \add вүҲbecause they invented prophecies in theirВҰ338161 own imaginationsВҰ338161\add*.
\v 18 Tell \add >them\add* that the masterВҰ338170 YahwehВҰ338170 says this: вҖҳThe women \add вүҲwon't end well\add* who sew magic charms onto every part of their handsВҰ338180, and make headbands for people of \add вүҲevery walk of life\add* \add that are used to deceive people and\add* hunt them down. \add Do you people really think you can get away with\add* hunting down my people, butВҰ338165 thenВҰ338165 save your own lives?
\v 19 You've profanedВҰ338198 me among my people for handfulsВҰ338204 of barleyВҰ338205 and crumbs of breadВҰ338207. \add вүЎYou people have\add* killed people who shouldn't have died, and saved the lives of those who shouldn't have continued to live, because of your lies to my people who heard you.
\p
\v 20 Therefore my masterВҰ338231 YahwehВҰ338231 saysВҰ338229 this: вҖҳI'm againstВҰ338234 the magicВҰ338236 charms thatВҰ338237 you've used to \add вүҲlure\add* the people in as if they were birds. Indeed, I'll tear them from your arms, and I'll let the people you've trapped like birds go free.
\v 21 I'llВҰ338261 tear away your headbands andВҰ338261 rescue my peopleВҰ338268 from your \add вүҲcontrol\add* so they'll no longer be trapped inВҰ338274 your \add вүҲsystem\add*. ThenВҰ338261 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ338276 that I am YahwehВҰ338280.
\p
\v 22 BecauseВҰ338282 you've discouraged the righteousВҰ338286 people with lies (even though IВҰ338288 didn'tВҰ338289 desire their discouragement), and because you \add people\add* \add вүҲencouraged the actions\add* of the wickedВҰ338293 people instead so they won'tВҰ338289 changeВҰ338296 their waysВҰ338297 to saveВҰ338299 their livesВҰ338299,
\v 23 \add вүҲbecause of that\add*, you'll no longer have false visionsВҰ338305 or continue to make predictions, because I'llВҰ338310 rescueВҰ338310 my peopleВҰ338313 out of yourВҰ338314 \add вүҲcontrol\add*. Then you'll knowВҰ338315 that I am YahwehВҰ338319.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 14
\s1 Yahweh's hate for idols
\rem /s1 Idolaters Condemned; God's Judgments Justified; God Condemns Idolatry; The Idolatry of Israel's Leaders
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOne day\add* \add some\add* of the IsraeliВҰ338325 eldersВҰ338324 cameВҰ338321 andВҰ338326 sat down \add to talk\add*,
\v 2 andВҰ338330 YahwehВҰ338333 \add вүҲgave\add* me this messageВҰ338331:
\v 3 вҖңHumanity's child, theseВҰ338341 menВҰ338340 have taken their idolsВҰ338343 \add вүҲto be their gods\add*, and \add вүҲtheir choice to disobey makes it very difficult for them to relate to me\add*. Should I \add вүҲeven let them ask me anything\add*?
\p
\v 4 Therefore tell them that the masterВҰ338367 Yahweh says this: вҖҳEvery IsraeliВҰ338372 person who \add вүҲmakes their idols their priority\add*, or who \add вүҲallows their disobedience to separate them from me\add*, and who then comesВҰ338386 to a prophetВҰ338389, I, Yahweh, will answerВҰ338392 them according to \add вүҲhow many idols they have\add*.
\v 5 I'll do that so that I can \add вүҲreclaim the IsraeliВҰ338403 people whose values are now far from mine due to\add* theirВҰ338411 idolsВҰ338410.
\p
\v 6 Therefore tell the IsraeliВҰ338420 people that the masterВҰ338423 YahwehВҰ338423 saysВҰ338422 this: вҖҳ\add вүҲChange your behaviour\add* and turn away from your idolsВҰ338428. \add вүҲMake a decision to stop disobeying me by doing those evil things\add*.
\p
\v 7 Any \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ338440 person\add* or any foreigner residing inВҰ338445 YisraelВҰ338440 who deserts me, who takes idolsВҰ338449 \add вүҲto be their gods\add* and \add вүҲallows their disobedience to separateВҰ338446 them from me\add*, and who then comesВҰ338458 to a prophetВҰ338461 to \add вүҲrequest my guidance\add*, I, YahwehВҰ338467, will answerВҰ338468 that person myselfВҰ338468.
\v 8 I'llВҰ338473 \add вүҲclearly show my disapproval\add* and make that personВҰ338475 into a signВҰ338478 \add for others\add* and into a \add вүҲtalking point\add*, and they'll be \add вүҲisolated from the rest of\add* my peopleВҰ338482, and you \add people\add* will knowВҰ338483 that I am YahwehВҰ338487.
\p
\v 9 If a prophet is deceived and speaksВҰ338494 a messageВҰ338495, then I, YahwehВҰ338497, will deceive that prophet. I'llВҰ338502 \add вүҲtake action\add* against him and destroyВҰ338507 him \add to remove him\add* from amongВҰ338508 the Israeli peopleВҰ338509.
\v 10 \add вүҲBoth the prophetВҰ338517 and the one who asks him for advice will be guilty, and I'll punish both of them for theirВҰ338513 disobedience.\add*
\v 11 Because of that, the IsraeliВҰ338525 people will no longer wanderВҰ338523 away from followingВҰ338528 me, nor defile themselvesВҰ338531 any longer through all their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*. They'll be my people, and I'llВҰ338540 be their godВҰ338542. That's the masterВҰ338544 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Turning the country into wasteland
\rem /s1 Judgment Inescapable; Noah, Daniel, and Job; The Certainty of the Lord's Judgment
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ338551 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ338549:
\v 13 вҖңHumanity's child, when a \add вүҲcountry\add* sins against me by \add вүҲchoosing to worship other gods\add*, so that I \add вүҲdecide to take action\add* against it, \add вүҲthen\add* I'll breakВҰ338569 the \add вүҲcycle of food production\add* and sendВҰ338574 a famineВҰ338577 out over it. I'll \add вүҲpunish\add* both people and animalsВҰ338581 from that land
\v 14 \add in such a way that\add* even if NoahВҰ338588, Daniel, andВҰ338583 YobВҰ338592 \add (Job)\add* \add вүҲlived in that place\add*, they could only rescue their own livesВҰ338596 by being \add вүҲblameless in my sight\add*. That's the masterВҰ338598 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 15 If I send \add вүҲvicious wild animals\add* through the \add вүҲcountry\add* and make it barren so that it becomesВҰ338608 a wasteland where no one can passВҰ338605 through because of those animals,
\v 16 then even if those same threeВҰ338615 menВҰ338616 were inВҰ338618 it, as IВҰ338624 live, declares the masterВҰ338623 YahwehВҰ338623, they wouldn't be able to rescue even their own \add вүҲchildren\add*вҖ”only their own lives would be saved, butВҰ338628 the land \add itself\add* would become a wasteland.
\p
\v 17 Or if I bringВҰ338641 a sword against that \add вүҲcountry\add* and say, вҖҳSword, go through the land and \add вүҲeliminate both the\add* people and \add domestic\add* animalsВҰ338653 from itвҖҷ,
\v 18 thenВҰ338655 even if those threeВҰ338655 menВҰ338656 were inВҰ338658 itВҰ338658, as IВҰ338664 live, declares the masterВҰ338663 YahwehВҰ338663, they wouldn't be able to rescue even their own sonsВҰ338667 or daughtersВҰ338668вҖ”only their own lives would be saved.
\p
\v 19 Or if I sendВҰ338676 a plague against that \add вүҲcountry\add* and pour out my rageВҰ338682 against it through bloodshedВҰ338684, inВҰ338684 order to \add вүҲeliminate both the\add* people and the \add domestic\add* animalsВҰ338688,
\v 20 as surely as I live, even if Noah, Daniel, and YobВҰ338694 were in that country, they wouldn't be able to rescue even their sons and daughtersВҰ338707. They'd save only themselves by being \add вүҲblameless in myВҰ338698 sight\add*. That's the masterВҰ338700 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 21 TheВҰ338719 masterВҰ338718 YahwehВҰ338718 saysВҰ338717 this: вҖҳI'llВҰ338732 certainly make things worse by sending my fourВҰ338723 punishments againstВҰ338733 YerushalemВҰ338735 to \add вүҲeliminate both the\add* people and the \add domestic\add* animals from it: famineВҰ338728, swordВҰ338727, wild animals, and plagueВҰ338731.\x + \xo 14:21: \xt Rev 6:8.\x*
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ338741 listen!\add* \add Despite that,\add* a remnantВҰ338745 will be left inВҰ338744 \add @the city\add*вҖ”survivors who'll go out withВҰ338744 sonsВҰ338747 and daughtersВҰ338748. \add вүҲYes,\add* they'll go out to you, and you'll see their behaviour and actionsВҰ338758 and \add вүҲunderstand why they deserved\add* the punishment that I sent to YerushalemВҰ338767, and aboutВҰ338750 everything else that I'veВҰ338764 sent against the \add вүҲcountry\add*.
\v 23 The survivors will relieve you \add people\add* when you seeВҰ338779 their behaviour andВҰ338775 their actionsВҰ338785, because you'll knowВҰ338786 that all those things that I'veВҰ338790 done against \add @Yerushalem\add*, I \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ338788 do them withoutВҰ338789 good reason\add*. That's the masterВҰ338799 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 15
\s1 The vine stem is useless as wood
\rem /s1 A Parable about a Vine; The people and their leaders condemned; JerusalemвҖ”a Useless Vine; The Useless Vine; Jerusalem, A Useless Vine
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ338806 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ338804:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, how is a vineВҰ338818 better than any treeВҰ338821 withВҰ338825 branchesВҰ338822 inВҰ338825 a forestВҰ338826?
\v 3 Do peopleВҰ338835 takeВҰ338835 wood from \add @a vine\add* to make anythingВҰ338832? Would anyone \add вүҲuse\add* \add @vine wood\add* \add even\add* to make something to hang a mug on?
\v 4 If it's \add вүҲused as firewood\add*, and if the fire burns bothВҰ338849 ends, and even the middleВҰ338853, is it good \add wood, or indeed good\add* for anythingВҰ338856?
\v 5 \add вүҲOriginally,\add* \add @the vine wood\add* couldn't \add be used to\add* make anything, so surely, when the fireВҰ338867's burnt it, it still can'tВҰ338861 do anything useful.
\p
\v 6 Therefore the masterВҰ338878 YahwehВҰ338878 saysВҰ338877 this: вҖҳUnlike the treesВҰ338884 in the forestsВҰ338885, I'veВҰ338892 given the vineВҰ338883 as fuel for fires. I'll act in the same way toward Yerushalem'sВҰ338896 inhabitantsВҰ338895,
\v 7 andВҰ338898 I'llВҰ338898 \add вүҲstart to take action\add* against them. Even if they get out of the fire, the fire will still consumeВҰ338906 them, so you \add people\add* will know that I am YahwehВҰ338911, when I \add вүҲtake action\add* against them.
\v 8 ThenВҰ338918 I'llВҰ338918 make the land into an abandoned wasteland becauseВҰ338923 theyВҰ338924 \add вүҲchose to worship other gods\add*. That's the masterВҰ338927 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 16
\s1 Unfaithful Yerushalem's vile practices
\rem /s1 JerusalemвҖ”an Unfaithful Wife; Jerusalem the Unfaithful; An Allegory of Unfaithful Jerusalem; God's Faithless Bride
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ338934 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ338932:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, inform YerushalemВҰ338944 about \add вүҲtheir detestable behaviour\add*,
\v 3 and declare that the masterВҰ338953 YahwehВҰ338953 saysВҰ338952 this to YerushalemВҰ338955: Your beginning and your birthВҰ338957 took place in the land of Canaan, your fatherВҰ338960 was an AmoriteВҰ338961, and your motherВҰ338962 was a HittiteВҰ338963.\f + \fr 16:3 \ft A bunch of insults to the proud Israelis.\f*
\v 4 \add вүҲWhenВҰ338965 you were born\add*, your mother didn'tВҰ338969 cut your cord, nor did she cleanВҰ338977 you with waterВҰ338973 or rub you down with salt, or wrap cloth around you.
\v 5 No \add вүҲone cared enough\add* about you to do any of theseВҰ338993 things for youвҖ”to be compassionate toward you. YourВҰ339002 lifeВҰ339002 \add вүҲwas despised\add* \add and\add* you were thrownВҰ338996 out into the open fieldВҰ339000 onВҰ339001 the \add very\add* dayВҰ339003 that you were born.
\p
\v 6 ButВҰ339007 I went past, andВҰ339007 I saw you, \add Yerushalem,\add* writhing in your own blood, so I said to you \add as you lay there\add* in your blood, вҖңLive!вҖқ\f + \fr 16:6 \ft The last part of the verse is repeated in the Hebrew.\f*
\v 7 I made you grow like a plantВҰ339022 inВҰ339028 the countrysideВҰ339023. You grew up and became tall, and you became the \add вүҲmost precious\add* jewelВҰ339028. Your breastsВҰ339030 became firm, and your hair grew thick, even though you'd been nakedВҰ339035 and bare.
\p
\v 8 I wentВҰ339052 past again and saw you. Wow, the time of love came for you, so I spreadВҰ339045 my robe out over you and coveredВҰ339048 yourВҰ339042 nakednessВҰ339049. ThenВҰ339038 I \add вүҲmade a promise\add* to you and brought you into a contract and you becameВҰ339058 mine. That's the masterВҰ339056 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 9 I washedВҰ339063 you, \add Yerushalem,\add* withВҰ339062 waterВҰ339062, and rinsed your bloodВҰ339064 off you, and I \add вүҲput lotion onВҰ339062 your skin\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ339069 I dressed you in embroidered clothesВҰ339069 andВҰ339069 put leatherВҰ339072 sandalsВҰ339071 onВҰ339074 your feet. I wrappedВҰ339073 you in fine linenВҰ339074, thenВҰ339069 coveredВҰ339075 you withВҰ339074 silk.
\v 11 Next I adornedВҰ339078 youВҰ339078 with jewellery, and I put braceletsВҰ339081 on your handsВҰ339084 and a chainВҰ339085 around your neck.
\v 12 I put a ring in your nose and earringsВҰ339095 in your earsВҰ339098, and a beautifulВҰ339100 crownВҰ339099 onВҰ339101 your headВҰ339101.
\v 13 SoВҰ339103 you were adornedВҰ339103 withВҰ339117 goldВҰ339104 and silverВҰ339105, and you were dressed inВҰ339117 fine linenВҰ339107, silk, and embroideredВҰ339110 clothesВҰ339106. You ateВҰ339114 \add good food made from\add* fine flourВҰ339111, honeyВҰ339112, and oilВҰ339113, and you were very beautifulВҰ339116, and you became a queenВҰ339120.
\v 14 Your \add вүҲreputation\add*, \add Yerushalem,\add* \add вүҲspread\add* amongВҰ339125 the nationsВҰ339125 because of your beautyВҰ339126, because it was perfectВҰ339129 inВҰ339125 the majesty I'd given you. That's the masterВҰ339137 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ339140 \add Yerushalem,\add* you trustedВҰ339140 inВҰ339141 your own beauty, and you actedВҰ339142 like a prostitute because of your reputation. You \add вүҲflirted withВҰ339141 everyoneВҰ339152 going past, and prostituted yourself\add*, so that your beauty became theirs.
\v 16 ThenВҰ339159 you tookВҰ339159 yourВҰ339160 clothesВҰ339160 and made \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* for yourself with them, decorated in various colours, and there you actedВҰ339166 like a prostituteВҰ339166. This shouldn'tВҰ339168 have happened, nor should such a thing exist.
\v 17 You tookВҰ339173 the fine goldВҰ339176 and silverВҰ339177 jewellery thatВҰ339178 I gaveВҰ339179 you, and you made maleВҰ339185 sculptures for yourselves, and you \add вүҲbehaved withВҰ339188 them like a prostituteВҰ339186 would\add*.
\v 18 You tookВҰ339190 yourВҰ339194 embroideredВҰ339194 garments and coveredВҰ339195 \add @those idols\add*, and youВҰ339198 \add вүҲoffered\add* my oils and perfumes to them.
\v 19 The \add high-quality\add* breadВҰ339202 thatВҰ339203 I gaveВҰ339205 you (made with fine flourВҰ339207, oilВҰ339208, and honeyВҰ339209), you placed \add вүҲin front of\add* them to be a fragrant aromaВҰ339213, \add вүҲand indeed itВҰ339211 was\add*. That's the masterВҰ339217 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ339220 you tookВҰ339220 your sonsВҰ339223 and daughtersВҰ339226 that you bore for me, and you sacrificedВҰ339230 them to \add @those idols\add* to be devouredВҰ339232 as food. Are your acts of prostitutionВҰ339234 a smallВҰ339233 matter?
\v 21 You slaughteredВҰ339237 my childrenВҰ339240 for the idols andВҰ339241 made them passВҰ339242 throughВҰ339242 the fire.
\v 22 In all your \add вүҲevil goings onВҰ339258\add* and your acts of prostitutionВҰ339250, you \add вүҲnever thought back to\add* the daysВҰ339256 \add вүҲwhen you were young\add*, when you were nakedВҰ339259 and bare as you thrashed aboutВҰ339261 inВҰ339258 your \add own\add* bloodВҰ339262.
\rem /s1 Jerusalem's Life as a Prostitute
\v 23 After all yourВҰ339269 wickednessВҰ339269, \add вүҲyou won't end well\add*. That's the masterВҰ339274 Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 The anger of God on Yerushalem
\p
\v 24 You made yourself a moundВҰ339280 andВҰ339282 builtВҰ339277 a raised shrine in every public square.
\v 25 You builtВҰ339296 your raised platform at the top of everyВҰ339292 street and made your beautyВҰ339301 a disgrace, and you spreadВҰ339302 your legs for anyoneВҰ339308 who passedВҰ339308 by, and you multiplied your acts of prostitutionВҰ339298.
\v 26 You've actedВҰ339315 like a prostitute with your lusty neighboursВҰ339321 the Egyptians, andВҰ339315 you committed many more acts of prostitution, provokingВҰ339328 me to angerВҰ339328.
\p
\v 27 Listen, I'll hit you withВҰ339337 my hand andВҰ339330 cut off your food \add supply\add*. I'll hand your life over to your enemiesВҰ339338, the daughtersВҰ339339 of the PhilistinesВҰ339340, who were ashamedВҰ339341 of your obscene behaviour.
\p
\v 28 You've acted like a prostitute with the Assyrians becauseВҰ339350 you couldn't be satisfied. You acted like a prostitute andВҰ339345 still you weren't satisfied.
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ339357\add* you performed many more acts of prostitutionВҰ339360 inВҰ339368 \add Babylonia\add* (the \add вүҲcountry\add* of the ChaldeanВҰ339365 merchantsВҰ339364), andВҰ339357 even that didn'tВҰ339369 satisfyВҰ339370 you.
\v 30 Your heartВҰ339374 is so sick that you would do things like thatвҖ”things that only a shameless prostituteВҰ339387 would do. That's the masterВҰ339376 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 31 You made your moundsВҰ339391 at the top of every street and builtВҰ339390 your tall shrines in every public square, \add вүҲyet\add* you weren't like a prostituteВҰ339406, \add вүҲin the sense that\add* you scoffed at taking payment.
\v 32 You adulterousВҰ339411 womanВҰ339410, you \add вүҲprefer\add* strangersВҰ339417 \add вүҲover\add* your husbandВҰ339413.
\v 33 \add It's normal for\add* \add вүҲclients to pay\add* the prostitute, butВҰ339425 you \add do the opposite\add*: you giveВҰ339422 your wages to all your loversВҰ339432 and bribeВҰ339433 them to comeВҰ339435 to you from all aroundВҰ339437 for your acts of prostitution.
\v 34 \add вүҲYes,\add* there's a difference between you andВҰ339440 other womenВҰ339446. No one offers paymentВҰ339453 for you to act as a prostituteВҰ339450. You're the very oppositeВҰ339459вҖ”you \add вүҲpaid\add* them \add вүҲbutВҰ339440\add* nothing was givenВҰ339455 to you.
\s1 The punishment of God of Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Judgment on Jerusalem's Prostitution; God's Judgment on Jerusalem
\p
\v 35 Therefore, \add Yerushalem\add*, you prostituteВҰ339462, listenВҰ339463 to Yahweh's messageВҰ339464.
\v 36 The masterВҰ339472 YahwehВҰ339472 saysВҰ339471 this: вҖҳBecause you've pouredВҰ339475 out your lust and uncoveredВҰ339477 your nakednessВҰ339478 through your acts of prostitutionВҰ339479 with your loversВҰ339482 and with all your detestableВҰ339487 idolsВҰ339486, and becauseВҰ339474 you gaveВҰ339491 them your children'sВҰ339489 bloodВҰ339488,
\v 37 then listen: I'll gather all your loversВҰ339501 that you've met, \add вүҲincludingВҰ339505 the ones\add* you lovedВҰ339509 and the ones you hatedВҰ339514вҖ”I'll gather them againstВҰ339517 you on every side. I'll uncoverВҰ339519 your nakedness for them so they see all your nakedness.
\v 38 ThenВҰ339529 I'll punish you for your adulteryВҰ339531 and the shedding of blood, and I'll bringВҰ339534 on you the bloodshed of my anger and passion.
\v 39 I'llВҰ339539 \add вүҲallow them to conquer you\add* so they'll \add вүҲtear apart\add* your moundsВҰ339543 and breakВҰ339544 down your tallВҰ339545 shrinesВҰ339545, and they'll stripВҰ339546 your clothesВҰ339548 off you and takeВҰ339549 all your jewelleryвҖ”leaving you nakedВҰ339553 and bare.
\p
\v 40 ThenВҰ339556 they'll bringВҰ339556 a crowd up againstВҰ339557 you and \add вүҲthrow heavy stonesВҰ339561 atВҰ339561 you\add*, and they'll cut you apart withВҰ339561 theirВҰ339563 swordsВҰ339563.
\v 41 They'll burnВҰ339565 down your housesВҰ339566 and \add вүҲpunish you in several ways\add* in the sightВҰ339572 of many womenВҰ339573, because I'llВҰ339575 put a stop to your prostitutionВҰ339576, and you'll no longer pay your lovers.
\v 42 ThenВҰ339585 I'll calm my rageВҰ339586 againstВҰ339594 you. My angerВҰ339586 will leave you, because I'll be satisfiedВҰ339585 andВҰ339585 won'tВҰ339592 be angryВҰ339593 \add at you\add* any longer.
\p
\v 43 BecauseВҰ339596 you didn'tВҰ339598 call to mind your younger daysВҰ339604, and made me shake withВҰ339618 anger because of all those things, thereforeВҰ339615, listen: I myself will bring the punishment for what you've done down onto your own headВҰ339618. That's the masterВҰ339621 Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 Ke what the mother like just the child woman
\p Haven't you added prostitution to all your other detestable practices?
\rem /s1 Like Mother, Like Daughter
\v 44 Listen, everyoneВҰ339635 who speaksВҰ339639 proverbsВҰ339637 aboutВҰ339638 youВҰ339638 will sayВҰ339640, вҖңLike motherВҰ339641, like daughterВҰ339642.вҖқ
\v 45 You are the daughterВҰ339644 of your mother, who detested her husband and her children, and you are the sister of your sisters, who detested their husbands and their children. YourВҰ339646 mother was a HittiteВҰ339659, and your fatherВҰ339660 was an AmoriteВҰ339661.
\p
\v 46 YourВҰ339671 olderВҰ339664 sister was ShomronВҰ339665 \add (SamariaВҰ339665)\add*, and her daughters were the ones living in the northВҰ339671, while yourВҰ339671 youngerВҰ339673 sister was the one living southВҰ339676 of you, that is, SodomВҰ339677 and her daughters.
\v 47 \add вүҲNot only did you follow\add* their customs and copy their behaviourВҰ339688 and practices, butВҰ339680 inВҰ339681 \add вүҲeverything you did\add*, you've been \em worse\em* than they were.
\p
\v 48 This is the masterВҰ339698 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, your sisterВҰ339704 SodomВҰ339703 and her daughters didn't do as much evil as you and your daughters have done.
\v 49 Listen, yourВҰ339718 sisterВҰ339718 Sodom'sВҰ339717 sin was that sheВҰ339733 was arrogant in herВҰ339727 leisure, careless and unconcerned about anything. She didn'tВҰ339732 \add вүҲassist\add* the poor and needyВҰ339731 people.
\v 50 She was arrogant andВҰ339735 performed disgusting actions \add вүҲin front of\add* me, so I took them away, just as you've seen.
\p
\v 51 As for ShomronВҰ339745, they didn'tВҰ339748 commit even half of your sinsВҰ339747. No, you've done many more disgusting things than they did, and you've shown thatВҰ339763 your sistersВҰ339758 were better than you, because of all the disgusting things you do.
\v 52 Also how you display your own shameвҖ”you'veВҰ339774 shown thatВҰ339777 your sisters were better than you by the sinsВҰ339776 you committed inВҰ339776 all those disgusting ways. Your sisters now seem better than you.
\rem /s1 Sodom and Samaria Will Be Restored
\p
\v 53 From theirВҰ339795 captivity, I'llВҰ339792 restoreВҰ339792 the fortunes of SodomВҰ339800 and her daughters, and of ShomronВҰ339806 and her daughters, and your fortunes \add вүҲwill be similar\add*,\f + \fr 16:53 \ft i.e., to go into captivity, but then after a time, to be restored.\f*
\v 54 so that you'll display yourВҰ339815 shame. You'll be humiliated because of everything you'veВҰ339820 done, and inВҰ339821 that way you'll be a consolationВҰ339821 to \add @Sodom and Shomron\add*.
\v 55 Your sisterВҰ339824 SodomВҰ339825 and her daughters will be restored to their former condition, and ShomronВҰ339829 and her daughters will be restored \add вүҲsimilarly\add*. ThenВҰ339824 you and your daughters will be restored to your former condition.
\v 56 \add вүҲYou never even mentionedВҰ339842 your sisterВҰ339841 SodomВҰ339840 inВҰ339843 the period when you were proud\add*,
\v 57 beforeВҰ339847 your wickednessВҰ339849 was revealed. ButВҰ339856 now you're an object of scorn to the daughters of AramВҰ339855 \add (SyriaВҰ339855)\add* and to all the daughters of the PhilistinesВҰ339860 around herВҰ339858. People all around despiseВҰ339861 you.
\v 58 You'll display your shame and your disgusting actions. That's Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 The agreement without ending
\rem /s1 An Everlasting Covenant; A Covenant That Lasts Forever
\p
\v 59 TheВҰ339881 masterВҰ339880 YahwehВҰ339880 saysВҰ339879 this: вҖҳI'llВҰ339882 deal with you as you deserveвҖ”you who've despisedВҰ339889 your oath by breakingВҰ339891 \add &our\add* agreement.
\v 60 ButВҰ339894 I myself will call to mind my agreement with you that was made \add вүҲwhen you were younger\add*, andВҰ339894 I'llВҰ339894 establishВҰ339902 a never-ending agreement with you.
\v 61 ThenВҰ339907 you'll call to mind your behaviour and be ashamedВҰ339911 when you \add вүҲadopt\add* your olderВҰ339916 and youngerВҰ339920 sistersВҰ339915. I'llВҰ339922 giveВҰ339922 them to you as daughtersВҰ339925, butВҰ339907 not because of your agreement.
\v 62 I myself will establishВҰ339929 my agreement with you, andВҰ339935 you'll knowВҰ339935 that I am YahwehВҰ339939,
\v 63 so that you'll call everything to mind and be ashamedВҰ339943. Then you'll no longer open your mouthВҰ339950 to speak, because of your shame, when I've forgivenВҰ339953 you for everything you'veВҰ339959 done. That's the masterВҰ339961 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 17
\s1 The two eagles and the vine
\rem /s1 A Story of Two Eagles; The Two Eagles and the Vine; Two Eagles and a Vine; The Parable of the Eagles and the Vine
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ339968 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ339966:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity'sВҰ339982 child, present a riddle andВҰ339977 tellВҰ339977 a parableВҰ339978 to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ339981 people\add*.
\v 3 Tell \add >them\add*, вҖҳThe masterВҰ339989 YahwehВҰ339989 saysВҰ339987 this: вҖҳA large eagleВҰ339991, with large wingsВҰ339994 full of multi-coloured feathersВҰ339996, and longВҰ339995 pinions, wentВҰ340003 to LebanonВҰ340006 and grabbed hold of the top of a cedarВҰ340011 tree.
\v 4 He broke off the top shootВҰ340015 of \add @the tree\add* and took it to Canaan \add where he\add* placedВҰ340024 it inВҰ340022 a cityВҰ340022 \add full\add* of merchantsВҰ340021.
\v 5 He \add вүҲalso\add* tookВҰ340026 some of the land's seed andВҰ340026 planted it inВҰ340030 fertile soil, \add вүҲbeside a large body of waterВҰ340036 where\add* a willowВҰ340038 \add might grow\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ340041 \add @the seed\add* sproutedВҰ340041 and became a spreading vine low to the ground. Its branches turnedВҰ340047 toward him, and its rootsВҰ340050 grew \add вүҲdown below\add*, so it became a vine and producedВҰ340055 branches and sent out shootsВҰ340056.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ340060\add* there was another large eagle with large wingsВҰ340066 and many feathers. Oh wow, that vineВҰ340071 turned its rootsВҰ340074 toward this eagle, and it spread out its branchesВҰ340076 toward the eagle from the place it had been plantedВҰ340083 so it might get wateredВҰ340080.
\v 8 It had been plantedВҰ340094 in goodВҰ340088 soil beside a large body of waterВҰ340091 so it would grow branchesВҰ340096 and produceВҰ340098 fruitВҰ340098, to become a magnificent vineВҰ340100.вҖҷ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲAsk\add* \add the people\add*: вҖҳThe masterВҰ340107 YahwehВҰ340107 wants to know if it'll prosperВҰ340109. Won't it be uprooted and strippedВҰ340119 of its fruitВҰ340117 so that it withersВҰ340120, and all its freshВҰ340123 growthВҰ340124 will dry out? \add вүҲYou wouldn't have to be very strong or get lots of people to help\add* to pull it out by its roots.
\v 10 SoВҰ340137 listen. After it had been plantedВҰ340138, would it thriveВҰ340139? Wouldn't it wither up when the easternВҰ340144 windВҰ340143 touchesВҰ340141 it? \add Yes,\add* it would wither right up inВҰ340142 the garden plot whereВҰ340150 it sprouted.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The vine part of the parable explained
\rem /s1 The Riddle Explained; The Parable Is Explained
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ340157 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ340155:
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲAsk\add* those rebelliousВҰ340165 \add вүҲpeople\add*, вҖҳDon't you know what those things mean? Listen, the king of Babylon came to YerushalemВҰ340178 and captured its king and its princesВҰ340185 and took them with him to Babylon.\x + \xo 17:12-15: \xt 2Ki 24:15-20; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 13 Then he took \add a member\add* of the royalВҰ340193 familyВҰ340192, made an agreement withВҰ340199 himвҖ”\add вүҲforcing him to make various commitments\add*. Then he took away the \add вүҲcountry's\add* \add former\add* powerful people,
\v 14 so the kingdomВҰ340207 would remain \add вүҲsubjected and not be able to become powerful again\add*. \add However,\add* by keeping the agreement, the \add вүҲcountry\add* would \add at least\add* survive.
\v 15 ButВҰ340217 the king of Yerushalem rebelledВҰ340217 against him by sendingВҰ340220 his ambassadorsВҰ340221 to EgyptВҰ340222 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* to acquire horsesВҰ340226 andВҰ340217 an army. Will he succeedВҰ340230? Will the one doing theseВҰ340233 things escape? If he breaksВҰ340234 the agreement, will he \add вүҲsurvive\add*?
\v 16 This is the masterВҰ340242 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, he'll definitely die in the land of the king who made him king, the king whose promises he despisedВҰ340252, and whose agreement he brokeВҰ340257. He'll die in the middle of BabylonВҰ340264.
\v 17 \add Egypt's\add* Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ340274)\add* withВҰ340268 his mighty army and hugeВҰ340269 hordeВҰ340270 won'tВҰ340267 help himВҰ340273 inВҰ340268 battleВҰ340275, when ramps are constructed and siegeВҰ340279 walls are builtВҰ340278 up to cut off many livesВҰ340281,
\v 18 because the king despisedВҰ340284 his promise by breakingВҰ340286 the agreement. Wow, he reached out to make a promise, andВҰ340284 yet \add afterwards\add* he did all those things. He won'tВҰ340295 escapeВҰ340296.
\v 19 Therefore the masterВҰ340303 YahwehВҰ340303 saysВҰ340302 this: вҖҳAs I live, wasn't it my promise that he despisedВҰ340313 and my agreement that he brokeВҰ340316? \add вүҲTherefore\add* I'llВҰ340317 \add вүҲcause him to be punished for what he did\add*.
\v 20 I'll spreadВҰ340320 my netВҰ340322 out over him, and he'll be caughtВҰ340323 inВҰ340324 my trap, and I'll take him to BabylonВҰ340326 and handle his judgementВҰ340327 thereВҰ340329 for the treason he committed when he betrayed me.
\v 21 All of his refugees in his armies will be killed by the swordВҰ340344, andВҰ340336 the ones who remain will be scatteredВҰ340350 in every direction. ThenВҰ340336 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ340351 that I am YahwehВҰ340354, because I'veВҰ340355 declared that that will happen.вҖқ
\s1 The tree-tip part of the parable explained
\rem /s1 God's Promise of Hope; Israel Exalted at Last
\p
\v 22 The masterВҰ340360 YahwehВҰ340360 saysВҰ340359 this, вҖҳSo I myself will takeВҰ340362 away the highest part of the cedarВҰ340365 tree, and I'll plant it away from itsВҰ340369 tenderВҰ340370 branches. I'll break it off, and I myself will plant it on a very highВҰ340377 mountainВҰ340375.
\v 23 I'llВҰ340383 plantВҰ340383 it onВҰ340398 Yisrael's highest mountainВҰ340380 so it'll grow branches and produceВҰ340384 fruitВҰ340387, and it'll become a majesticВҰ340390 cedarВҰ340389 so that every winged bird will live underВҰ340392 it. They'll nest inВҰ340398 the shadeВҰ340398 of its branches,
\v 24 thenВҰ340402 all the trees in the countrysideВҰ340406 will know that I am Yahweh. I bringВҰ340410 down the high trees and I raiseВҰ340414 up the low trees. I wither the watered tree and I cause the wilted tree to bloom. I am Yahweh. I'veВҰ340425 declared that that will happen, and I will do it.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 Individual responsibility
\rem /s1 The Justice of a Righteous God; Individual Responsibility; The Soul Who Sins Will Die; Individual Retribution
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ340432 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ340430:
\v 2 вҖңWhat do you mean, you \add people\add* who use this proverb about YisraelВҰ340448? You sayВҰ340449, вҖҳFathers eatВҰ340451 sour grapesВҰ340452, \add вүҲbutВҰ340453 it's\add* the children'sВҰ340454 teethВҰ340453 that are \add вүҲset on edge\add*вҖҷ.
\p
\v 3 This is the masterВҰ340461 Yahweh's declaration: as I live, there'll \add вүҲcertainly no longer be any occasion for youВҰ340466 to use\add* this proverb inВҰ340471 YisraelВҰ340471.
\v 4 Listen, every life belongs to me: the fatherВҰ340480's life as well as the son'sвҖ”they belong to me. The \add вүҲone who disobeys\add* is the one who'll die.
\s2 The godly man
\p
\v 5 If there's a \add вүҲgodlyВҰ340496\add* \add >man\add* who does what's fair and rightВҰ340496,
\v 6 who doesn't eat at the \add вүҲhilltop\add* \add shrines\add*, who doesn't \add вүҲrequest help\add* from Yisrael'sВҰ340513 idolsВҰ340511, who doesn't \add вүҲmess with\add* someone else's wifeВҰ340516 or a menstruatingВҰ340523 womanВҰ340522,
\v 7 who doesn't oppressВҰ340529 anyoneВҰ340527, who gives back to debtors what they put up as security for loans, who doesn't \add вүҲsteal\add* \add butВҰ340527 rather\add* gives his food to the hungryВҰ340537 andВҰ340539 \add вүҲgives clothesВҰ340542 to those without them\add*,
\v 8 who doesn't charge too much interestВҰ340544 if he lends \add >money\add*, and doesn't take too much profit for what he sells, who promotes true justiceВҰ340554 \add вүҲwithin the community\add*,
\v 9 who \add вүҲfollows\add* my instructions and \add вүҲfaithfullyВҰ340566 obeys\add* my regulationsВҰ340561, that man will be \add вүҲacquitted\add* \add and\add* will definitely live. That's the masterВҰ340572 Yahweh's declaration.\x + \xo 18:9: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*
\s3 The wayward son of the godly man
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ340575\add* suppose \add @that godly man\add* has a violentВҰ340578 son who kills andВҰ340581 sadly \add вүҲgoes against all those things above\add*,
\v 11 not \add вүҲfollowing\add* the example of his \add вүҲgodly\add* father, butВҰ340586 \add rather\add* who's eatenВҰ340599 at the \add вүҲhilltop\add* \add shrines\add* andВҰ340600 \add вүҲslept with someone else's\add* wifeВҰ340602,
\v 12 who oppressesВҰ340608 the poor and needyВҰ340607, who steals and robs, who doesn't returnВҰ340613 \add something given as\add* a pledgeВҰ340611, who \add вүҲrequests help from\add* idolsВҰ340616 and does \add вүҲdisgusting things\add*,
\v 13 who lends out money at too high interestВҰ340622, and who makes too much profit on what he sells. Should that man live? He certainlyВҰ340635 won'tВҰ340627! He'll definitely dieВҰ340635, and his bloodВҰ340637 will be on \add вүҲhis own head\add*.
\s3 The peace/prosperity of child righteous/honest/sensible
\p
\v 14 ButВҰ340641 listen, suppose he has a son, and his son sees all the sinsВҰ340649 thatВҰ340651 his fatherВҰ340650's committed, and though he sees them, he doesn't do those things.
\v 15 He hasn't eatenВҰ340662 at the \add вүҲhilltop\add* \add shrines\add*, and hasn't \add вүҲrequested help from the IsraeliВҰ340670 people's idolsВҰ340668\add*, and hasn't \add вүҲslept with someone else's\add* wifeВҰ340673,
\v 16 he doesn't oppressВҰ340680 anyoneВҰ340678, or \add вүҲkeep things givenВҰ340689 as\add* a pledge, or \add вүҲaccept\add* stolen things, butВҰ340678 instead gives his food to the hungryВҰ340688 andВҰ340678 \add вүҲgives clothesВҰ340693 to those without them\add*,
\v 17 he's turnedВҰ340696 his back onВҰ340704 \add вүҲcrime\add*, and doesn't charge high interestВҰ340698, he \add вүҲfollows\add* my instructions and \add вүҲobeys\add* my regulationsВҰ340704вҖ”he won'tВҰ340700 dieВҰ340708 for his father'sВҰ340710 \add вүҲevil actions\add*, butВҰ340699 he'll certainlyВҰ340711 live.
\v 18 His fatherВҰ340714, since he oppressed others by extortionВҰ340717 and robbedВҰ340719 \add вүҲpeople\add*, and did \add вүҲevil things\add* among his peopleвҖ”listen, he'll dieВҰ340731 inВҰ340732 his sin.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ340734 you people ask\add*, вҖҳWhy doesn't the son \add also\add* have to \add pay the cost for his family's crimes\add*?вҖҷ \add Well\add* it's because the son \add вүҲpromotes\add* justiceВҰ340743 and godliness and \add вүҲfollows\add* all my instructions. He'll definitely live.
\v 20 The one who sins is the one who'll die. The children won't \add have to\add* \add вүҲbe responsible for\add* their parents' sin, and the parents won't \add вүҲbe responsible for\add* their children's sinsвҖ”the righteousness of those who act rightly will be on themselves, and the wickedness of the wicked will be on themselves.\x + \xo 18:20: \xt Deu 24:16.\x*
\s2 The person repent of sins he/his
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ340783\add* if the wickedВҰ340783 \add >person\add* turns away from all \add вүҲtheir disobedience\add*, and \add вүҲfollows\add* all my instructions and \add вүҲdoes what's rightВҰ340800 and fair\add*, then \add @that person\add* will certainlyВҰ340801 live and not dieВҰ340804.
\v 22 All \add вүҲtheir acts of disobedience\add* won'tВҰ340811 be called to mind against them. They'll liveВҰ340818 by the \add вүҲrightВҰ340814 things theyВҰ340812 do\add*.
\v 23 That's the masterВҰ340825 Yahweh's declaration.
\p Do I \add вүҲcelebrate happily\add* about the deathВҰ340822 of wickedВҰ340823 \add people\add*, andВҰ340830 not about them turningВҰ340828 away from their \add evil\add* behaviourВҰ340829 so that they can liveВҰ340830?
\v 24 \add вүҲButВҰ340833\add* if a righteous person turnsВҰ340833 away from their righteousness, and \add вүҲdisobeys\add* and \add вүҲdoes disgusting things like\add* the wickedВҰ340843 people do, then will they liveВҰ340845? All the \add вүҲgood things\add* that had been done won'tВҰ340853 be called to mind when they betray me in their treason, so they'll dieВҰ340864 in the sins that they committedВҰ340836.
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ340866 you people complain\add* that the master'sВҰ340870 way isn'tВҰ340867 correct. PleaseВҰ340875 listenВҰ340871, \add you\add* \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ340874 people\add*: is it my ways that aren'tВҰ340867 correct, or is it \em your\em* ways?
\v 26 When the righteous person turnsВҰ340884 away from their righteousness, and commits injustice and dies because of it, then \add *that person\add* will die inВҰ340892 the injustice that they've done.
\v 27 \add вүҲButВҰ340899\add* when a wicked person turnsВҰ340899 away from the wicked things they've done and \add вүҲdoes what's fair and what's rightВҰ340906\add*, then \add *that person\add* will preserveВҰ340911 their lifeВҰ340910вҖ”
\v 28 they've \add вүҲbecome aware of all their disobedient behaviours\add* andВҰ340913 turnedВҰ340914 away from them. \add @That person\add* certainlyВҰ340921 won'tВҰ340923 dieВҰ340924, \add вүҲbutВҰ340913\add* will live.
\v 29 \add вүҲButВҰ340926 the IsraeliВҰ340928 people insist\add*, вҖҳThe master'sВҰ340932 way isn'tВҰ340929 fair!вҖҷ How is my way not fair, \add вүҲyou IsraeliВҰ340928 people\add*? It's \em your\em* ways that aren'tВҰ340929 fair.
\v 30 Therefore I'llВҰ340947 judgeВҰ340947 each person among you accordingВҰ340946 to their waysВҰ340946, \add вүҲyou IsraeliВҰ340949 people\add*. That's the masterВҰ340952 Yahweh's declaration.
\p \add вүҲChange your direction\add* and turn away from all your \add вүҲdisobedient behaviours\add* so that they won'tВҰ340959 be stumblingВҰ340963 blocksВҰ340963 of evilВҰ340964 for you.
\v 31 ThrowВҰ340966 off all the \add вүҲdisobedient things you people have done\add*. \add вүҲWork towards\add* a new heartВҰ340978 and a new spiritВҰ340980 for yourselves. Why should you dieВҰ340983, \add вүҲyou IsraeliВҰ340985 people\add*?
\v 32 I takeВҰ340989 no pleasureВҰ340989 inВҰ340990 the deathВҰ340990 of someone who diesВҰ340991. That's the masterВҰ340993 Yahweh's declaration, \add so\add* \add вүҲturnВҰ340995 away from your evil behaviour\add* and liveВҰ340996.
\c 19
\s1 A song of mourning for Yisrael's final kings
\rem /s1 A Lament for Israel's Princes; A Song of Sorrow; Israel Degraded; A Funeral Song for Israel's Kings
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow sing a mournful song for Yisrael's leaders,\add*
\v 2 saying:
\q1 вҖҳWho was your motherВҰ341009? A lionessВҰ341010вҖ”she lived with a lion's son.
\q1 There among the youngВҰ341015 lions, she rearedВҰ341016 herВҰ341017 cubs.
\q1
\v 3 She's the one who raised one of herВҰ341021 cubs to become a youngВҰ341022 lionвҖ”
\q1 a lion who learnedВҰ341024 to tear apart his victims,
\q1 andВҰ341019 thenВҰ341019 he devouredВҰ341029 people.
\q1
\v 4 ThenВҰ341031 the nationsВҰ341033 heardВҰ341031 about him.
\q1 He got caughtВҰ341035 inВҰ341034 theirВҰ341034 trap,
\q1 andВҰ341031 they took him to EgyptВҰ341041 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* withВҰ341034 hooksВҰ341037.
\q1
\v 5 \add @The mother lion\add* waitedВҰ341045 for his return,
\q1 \add вүҲbutВҰ341043 eventually she realisedВҰ341043 that he wasn't coming back\add*,
\q1 so she took another one of herВҰ341047 cubs andВҰ341043 made him into a youngВҰ341051 lion.
\q1
\v 6 This young lion roamed around amongst the \add other\add* lionsВҰ341057.
\q1 He was a young lion andВҰ341054 learnedВҰ341060 to tear his victimsвҖ”
\q1 he devouredВҰ341065 people.
\q1
\v 7 He \add ?вүҲseized\add* their fortresses and ruined their citiesВҰ341069.
\q1 The land and itsВҰ341073 \add вүҲproduce\add* were abandoned
\q1 because of the soundВҰ341074 of his roaringВҰ341075.
\q1
\v 8 ButВҰ341077 the nationsВҰ341079 came against him from the surrounding provincesВҰ341081.
\q1 They spreadВҰ341082 their nets over himвҖ”
\q1 he was caughtВҰ341086 inВҰ341085 their pit.
\q1
\v 9 With hooksВҰ341090 \add in him\add*, they put him in a cage,
\q1 andВҰ341088 thenВҰ341088 they took him to the Babylonian kingВҰ341094.
\q1 They took him to the fortresses
\q1 so that his voiceВҰ341102 would no longer be heardВҰ341101 in Yisrael's hills.
\b
\q1
\v 10 Your motherВҰ341110 was like a vineВҰ341111 plantedВҰ341116 inВҰ341112 your vineyardВҰ341112 beside the water.
\q1 It was fruitfulВҰ341117 and full of branchesВҰ341118 becauseВҰ341120 \add вүҲthere was plenty\add* of water.
\q1
\v 11 It had strong branches that were used for \add making\add* rulersВҰ341131' sceptersВҰ341130,
\q1 and it toweredВҰ341132 aboveВҰ341134 the branches,
\q1 and its heightВҰ341139 could be seen due to the mass of its foliage.
\q1
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ341143\add* the vine was uprootedВҰ341143 in fury and thrownВҰ341146 down onto the groundВҰ341145,
\q1 and an easternВҰ341148 wind driedВҰ341149 out its fruitВҰ341150.
\q1 Its strongВҰ341154 branchesВҰ341153 were broken off and witheredВҰ341152,
\q1 and thenВҰ341143 burnt in a fireВҰ341155.
\q1
\v 13 SoВҰ341158 now it's plantedВҰ341159 in the wildernessВҰ341160вҖ”
\q1 in a land of drought andВҰ341158 thirstВҰ341163.
\q1
\v 14 Fire wentВҰ341165 out from its large branches and consumedВҰ341170 its fruitВҰ341169.
\q1 There's no strong branches \add left\add* onВҰ341174 itвҖ”no scepterВҰ341178 for rulingВҰ341179 withВҰ341174.вҖҷ
\m That's a song for mourning, and should be sung as \add *such\add*.вҖқ
\c 20
\s1 Israeli rebellion
\rem /s1 The Rebellion of Israel; Rebellious Israel; The Lord's Will and Human Defiance; Israel's Continuing Rebellion
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSeven years\add* \add after we'd been taken to Babylon\add*, \add вүҲsome\add* IsraeliВҰ341195 eldersВҰ341195 cameВҰ341193 to \add вүҲget me to ask YahwehВҰ341200 for advice for them\add*.
\v 2 Then YahwehВҰ341208 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add this\add* messageВҰ341206:
\v 3 вҖңHumanity's child, tell the IsraeliВҰ341218 eldersВҰ341218 that the master Yahweh says this: вҖҳHave you \add people\add* come to \add вүҲget advice from me\add*? As I live, I won't \add вүҲallow you to ask for myВҰ341232 advice\add*. That's the master Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ
\p
\v 4 Will you judge them? Will you judge, humanity'sВҰ341246 child? Let them know about theirВҰ341250 ancestors' \add вүҲdisgusting behaviour\add*.
\v 5 Tell them that the masterВҰ341258 Yahweh says this: вҖҳOn the dayВҰ341260 that I choseВҰ341261 YisraelВҰ341262 andВҰ341253 made myselfВҰ341268 knownВҰ341268 to them inВҰ341262 EgyptВҰ341271, I raised myВҰ341273 hand to \add вүҲmake a promise\add* to Yakov's descendantsВҰ341265. I told \add >them\add*, вҖңI am Yahweh your godВҰ341278вҖқ\x + \xo 20:5-6: \xt Exo 6:2-8.\x*вҖ”
\v 6 on that dayВҰ341280 I raised my handВҰ341283 to \add вүҲmake a promise\add* to them that I would bringВҰ341285 them out of EgyptВҰ341287 into a land that I'd carefully selectedВҰ341293 for them. It was flowingВҰ341295 with milk and honeyВҰ341297вҖ”itВҰ341299 was the most beautifulВҰ341298 of all the landsВҰ341302.
\v 7 I told them, вҖңLet each \add вүҲfamily\add* throwВҰ341309 away their EgyptianВҰ341311 idolsВҰ341310, plusВҰ341310 \add вүҲany other detestableВҰ341307 thingsВҰ341307 they have\add*. Don't \add вүҲdefile\add* yourselvesВҰ341314. I am YahwehВҰ341316 yourВҰ341317 godВҰ341317.вҖқ
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ341319\add* they rebelledВҰ341319 againstВҰ341321 me andВҰ341319 were unwilling to listenВҰ341324 to me. \add *They\add* didn'tВҰ341322 throw away the detestableВҰ341329 thingsВҰ341329 \add вүҲthey had\add* or abandonВҰ341338 theirВҰ341330 Egyptian idolsВҰ341335, so I determined to pour my fury out onВҰ341321 them to satisfy my rageВҰ341341 among them \add вүҲright there\add* inВҰ341321 EgyptВҰ341336.
\v 9 I \add вүҲdid thatВҰ341357 to protect my reputation\add* so it wouldn't be \add вүҲtarnished\add* inВҰ341360 the eyesВҰ341355 of the nationsВҰ341356 \add вүҲwhere theyВҰ341359 were staying\add*. I made myselfВҰ341362 \add вүҲclearly\add* knownВҰ341362 to them\f + \fr 20:9 \ft them: Probably referring to those countries, but some translations interpret it to refer to the ones being brought out.\f* by bringingВҰ341365 them out of EgyptВҰ341367.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ341369\add* IВҰ341372 led them out of EgyptВҰ341371 andВҰ341369 took them into the wildernessВҰ341375.
\v 11 ThenВҰ341377 IВҰ341385 gaveВҰ341377 them my instructions andВҰ341377 regulationsВҰ341381вҖ”\add вүҲanyone who follows\add* them will liveВҰ341391.\x + \xo 20:11-13: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*
\v 12 I also \add вүҲestablished rest days\add* as a signВҰ341401 between myself andВҰ341403 themвҖ”for them to knowВҰ341404 that I am YahwehВҰ341407 who \add вүҲdeclares them different from others\add*.\x + \xo 20:12: \xt Exo 31:13-17.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ341410 the IsraeliВҰ341413 people\add* rebelledВҰ341410 againstВҰ341412 me in the wilderness. They \add вүҲwouldn't follow my instructions\add*, andВҰ341410 they rejectedВҰ341424 my regulationsВҰ341417, \add even though\add* whoever obeys them will live. They severelyВҰ341438 disrespected my rest days, so I said I'd pour my fury out onВҰ341412 them in the wilderness in order to end them.
\v 14 \add вүҲButВҰ341443 I did thatВҰ341450 to protect my reputation\add* so it wouldn't be \add вүҲtarnished\add* in the eyesВҰ341448 of the nationsВҰ341449, in whose sightВҰ341452 I had broughtВҰ341451 them out \add of Egypt\add*.
\v 15 SoВҰ341454 I myself \add вүҲtook action by making a promise\add* to them inВҰ341460 the wildernessВҰ341460 not to bringВҰ341462 them into the land thatВҰ341467 I'd been going to give themвҖ”a land flowingВҰ341470 withВҰ341460 milk andВҰ341454 honeyВҰ341472, whichВҰ341467 was the most beautifulВҰ341473 out of all the landsВҰ341477.\x + \xo 20:15: \xt Num 14:26-35.\x*
\v 16 I promised that because they'd rejectedВҰ341481 my instructions and not \add вүҲfollowed my regulationsВҰ341484\add*, and they disrespected my rest days, because \add вүҲwhat they really wanted was\add* their idolsВҰ341495.
\v 17 \add вүҲButВҰ341499\add* I pitied them, so I didn'tВҰ341502 \add вүҲwipe them out\add* inВҰ341508 the wildernessВҰ341508.
\p
\v 18 I told their childrenВҰ341513 inВҰ341514 the wildernessВҰ341514, вҖңDon't \add вүҲfollow yourВҰ341516 parents' habits or behaviour\add*, andВҰ341510 don'tВҰ341517 defile yourselvesВҰ341529 withВҰ341514 their idolsВҰ341526.
\v 19 I am YahwehВҰ341532 yourВҰ341533 godВҰ341533вҖ”\add вүҲfollow my instructions, obey my regulationsВҰ341534\add*,
\v 20 and keepВҰ341546 my rest days \add different from other days\add* so that they'll be a signВҰ341548 between me and you. \add That way\add* you'll all knowВҰ341551 that I am YahwehВҰ341554 yourВҰ341555 godВҰ341555.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever\add*, their sons andВҰ341557 daughters rebelledВҰ341557 against me. They didn'tВҰ341562 \add вүҲkeep my instructions or follow my regulationsВҰ341561\add*, \add even though\add* whoever obeys them will liveВҰ341577. They disrespected my rest days, so I determined to pour my fury out onВҰ341559 them to satisfy my rageВҰ341585 against them inВҰ341559 the wildernessВҰ341590.
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ341592 I didn'tВҰ341599 proceed, for the sake of my reputation\add*, so it wouldn't be mocked by the nationsВҰ341602 \add вүҲwho saw me\add* bring the Israelis out \add of Egypt\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲSo I took action\add* inВҰ341617 the wildernessВҰ341617, \add promising that instead\add* I would scatterВҰ341618 them among the nationsВҰ341620 and disperseВҰ341621 them into other countriesВҰ341623.\x + \xo 20:23: \xt Lev 26:33.\x*
\v 24 I decided to do that since they hadn't obeyed my instructions, and since they'd rejectedВҰ341631 my regulationsВҰ341630 and disrespected my rest daysвҖ”\add вүҲthey really wanted\add* their ancestors' idolsВҰ341637.
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ341642 I even gaveВҰ341645 them instructions that weren't goodВҰ341649, andВҰ341650 regulationsВҰ341647 that theyВҰ341652 couldn't liveВҰ341652 by.
\v 26 I declared them to be defiledВҰ341655 \add вүҲbecause of the giftsВҰ341657 they gave\add* (they sacrificed everyВҰ341659 \add вүҲwoman's\add* firstbornВҰ341661 child inВҰ341657 the fire) so that I could fill them withВҰ341657 horror so they would knowВҰ341667 that I am YahwehВҰ341670.вҖҷ
\rem /s1 Judgment and Restoration
\p
\v 27 Therefore, humanity'sВҰ341681 child, speakВҰ341674 to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ341677 people\add* andВҰ341682 tell them that the masterВҰ341686 YahwehВҰ341686 saysВҰ341685 this: вҖҳThat was also how yourВҰ341692 ancestorsВҰ341692 blasphemedВҰ341690 me when theyВҰ341690 were unfaithfulВҰ341695 to me.
\v 28 WhenВҰ341697 I broughtВҰ341697 them into the land thatВҰ341701 I'd promised to giveВҰ341706 them, thenВҰ341697 whenever they sawВҰ341709 any highВҰ341713 hill and leafyВҰ341717 treeВҰ341716, they offered their sacrificesВҰ341723. They provokedВҰ341727 me with their offerings, and also burnt their fragrant incense there and pouredВҰ341733 out their drinkВҰ341737 offerings.
\v 29 ThenВҰ341739 I \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңWhat's this high place whereВҰ341743 you present your offerings?вҖқ so the place is calledВҰ341748 BamahВҰ341750 \add (meaning вҖҳHigh placeвҖҷ)\add* to this dayВҰ341752.вҖҷ
\rem /s1 Judgment and Restoration
\p
\v 30 Therefore tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ341760 people\add* that the masterВҰ341764 YahwehВҰ341764 \add вүҲasks\add* this: вҖҳWhy do you \add вүҲdefile yourselvesВҰ341769\add* withВҰ341766 your ancestorsВҰ341767' customs? Why do you act like prostitutesВҰ341773, searching for disgusting thingsВҰ341771?
\v 31 To this dayВҰ341787, when you offer up your giftsВҰ341776 (\add offering\add* your sons \add вүҲas burnt sacrifices\add*), you defile yourselvesВҰ341781 withВҰ341775 all your idolsВҰ341784. SoВҰ341775 why shouldВҰ341789 I let you \add вүҲtry to find me, you IsraeliВҰ341791 people\add*? As I live, I won't allow you \add people\add* to \add вүҲrequest myВҰ341795 help or advice\add*. That's the masterВҰ341797 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 32 The thought thatВҰ341811's forming in yourВҰ341807 mind will never happen. You \add people\add* say, вҖңLet's be like the other nationsВҰ341816вҖ”like the clansВҰ341817 in other \add вүҲcountriesВҰ341818\add* who worship wood andВҰ341821 stoneВҰ341821.вҖқ
\s1 Punishment and forgiveness
\rem /s1 God Will Restore Israel; God Punishes and Forgives
\p
\v 33 This is the masterВҰ341827 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, I'llВҰ341838 certainly reignВҰ341838 over you \add people\add* with \add вүҲstrict control\add*, and with fury that'll be pouredВҰ341837 out onВҰ341832 you.
\v 34 I'll bringВҰ341841 you out from the other \add вүҲpeopleВҰ341845 groups\add* andВҰ341841 will gatherВҰ341846 you out of the countriesВҰ341850 where you've been scatteredВҰ341852. I'll do this withВҰ341853 \add вүҲpower, pouringВҰ341859 out fury\add*.
\v 35 ThenВҰ341861 I'll bringВҰ341861 you into the wildernessВҰ341865 of the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ341866 groups\add*, andВҰ341861 thereВҰ341869 I'll judgeВҰ341867 you face to faceвҖ”
\v 36 just like I judged yourВҰ341879 ancestorsВҰ341879 inВҰ341880 the Egyptian wildernessВҰ341880, that's how I'llВҰ341884 judge youВҰ341885 \add people\add*. That's the masterВҰ341887 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 37 I'll cause you \add people\add* to passВҰ341890 underВҰ341892 my staff \add to be counted\add*, andВҰ341894 I'll make you obey the requirements of \add &our\add* agreement.
\v 38 I'll purgeВҰ341899 the rebelsВҰ341901 from among you, as well as those who revolt againstВҰ341903 me. I'll send them out from the land whereВҰ341905 they're staying \add as foreigners\add*, butВҰ341899 they won'tВҰ341912 enter YisraelВҰ341911. ThenВҰ341899 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ341914 that I am YahwehВҰ341918.
\p
\v 39 SoВҰ341920 to you \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ341921 people\add*, the masterВҰ341928 YahwehВҰ341928 says this: вҖҳEach of you should go to his own idols. Worship them if you refuse to listenВҰ341938 to me, butВҰ341920 you must no longer desecrate my sacredВҰ341943 name withВҰ341948 your giftsВҰ341948 andВҰ341920 your idols,
\v 40 because this is the masterВҰ341960 Yahweh's declaration: all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ341957 people\add* will worship me there onВҰ341952 my sacredВҰ341983 mountain inВҰ341952 YisraelВҰ341958. I'llВҰ341973 be happy to acceptВҰ341971 your offeringsВҰ341980 there, along withВҰ341952 your choiceВҰ341979 giftsВҰ341980 \add вүҲdedicated to me\add*.
\v 41 I'll acceptВҰ341987 you like a soothingВҰ341986 aromaВҰ341985 when I bringВҰ341989 you out from the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ341993 groups\add* and gatherВҰ341994 you out of the countriesВҰ341998 where you've been scatteredВҰ342000. I'll \add вүҲdisplay my holiness\add* among you for the nationsВҰ342005 to see.
\v 42 You'll knowВҰ342007 that I am YahwehВҰ342011 when I bringВҰ342012 youВҰ342013 \add back\add* to YisraelВҰ342017вҖ”to the land that I promised to giveВҰ342026 to yourВҰ342028 ancestorsВҰ342028.
\v 43 There you'll \add вүҲcall to mind\add* your conduct and \add вүҲeverything you defiled yourselves by doing\add*, and you'll despise yourselves for all the evilВҰ342047 things you'veВҰ342041 done.
\v 44 ThenВҰ342051 you'll knowВҰ342051 that I am Yahweh, when I do this to you for the sake of my \add вүҲreputation\add*, not because of your evilВҰ342062 practicesВҰ342063, andВҰ342063 not because of your corruptВҰ342064 actions, \add вүҲyou IsraeliВҰ342065 people\add*. That's the masterВҰ342068 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
