\rem /s1 God's Judgment on the Younger Sister; The Lord's Judgment of Oholibah
\p
\v 22 Therefore, OholibahВҰ343531, the masterВҰ343535 YahwehВҰ343535 saysВҰ343534 this, вҖҳListen, I'll turn yourВҰ343547 loversВҰ343541 against you. I'll bringВҰ343549 thoseВҰ343544 that you rejected against you from everyВҰ343551 side:
\v 23 the Babylonians and all the Chaldeans, PekodВҰ343558, ShoaВҰ343559, and KoaВҰ343560, and all the Assyrians with themвҖ”strong, handsome men, governorsВҰ343568 and commandersВҰ343569, all of them officersВҰ343571 and \add вүҲfamous\add* men, all of them riding on horsesВҰ343574.
\v 24 They'll bring many peopleВҰ343583 against you with weaponsВҰ343579, as well as chariotsВҰ343580 and wagonsВҰ343581. They'll \add вүҲsurround you with\add* \add units with\add* large shields, small shields, and helmetsВҰ343586. I'llВҰ343590 get them to punish you, and they'll punish you with theirВҰ343594 actions.
\v 25 I'llВҰ343596 directВҰ343596 my jealousВҰ343597 anger atВҰ343601 you, and they'll deal withВҰ343601 you inВҰ343601 fury. They'll cut off your noses and your earsВҰ343603, and even the survivors will be killed by the swordВҰ343606. They'll takeВҰ343611 away your sonsВҰ343609 and your daughtersВҰ343610, and \add вүҲthe remainder will be burnt\add*.
\v 26 They'll stripВҰ343616 off your clothesВҰ343619 andВҰ343616 takeВҰ343620 away all your \add вүҲjewellery\add*.
\v 27 I'llВҰ343624 remove your shameful behaviour from you, includingВҰ343627 your acts of prostitutionВҰ343629 with Egypt. You'll \add вүҲgive up your longing looks towards them\add*, andВҰ343624 you won'tВҰ343632 think about Egypt any more,вҖҷ
\v 28 because the masterВҰ343647 YahwehВҰ343647 says this, Listen, I'll \add вүҲhand you over to\add* the ones you hateвҖ”back into the \add вүҲcontrol\add* of the ones you'd turned away from.
\v 29 They'll \add вүҲshow their hate for you as\add* they takeВҰ343664 all your possessions and abandon you naked and bareвҖ”\add вүҲyes,\add* your nakedness will be uncoveredВҰ343671 just like when you engaged inВҰ343663 promiscuity and prostitution.
\v 30 These things will be done to you becauseВҰ343680 you actedВҰ343680 like a prostituteВҰ343680вҖ”lusting afterВҰ343681 nationsВҰ343682 whose idolsВҰ343687 defiled you.
\p
\v 31 You \add вүҲfollowed a similar pathВҰ343689 to that\add* of yourВҰ343690 \add older\add* sisterВҰ343690, so I'llВҰ343692 \add вүҲgiveВҰ343692 youВҰ343691 the same punishment that I gave herВҰ343693\add*.вҖҷ
\v 32 The masterВҰ343699 YahwehВҰ343699 saysВҰ343698 this, вҖҳYou'll \add вүҲsuffer the same extreme suffering that your sisterВҰ343702 suffered\add*. You'll becomeВҰ343706 a laughingstockВҰ343707 and a subject for derisionВҰ343708вҖ”\add вүҲthere's a lot of pain coming your way\add*.
\v 33 You'll be filledВҰ343714 with drunkenness and sorrowВҰ343713, horrorВҰ343716 and devastationвҖ”\add вүҲthe same suffering that yourВҰ343719 sisterВҰ343719 ShomronВҰ343720 was made to drink\add*.
\v 34 You'll drinkВҰ343722 \add @that cup of suffering\add* and drainВҰ343724 it empty, thenВҰ343722 you'll shatter it and tear your breastsВҰ343729 with the piecesВҰ343727. That's the masterВҰ343735 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ
\p
\v 35 So the masterВҰ343742 YahwehВҰ343742 saysВҰ343741 this, вҖҳBecause you'veВҰ343745 forgottenВҰ343745 me and thrownВҰ343747 me away behindВҰ343749 your back, you'll bear the consequences of your shameful behaviour and your prostitutionВҰ343758.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s2 Revealing the disgusting deeds of the sisters
\rem /s1 God's Judgment on Both Sisters; The Lord's Judgment on Both Sisters
\p
\v 36 YahwehВҰ343762 saidВҰ343761 to me, вҖңHumanity's child, will youВҰ343767 judgeВҰ343767 OholahВҰ343770 and OholibahВҰ343773? Present them \add a list of\add* theirВҰ343777 disgusting actions,
\v 37 since they've committed adultery, and also have bloodВҰ343781 onВҰ343782 their handsВҰ343782. They've committed adultery \add вүҲby worshipping\add* their idols, and they've even caused their sons to pass throughВҰ343795 the fire \add to be considered\add* as food for their idols.
\v 38 Then \add вүҲon top of that\add*, they defile my sanctuaryВҰ343806, and \add вүҲat the same time\add*, they disrespect my rest days.
\v 39 WhenВҰ343814 they'd slaughteredВҰ343814 their childrenВҰ343817 for their idolsВҰ343818, thenВҰ343814 they cameВҰ343819 to my sanctuaryВҰ343822 onВҰ343814 the same dayВҰ343823 to desecrate itВҰ343825. SoВҰ343814 listen, that's what they've done \add вүҲright there inВҰ343814 my residence\add*.
\p
\v 40 You sent messengersВҰ343840 \add to go and bring\add* menВҰ343836 from far away. Now look, they indeed cameВҰ343845вҖ”thoseВҰ343846 who you \add prepared for by\add* bathing, paintingВҰ343848 your eyesВҰ343849, and adorningВҰ343850 yourselfВҰ343850 with jewellery.
\v 41 You satВҰ343853 on a lovely couchВҰ343856 bed with a tableВҰ343858 arrangedВҰ343859 \add вүҲin front of you\add* where you placed my incenseВҰ343861 andВҰ343853 my \add olive\add* oilВҰ343862.
\v 42 ThenВҰ343866 the soundВҰ343866 of a noisy crowdВҰ343867 was around herВҰ343869 as all kinds of menВҰ343872, even SabeansВҰ343876, were broughtВҰ343875 inВҰ343869 from the wildernessВҰ343878, and theyВҰ343879 put braceletsВҰ343880 on their handsВҰ343883 and beautifulВҰ343885 crownsВҰ343884 on their headsВҰ343888.
\v 43 ThenВҰ343890 I saidВҰ343890 about \add вүҲthat experienced adultererВҰ343892\add*, вҖҳNow they'll \add вүҲtreat herВҰ343897 as a prostituteВҰ343895\add*, andВҰ343898 she'll fornicateВҰ343897 with them.вҖҷ
\v 44 They \add вүҲhad sex with\add* her like men do with a prostituteВҰ343906. In that way theyВҰ343908 \add вүҲhad sex with\add* the two immoral womenВҰ343915, OholahВҰ343911 andВҰ343912 OholibahВҰ343914.
\v 45 \add вүҲButВҰ343918\add* righteousВҰ343919 men will \add вүҲjudgeВҰ343921\add* and punish them as adulteresses, and they'll punish them withВҰ343932 the \add appropriate\add* sentence for those who've shed blood, because they're adulteresses plusВҰ343925 they have blood onВҰ343932 theirВҰ343932 handsВҰ343932.
\p
\v 46 So the masterВҰ343938 YahwehВҰ343938 saysВҰ343937 this: I'll bringВҰ343940 a groupВҰ343942 \add to attack\add* \add @Shomron and Yerushalem\add* and give them up to be terrorizedВҰ343945 and plunderedВҰ343946.
\v 47 ThenВҰ343948 that groupВҰ343951 will stoneВҰ343948 them with stones and cut them down with their swordsВҰ343954. They'll killВҰ343957 their \add вүҲchildren\add* and burnВҰ343960 down their housesВҰ343958.
\v 48 \add That's how\add* I'llВҰ343962 remove shameful behaviour from the land, andВҰ343962 discipline all the womenВҰ343970 so they'll no longer act like prostitutes.
\v 49 They'll use your shameful behaviour against you. You'll all bear the guilt of the sinsВҰ343978 you did with your idolsВҰ343979, andВҰ343975 in that way you'll knowВҰ343981 that I am the masterВҰ343984 YahwehВҰ343984.вҖқ
\c 24
\s1 The rusty cooking pot
\rem /s1 The Corroded Cooking Pot; The Sign of the Cooking Pot; The Cooking Pot; The siege and capture of Jerusalem; The Boiling Pot
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ343991 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ343989 onВҰ343993 the 15th of January of the ninthВҰ343994 yearВҰ343993 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*.
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, writeВҰ344004 down \add вүҲthe day and month\add* for yourselfВҰ344007, because onВҰ344024 this exact day, the Babylonian king \add вүҲstarted his siege of\add* YerushalemВҰ344023.\x + \xo 24:2: \xt 2Ki 25:1.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ344028 tell this parableВҰ344034 to the rebelliousВҰ344033 Israeli people and explain that it comes from\add* the masterВҰ344039 YahwehВҰ344039:
\q1 Pour waterВҰ344048 into the cooking pot and place it on the fire.
\q1
\v 4 Put in the leg and shoulderВҰ344058 of a goodВҰ344056 \add sheep\add*,
\q1 then fillВҰ344061 it up with the best bonesВҰ344060.
\q1
\v 5 \add Yes,\add* takeВҰ344065 the best one from the flockВҰ344064
\q1 and pile up the \add вүҲfuel\add* underneathВҰ344069 itвҖ”
\q1 keeping it boilingВҰ344071 to \add make sure\add* the bones inВҰ344076 it cook \add well\add*.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲNow\add* the masterВҰ344084 YahwehВҰ344084 saysВҰ344082 this: The cityВҰ344087 of bloodВҰ344088 \add вүҲwon't end well\add*вҖ”\add it's like\add* a cooking pot that has rust inВҰ344092 it, and that rust won't come out of it. Take piece after piece out of it, butВҰ344093 don'tВҰ344094 \add вүҲbe choosy about whichВҰ344090 pieces\add*,
\v 7 because \add вүҲthe bloodВҰ344107 the city shed\add* is \add all the way\add* \add вүҲthrough\add* itsВҰ344108 centre. It \add вүҲdisplayed the blood\add* on a flat rockВҰ344113 \add to be easily seen\add*, rather than pouring it out on the ground where it could be coveredВҰ344120 over withВҰ344108 dust,
\v 8 \add вүҲso it makes me angry enough to\add* get revengeВҰ344127: IВҰ344128 placed \em the city's\em* bloodВҰ344131 on the smooth rockВҰ344135, so it couldn't be coveredВҰ344137.
\p
\v 9 Therefore, the masterВҰ344143 YahwehВҰ344143 saysВҰ344142 this: The cityВҰ344146 of bloodВҰ344147 \add вүҲwon't end well\add*. I'llВҰ344151 also enlarge the pile of \add fire\add*wood \add to put underneath it\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲStack up\add* the wood and kindleВҰ344156 the fireВҰ344157. \add вүҲCook the meat well\add* and mix in the spicesВҰ344161 and let the bonesВҰ344162 be charredВҰ344163.
\v 11 ThenВҰ344165 put the emptyВҰ344169 pot onto \add the hot\add* coalsВҰ344168 in order to heat andВҰ344165 scorch its bronzeВҰ344173, so the impurities in it will be meltedВҰ344174вҖ”its corrosion \add вүҲeaten away\add*.вҖҷ
\v 12 \add ?вүҲThat was a lot of work, butВҰ344182\add* the fireВҰ344188 didn'tВҰ344182 remove the corrosion from it.
\v 13 Your shameful behaviour is in your uncleanness. Because you wouldn't \add вүҲaccept it when\add* I tried to cleanseВҰ344194 you, you won'tВҰ344195 be purified anymore untilВҰ344202 I've satisfiedВҰ344204 my fury againstВҰ344201 you.
\v 14 I, Yahweh, have declared it, and I will do it. I won'tВҰ344215 relent, nor will I rest from it. \add вүҲYou'll be judgedВҰ344225 by your own practicesВҰ344223 and your own behaviour\add*. That's the masterВҰ344227 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\s1 The death of Yehezkel's wife
\rem /s1 The Death of the Prophet's Wife; The Death of Ezekiel's Wife; Ezekiel's Bereavement; Ezekiel's Wife Dies
\p
\v 15 Then YahwehВҰ344234 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ344232:
\v 16 вҖңListen, humanity'sВҰ344240 child, I'm taking your \add вүҲcherished wife\add* from you withВҰ344248 a plague, butВҰ344249 you mustn't mourn or weep, or let any tearsВҰ344255 \add вүҲshow\add*.
\v 17 You must groan silentlyВҰ344259. Don't \add вүҲorganise\add* a funeral \add вүҲwhen she's\add* deadВҰ344260. Put onВҰ344270 your turbanВҰ344265 and your sandalsВҰ344268, butВҰ344268 don'tВҰ344262 veil your beard, or eatВҰ344279 the breadВҰ344276 of men who mournВҰ344261 who've lost their wives.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ344281\add* I spokeВҰ344281 to the peopleВҰ344284 in the morning, andВҰ344281 thenВҰ344281 my wifeВҰ344287 diedВҰ344286 in the eveningВҰ344288. In the morning I did what I'd been commandedВҰ344292 to do.
\v 19 ThenВҰ344294 the peopleВҰ344296 asked me, вҖңWon't you tell us what theseВҰ344303 things meanвҖ”the \add вүҲway that you'reВҰ344306 behaving\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңYahwehВҰ344313 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ344311,вҖқ I answered them,
\v 21 вҖңto tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ344320 people\add* that the masterВҰ344325 YahwehВҰ344325 saysВҰ344324 this to them: Listen, I'll desecrate my sanctuaryВҰ344331вҖ”the prideВҰ344332 of your powerВҰ344333, the delight of your eyesВҰ344335, and the yearning of your soulВҰ344337вҖ”and \add also\add* your sonsВҰ344338 and daughtersВҰ344339 who youВҰ344341 left behind \add there inВҰ344342 Yerushalem\add* will be killed by the swordВҰ344342.
\v 22 \add вүҲWhenВҰ344345 that happens,\add* you \add peopleВҰ344354\add* will do exactly as I'veВҰ344347 done: you won'tВҰ344351 veil your beards, or eatВҰ344356 the breadВҰ344353 of mourning men,
\v 23 \add вүҲbutВҰ344358 instead\add* your turbansВҰ344358 will be on your headsВҰ344361, and your sandalsВҰ344362 on your feetВҰ344363. You won'tВҰ344364 mourn or weep, because you'll melt away \add вүҲdue to your disobedience\add*, and everyone will groanВҰ344370 for \add вүҲtheir relatives\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ344376\add* Yehezkel will be a signВҰ344379 for you, because when that time comesВҰ344385, you'll do \add вүҲexactly the same as he's doing\add*. ThenВҰ344376 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ344386 that I am the masterВҰ344389 YahwehВҰ344389.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңButВҰ344393 you, humanity'sВҰ344396 child, on the dayВҰ344398 that I capture their temple, (which is their joyВҰ344404, their pride, and what they see and desireВҰ344408), and when I takeВҰ344399 away their sonsВҰ344414 and daughtersВҰ344415,
\v 26 a refugee will comeВҰ344419 to you here on that dayВҰ344417 to give you the newsВҰ344422.
\v 27 At that time, yourВҰ344428 mouthВҰ344428 will be openedВҰ344427 up to that refugee and you'll speakВҰ344432 \add againВҰ344435\add*вҖ”you'll no longer be silent. You'll be a signВҰ344438 for them so that they'll knowВҰ344439 that I am YahwehВҰ344443.вҖқ
\c 25
\ms1 Yahweh's judgement of nations
\mr (25:1вҖ“32:32)
\s1 Ammon's punishment
\rem /s1 Proclamation against Ammon; Prophecy against Ammon; A Prophecy Against Ammon; Prophecies against foreign nations; A Message for Ammon
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ344449 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ344447:\x + \xo 25:1-7: \xt Jer 49:1-6; Eze 21:28-32; Amos 1:13-15; Zeph 2:8-11.\x*
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲkeep looking towards the Ammonites\add* andВҰ344462 prophesyВҰ344462 againstВҰ344458 them.
\v 3 Tell \add *them\add* to listenВҰ344468 to this messageВҰ344469 \add becauseВҰ344478\add* this is what the master YahwehВҰ344471 says: You \add вүҲcelebrated\add* my sanctuaryВҰ344483 \add вүҲbeing\add* desecrated, and the land of YisraelВҰ344490 \add вүҲbeing\add* desolateВҰ344492, and the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YehudahВҰ344496 \add вүҲgoing\add* into exileВҰ344499,
\v 4 so \add вүҲbecause of that\add*, listen: I'm giving you to a peopleВҰ344504 inВҰ344512 the east as their possessionВҰ344507. They'll set up camp against you and set up their tentsВҰ344513 amongВҰ344512 you. They'll eatВҰ344515 your fruitВҰ344516 and drinkВҰ344518 your milk.
\v 5 I'llВҰ344521 make \add the Ammonite capital city\add*, Rabbah,\f + \fr 25:5 \ft Now the modern city of Amman (in Jordan) has been built on Rabbah's ruins.\f* into a camelВҰ344526 pastureВҰ344525, andВҰ344521 the AmmoniteВҰ344530 peopleВҰ344529 into a restingВҰ344531 placeВҰ344531 for flocksВҰ344533. ThenВҰ344521 you \add people\add* will knowВҰ344534 that I am YahwehВҰ344538.
\p
\v 6 Because the masterВҰ344544 YahwehВҰ344544 saysВҰ344543 this: You clappedВҰ344547 your hands and stampedВҰ344549 your feetВҰ344550 and celebrated withВҰ344550 all the contempt within youВҰ344547 against the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ344558 nation\add*,
\v 7 therefore, listen \add Ammon\add*. I'll strike you \add вүҲdown\add* and giveВҰ344568 you as plunderВҰ344570 to the \add other\add* nationsВҰ344573. I'll cut you off from the peopleВҰ344577 groups and make you perishВҰ344578 from among the countriesВҰ344581. I'll destroyВҰ344582 you, and you'll knowВҰ344583 that I am YahwehВҰ344587.вҖҷ
\s1 Moab's punishment
\rem /s1 A Prophecy Against Moab; Proclamation against Moab; A Message for Moab; Prophecy against Moab
\p
\v 8 The masterВҰ344592 YahwehВҰ344592 saysВҰ344591 this, вҖҳBecause MoabВҰ344596 andВҰ344597 SeirВҰ344597 say that the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YehudahВҰ344603 is \add just\add* like every other nationВҰ344601,\x + \xo 25:8-11: \xt Gen 19:36-37; 25:10-12; Jer 48:1-47; Amos 2:1-3; Zeph 2:8-11.\x*
\v 9 \add вүҲwell\add* listen, I'll \add вүҲdestroy the borderВҰ344614 cities\add* \add protecting\add* MoabВҰ344611, starting with the splendour of Beyt-Yeshimot, BaalВҰ344619-MeonВҰ344620, and KiriataimВҰ344621.
\v 10 \add I'll hand them over\add* to the people inВҰ344640 the east who've \add already\add* been against the AmmonitesвҖ”I'll give them up as a possessionВҰ344632 so that the Ammonites won'tВҰ344634 be rememberedВҰ344636 amongВҰ344640 the nationsВҰ344640.
\v 11 \add вүҲYes,\add* I'llВҰ344643 execute judgementsВҰ344644 against Moab, thenВҰ344642 they'll knowВҰ344645 that I am YahwehВҰ344649.вҖҷ
\s1 Edom's punishment
\rem /s1 A Prophecy Against Edom; Prophecy against Edom; Proclamation against Edom; A Message for Edom
\p
\v 12 TheВҰ344655 masterВҰ344654 YahwehВҰ344654 \add also\add* saysВҰ344653, вҖҳEdomВҰ344658 has taken vengeanceВҰ344660 againstВҰ344661 the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YehudahВҰ344662 and has done wrong by doing that.\x + \xo 25:12-14: \xt Gen 25:24-34; 36:39; Jer 49:7-22; Eze 35:1-15; Jer 49:7-22; Oba 1-14; Mal 1:2-5.\x*
\v 13 Therefore, the masterВҰ344671 YahwehВҰ344671 saysВҰ344670: I'll hit EdomВҰ344677 withВҰ344686 my handВҰ344674 and destroy every person and animalВҰ344681 there. I'll make it a ruined, abandoned place, from TemanВҰ344684 \add all the way\add* to DedanВҰ344685вҖ”they'll be killed by the swordВҰ344686.
\v 14 I'llВҰ344689 \add вүҲuse\add* my peopleВҰ344695 YisraelВҰ344696 to place my vengeance onВҰ344693 Edom, and they'll \add вүҲapply\add* my angerВҰ344699 and fury to Edom \add вүҲso\add* they'll knowВҰ344701 my vengeance. That's the masterВҰ344706 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ
\s1 Philistia's punishment
\rem /s1 A Prophecy Against Philistia; Prophecy against Philistia; Proclamation against Philistia; A Message for Philistia
\p
\v 15 The masterВҰ344712 YahwehВҰ344712 saysВҰ344711 this, вҖҳThe PhilistinesВҰ344716 have \add вүҲchosen\add* hateful vengeance andВҰ344718 \add вүҲhave put much effort into trying\add* to destroyВҰ344722 \add *Yehudah\add*.\x + \xo 25:15-17: \xt Yoel 3:4-8; Amos 1:6-8; Jdg 13:1; 1Sam 4:1.\x*
\v 16 So this is what the masterВҰ344729 YahwehВҰ344729 saysВҰ344728: Listen, I'll \add вүҲtake action\add* against the PhilistinesВҰ344736, and I'll cut off the KerethitesВҰ344740 and destroyВҰ344741 the remnantВҰ344744 along the coastВҰ344745.
\v 17 I'llВҰ344748 take severe vengeance against them withВҰ344749 furious acts to punish themвҖ”they'll knowВҰ344754 that I am YahwehВҰ344758, when I take my vengeance onВҰ344749 them.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 26
\s1 Tsor's punishment
\rem /s1 Prophecy against Tyre; A Prophecy Against Tyre; Proclamation against Tyre; A Message for Tyre
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAt the beginning\add* of the monthВҰ344772 inВҰ344767 the eleventh yearВҰ344770 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*, YahwehВҰ344776 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ344774:\x + \xo 26:1вҖ“28:19: \xt Yoel 3:4-8; Amos 1:9-10.\x*
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, Tsor \add (TyreВҰ344787)\add* has saidВҰ344786 against Yerushalem, вҖҳ\add вүҲNice one\add*! \add вүҲYerushalem'sВҰ344790\add* gates are brokenВҰ344792. \add вүҲIt's going my wayвҖ”I can take advantage\add* becauseВҰ344783 it's been destroyed.вҖҷ
\p
\v 3 Because of that, the masterВҰ344803 YahwehВҰ344803 saysВҰ344802 this: вҖҳListen, I'm opposed to you, Tsor, and I'llВҰ344808 raise up many nationsВҰ344810 against you, just like the seaВҰ344813 raises itsВҰ344814 wavesВҰ344814.
\v 4 They'll destroyВҰ344816 Tsor's wallsВҰ344817 and tear down its towersВҰ344820, thenВҰ344816 I'llВҰ344821 sweep its dust away and make it like a bare rockВҰ344827.
\v 5 It'll become a placeВҰ344829 in the middleВҰ344832 of the seaВҰ344833 for \add people to\add* spreadВҰ344829 their netsВҰ344830 \add out to dry them\add*, since I'veВҰ344836 declared it, and it'll become plunderВҰ344841 for the nationsВҰ344842. That's the masterВҰ344838 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 6 Its \add вүҲyoung women\add* who are inВҰ344847 the countrysideВҰ344846 will be slaughtered by swordsВҰ344847, andВҰ344849 thenВҰ344844 they'll knowВҰ344849 thatВҰ344845 I am YahwehВҰ344853.вҖҷ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲYes,\add* this is what YahwehВҰ344859 says: Listen, I'm bringingВҰ344862 the Babylonian KingВҰ344867 NebuchadnezzarВҰ344866, king of kingsВҰ344872, from the northВҰ344870, againstВҰ344863 Tsor, with horsesВҰ344873 and chariotsВҰ344874, and with horsemen and a \add вүҲlarge army\add*.
\v 8 He'll killВҰ344884 your daughters inВҰ344883 the countrysideВҰ344882. He'll set up a siegeВҰ344887 program and buildВҰ344888 a ramp against your walls and liftВҰ344891 up shieldsВҰ344893 against you.
\v 9 He'll use his batteringВҰ344896 rams to \add вүҲsmash down\add* your wallsВҰ344898, andВҰ344895 he'll tear down your towersВҰ344899 withВҰ344898 his axesВҰ344901.
\v 10 \add вүҲThey'll have\add* so many horsesВҰ344904 that their dust will coverВҰ344905 youВҰ344905. Your walls will shakeВҰ344911 withВҰ344913 the noiseВҰ344907 of \add their\add* horsemen, wagonsВҰ344909, and chariotsВҰ344910. When he \add вүҲrides through\add* your gatesВҰ344914, he'll \add pick his way over the stones\add* like men do when enteringВҰ344913 a cityВҰ344916 whose walls have been brokenВҰ344917 down.
\v 11 The hoovesВҰ344919 of his horsesВҰ344920 will trampleВҰ344921 all of your streetsВҰ344926. He'll slaughter your peopleВҰ344927 withВҰ344928 the swordВҰ344928 and your mighty stone pillarsВҰ344930 will \add вүҲbe knocked\add* to the groundВҰ344932.
\v 12 They'll tear down your wallsВҰ344940 and destroy your nice homesвҖ”plunderingВҰ344935 your riches and looting your merchandiseВҰ344938. ThenВҰ344935 they'll throw your \add building\add* stonesВҰ344944, wood, and rubble into the \add вүҲocean\add*.
\v 13 I'llВҰ344951 stop the soundВҰ344954 of your songsВҰ344953, andВҰ344951 the \add вүҲmusic\add* from your harpsВҰ344955 won'tВҰ344956 be heardВҰ344957 anymore.
\v 14 I'llВҰ344960 make you \add back into\add* a bare rockвҖ”you'll become a placeВҰ344963 where nets are spreadВҰ344963 \add out to dry\add*. You'll never be builtВҰ344967 againВҰ344968, because I, master Yahweh, have spokenВҰ344972. That's the master Yahweh's declaration.
\rem /s1 The Effect of Tyre's Destruction
\p
\v 15 The masterВҰ344980 YahwehВҰ344980 saysВҰ344979 this to Tsor, вҖҳWon't the islandsВҰ344993 shake with the soundВҰ344985 of yourВҰ344986 downfallВҰ344986, and with the groansВҰ344987 of the woundedВҰ344988 when the terrible slaughterВҰ344990 is happening inВҰ344987 youВҰ344991?
\v 16 ThenВҰ344995 all the \add вүҲleaders of the coastal kingdoms\add* will step down from their thronesВҰ344997 and removeВҰ345001 their robesВҰ345004 and take off their embroideredВҰ345008 clothes. \add Instead,\add* they'll clothe themselves in fear, they'll sitВҰ345016 on the ground and trembleВҰ345010 every momentВҰ345018, and they'll be appalledВҰ345019 because of youВҰ345020.
\v 17 ThenВҰ345022 they'll \add вүҲsing this song of mourning\add* for you andВҰ345022 say to you,
\q1 How you, who were inhabitedВҰ345029 \add вүҲby sailors\add*, have been destroyed.
\q1 The famous city thatВҰ345033 was so strong, it's now gone from the sea.
\q1 The ones living inВҰ345036 herВҰ345038 once spread terrorВҰ345042 around themselves onВҰ345036 everyone who lived \add вүҲnearby\add*.
\q1
\v 18 Now the coastalВҰ345049 \add kingdoms\add* trembleВҰ345048 onВҰ345056 the dayВҰ345050 of your downfallВҰ345051.
\q1 The islandsВҰ345053 inВҰ345056 the seaВҰ345056 are terrifiedВҰ345052 by your passingВҰ345057.вҖҷ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲYes,\add* the masterВҰ345063 YahwehВҰ345063 saysВҰ345062 this: When I make you a desolateВҰ345068 cityВҰ345067, like the other citiesВҰ345069 thatВҰ345070 are uninhabitedВҰ345073, when I raise up the deep seas against you, and when the greatВҰ345081 watersВҰ345080 coverВҰ345079 you,
\v 20 thenВҰ345083 I'll take you down to the pit that ancient peopleВҰ345090 went down to, because I'll make you live in the lowestВҰ345094 realms of the earth like ancient ruinsВҰ345095. Because of that, you won'tВҰ345102 come back andВҰ345083 \add вүҲbe splendidВҰ345105\add* in the land of the livingВҰ345107.
\v 21 I'llВҰ345110 send disaster onto you, and you won'tВҰ345113 exist anymore. Then \add people\add* will look for you, butВҰ345111 you'll never be foundВҰ345115 againВҰ345116. That's the masterВҰ345119 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ\x + \xo 26:21: \xt Rev 18:21.\x*
\c 27
