\v 11 The men of ArvadВҰ345265 and Helek in your army were on your walls surrounding you,
\q1 and the peopleВҰ345264 from Gammad were in your towersВҰ345272.
\q1 They hung up theirВҰ345274 shieldsВҰ345274 on your walls all around you.
\q1 They completed your beautyВҰ345282.
\p
\v 12 вҖңTarshishВҰ345284 was a trading partner withВҰ345290 you becauseВҰ345286 of your abundantВҰ345286 wealthВҰ345289 of goods. They tradedВҰ345285 silverВҰ345290, iron, tin, and lead for your waresВҰ345295.
\v 13 Yavan, TubalВҰ345298, and MeshechВҰ345299 tradedВҰ345301 \add вүҲslaves\add*, as well as bronzeВҰ345305 items, for yourВҰ345307 merchandiseВҰ345307.
\v 14 Beyt-TogarmahВҰ345310 provided horsesВҰ345311, stallions, and mulesВҰ345313 in exchangeВҰ345314 for yourВҰ345315 products.
\v 15 People from DedanВҰ345318 \add (Rhodes Island)\add* were yourВҰ345319 tradersВҰ345319 on many coasts. \add вүҲYou sent\add* the merchandiseВҰ345322 \add and\add* theyВҰ345328 sent back ivoryВҰ345325 tusks and ebonyВҰ345326 \add wood\add* as paymentВҰ345329.
\v 16 Syria \add (Heb. Aram)\add* was a dealer inВҰ345335 your many productsВҰ345334вҖ”theyВҰ345341 provided emeralds, purpleВҰ345336 dye, coloured cloth, fine fabric, pearls, and rubiesВҰ345340 for your merchandiseВҰ345342.
\v 17 Yehudah and YisraelВҰ345346 were trading withВҰ345349 youВҰ345348. They provided wheatВҰ345349 from MinnitВҰ345350, cakes, honeyВҰ345352, oilВҰ345353, and balsam for yourВҰ345356 merchandiseВҰ345356.
\v 18 DamascusВҰ345358 was a traderВҰ345359 of all your productsВҰ345361, of all your enormous wealthВҰ345365, and of the wine from HelbonВҰ345367 and the wool from Zahar.\f + \fr 27:18 \ft Possibly, Zahar (used only once in the Hebrew scriptures) could refer to the white colour of the wool.\f*
\v 19 Dan and YavanВҰ345372 from UzalВҰ345373 \add вүҲprovided you withВҰ345374\add* merchandise of wroughtВҰ345377 iron, cinnamon, and \add fragrant\add* calamusВҰ345379 \add seeds\add* which became yourВҰ345380 merchandise.
\v 20 Dedan was yourВҰ345384 dealer inВҰ345385 woven saddle blankets.
\v 21 ArabiaВҰ345390 and all of KedarВҰ345394's leaders were tradersВҰ345396 with youвҖ”theyВҰ345395 provided you with lambsВҰ345398, rams, and goatsВҰ345400.
\v 22 Traders from ShebaВҰ345405 and Ramah came to sell youВҰ345408 the best of everyВҰ345410 spiceВҰ345412 and all kinds of preciousВҰ345416 gemsвҖ”they tradedВҰ345404 goldВҰ345417 for yourВҰ345408 goods.
\v 23 Haran, Kanneh, and EdenВҰ345423 were tradersВҰ345424 with youВҰ345428, along with ShebaВҰ345425, Ashur, and Kilmad.
\v 24 Those were your tradersВҰ345431 in fancy robes made of violet cloth withВҰ345432 woven colours, and in blanketsВҰ345436 of multicolouredВҰ345435, embroideredВҰ345435, and well-woven cloth \add вүҲin your marketplacesВҰ345441\add*.
\v 25 TarshishВҰ345444's shipsВҰ345443 were the transporters of yourВҰ345446 merchandiseВҰ345446.
\q1 SoВҰ345444 youВҰ345445 were filledВҰ345447 upвҖ”heavilyВҰ345448 laden withВҰ345450 cargo \add there\add* inВҰ345450 the heartВҰ345450 of the seas.
\q1
\rem /s1 The Destruction of Tyre
\v 26 YourВҰ345459 rowersВҰ345457 have broughtВҰ345456 you into vast seas.
\q1 The east windВҰ345459 has wreckedВҰ345461 you inВҰ345462 the middle of them.
\q1
\v 27 YourВҰ345486 wealth, merchandise, and trade goods,
\q1 your sailorsВҰ345469, pilotsВҰ345469, and ship-builders,
\q1 your traders of merchandise and all the menВҰ345477 of war who are inВҰ345486 youВҰ345486, and all your crewвҖ”
\q1 theyВҰ345487 will sink into the depths of the sea \add вүҲatВҰ345486 the time\add* of your destruction.
\q1
\v 28 The surroundings will shake
\q1 when theyВҰ345496 hear yourВҰ345495 pilot'sВҰ345495 cry \add of distress\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 29 All \add вүҲthe oarsmen\add* will comeВҰ345499 down off theirВҰ345500 shipsВҰ345500.
\q1 Mariners andВҰ345499 all the pilots on the seaВҰ345508 will standВҰ345512 on the land,
\q1
\v 30 thenВҰ345514 they'll raiseВҰ345514 their voicesВҰ345516 towards youВҰ345515 andВҰ345514 will wail bitterlyВҰ345518.
\q1 They'll throwВҰ345519 dust up onto their headsВҰ345523. They'll roll around \add to get covered\add* inВҰ345516 ashesВҰ345524.
\q1
\v 31 They'll shaveВҰ345527 their heads bald for you and \add вүҲdress inВҰ345534\add* \add rough\add* sackcloth,\f + \fr 27:30 \ft All of these (dust, ashes, shaving, sackcloth) are traditional signs of mourning.\f*
\q1 and they'll weep bitterlyВҰ345534 over you and they will cry out \add withВҰ345534 loud moans\add*.
\q1
\v 32 They will wail \add вүҲloudly\add* for you andВҰ345540 sing \add вүҲfuneral songs\add* about you.
\q1 Who is like \add the city of\add* Tsor, which has now been brought to silenceВҰ345548 inВҰ345542 the middleВҰ345549 of the seaВҰ345550?
\q1
\v 33 When your merchandise wentВҰ345552 ashore from the sea, it pleased many peopleВҰ345556 groups.
\q1 You enriched kingsВҰ345562 \add вүҲacross the world\add* withВҰ345558 your great wealthВҰ345559 and merchandise.
\q1
\v 34 ButВҰ345573 when youВҰ345576 were shattered by the seas, by deep watersВҰ345571,
\q1 your merchandiseВҰ345572 and all your crew sank.
\q1
\v 35 All the inhabitantsВҰ345580 of the coastalВҰ345581 \add kingdoms\add* were appalledВҰ345582 at youВҰ345583,
\q1 and their kingsВҰ345584 shudderedВҰ345585 in horrorвҖ”their facesВҰ345588 trembled.
\q1
\v 36 The merchants of the peopleВҰ345591 hiss atВҰ345591 you.
\q1 You've becomeВҰ345595 a horror, and you \add вүҲwon'tВҰ345596 exist anymore\add*.вҖқ
\c 28
\s1 Against the pride of Tsor's king
\rem /s1 Prophecy against the King of Tyre; A Message for Tyre's King; A Prophecy Against the King of Tyre; Proclamation against the King of Tyre
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ345605 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ345603:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, tell Tsor's rulerВҰ345613 that the masterВҰ345619 YahwehВҰ345619 says this: Your heart is proud and you've said, вҖңI'm a god. I'll sit in the seat of godsВҰ345628 in the \add вүҲvital centre\add* of the oceans.вҖқ Even though you're a man and not a god, you \add вүҲtell yourself that you're\add* a god.
\p
\v 3 Listen, \add you king of Tsor\add*, are you wiser than Daniyel was? Are there any secretsВҰ345650 thatВҰ345650 you don'tВҰ345651 \add already\add* know?
\v 4 You've used your wisdomВҰ345654 and skill to make yourselfВҰ345657 wealthyВҰ345658, and amassedВҰ345659 goldВҰ345660 and silverВҰ345661 inВҰ345655 your treasuriesВҰ345662.
\v 5 By greatВҰ345664 wisdomВҰ345665 and by your tradingВҰ345666, you've multiplied your wealth, \add вүҲbutВҰ345669\add* \add now\add* \add вүҲyou've becomeВҰ345669\add* arrogant because of your wealth.
\p
\v 6 Therefore, the masterВҰ345677 YahwehВҰ345677 saysВҰ345676 this: Because you'veВҰ345680 \add вүҲconvinced yourself that you're invincible like\add* a godВҰ345685,
\v 7 I'll bring foreigners against youвҖ”terrifying \add вүҲwarriors\add* from other nationsВҰ345693. They'll bring theirВҰ345695 swordsВҰ345695 against the beautyВҰ345698 of your wisdomВҰ345699, and they'll defileВҰ345700 your splendourВҰ345701.
\v 8 They'll send you down to the pit, and you'll die \add violently\add* like those who die atВҰ345708 sea.
\v 9 Will you really say, вҖңI'm a godвҖқ to the faceВҰ345715 of one who's \add about to\add* kill you? You're a man and not GodВҰ345713, and you'll be \add вүҲatВҰ345722 the mercy\add* of the one who \add вүҲruns you through\add*.
\v 10 You'll dieВҰ345727 \add вүҲlike an ungodly person killed by\add* foreigners, because I'veВҰ345733 declared it. That's the masterВҰ345735 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The fall of the king of Tsor
\rem /s1 The Fall of the King of Tyre; Lamentation over the King of Tyre
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ345742 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ345740:
\v 12 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲsing a mourning song\add* for the kingВҰ345753 of Tsor \add (TyreВҰ345754)\add* and tell him that the masterВҰ345759 YahwehВҰ345759 saysВҰ345758 this:
\q1 You were the model of perfection,
\q1 full of wisdomВҰ345765 and perfect in beautyВҰ345767.
\q1
\v 13 You were in EdenвҖ”God's gardenВҰ345770.
\q1 Every preciousВҰ345777 stoneВҰ345776 coveredВҰ345778 you:
\q1 ruby, topazВҰ345780, emeraldВҰ345787, chrysoliteВҰ345782,
\q1 onyx, jasperВҰ345784, sapphireВҰ345785, turquoiseВҰ345786, and berylВҰ345787.
\q1 Your settingsВҰ345790 and mountingsВҰ345791 were made from goldВҰ345788.
\q1 They were preparedВҰ345795 on the \add very\add* dayВҰ345793 that you were createdВҰ345794.
\q1
\v 14 I placedВҰ345802 you onВҰ345803 God's sacredВҰ345804 mountainВҰ345803
\q1 like the winged creatures thatВҰ345801 I appointedВҰ345802 to guardВҰ345801 humanity.
\q1 You were among the fiery stonesВҰ345808 where you walkedВҰ345811 around.
\q1
\v 15 You had integrity inВҰ345815 yourВҰ345816 waysВҰ345815 from the dayВҰ345816 you were createdВҰ345817
\q1 untilВҰ345818 injustice was foundВҰ345820 within you.
\q1
\v 16 Through yourВҰ345827 great tradeВҰ345825 you were filledВҰ345826 with violenceВҰ345828, and so you sinnedВҰ345829.
\q1 Then I threw you out of God's mountain, like someone who was defiled,
\q1 and I destroyedВҰ345833 you, guardianВҰ345835 winged creature,
\q1 and drove you from amongВҰ345836 the fiery stonesВҰ345837.
\q1
\v 17 Your heartВҰ345842 was arrogant due to your beautyВҰ345843.
\q1 You ruined your wisdomВҰ345845 because of your splendourВҰ345848.
\q1 I threwВҰ345852 you down to the earth.
\q1 I put you inВҰ345843 frontВҰ345853 of kingsВҰ345854 so they can see you.
\q1
\v 18 Because of \add вүҲall your disobedience\add* and your \add вүҲdishonest\add* tradeВҰ345862,
\q1 you've defiled your sacred places,
\q1 \add вүҲso\add* I've made fireВҰ345867 come out from you to consumeВҰ345870 you.
\q1 I'll turn you into ashesВҰ345872 onВҰ345861 the earthВҰ345875
\q1 inВҰ345861 the sightВҰ345876 of everyone who looks atВҰ345861 you.
\q1
\v 19 Everyone who knewВҰ345883 you amongВҰ345884 the peopleВҰ345884 groups
\q1 will \add вүҲshudder to look atВҰ345884\add* you \add now\add*вҖ”
\q1 they will be horrified, and you \add вүҲwon'tВҰ345889 exist any longer\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The punishment of Tsidon
