\rem /s1 Prophecy against Egypt; A Message for Egypt; Proclamation against Egypt; A Prophecy Against Egypt
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAt the beginning of January\add* inВҰ346025 the twelfth yearВҰ346025 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*, YahwehВҰ346034 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ346032:\x + \xo 29:1вҖ“32:32: \xt Isa 19:1-25; Jer 46:2-26.\x*
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲstand firmly\add* against Egypt'sВҰ346047 kingВҰ346046 Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ346045)\add*. Prophesy against him and against all of Egypt,
\v 3 telling \add them\add* that the masterВҰ346061 YahwehВҰ346061 says this: Listen, I'm againstВҰ346064 you, Far-oh, kingВҰ346066 of EgyptВҰ346068вҖ”you, the greatВҰ346070 seaВҰ346069 monsterВҰ346069 that lurks in the middleВҰ346072 of the river, who says, вҖңMy river is my own. I've made it for myselfВҰ346079.вҖқ
\v 4 I'll put hooksВҰ346082 into your jaw, andВҰ346081 the fish from your streams will cling to the scales onВҰ346084 your \add side\add*. I'll lift you up from the middle of your river, along withВҰ346084 all the river's fish that cling to your scales.
\v 5 I'll flingВҰ346101 you into the wildernessВҰ346102вҖ”you and all the fishВҰ346107 from your river. You'll fall on the open countrysideВҰ346112вҖ”\add @your corpse\add* won'tВҰ346114 be taken or moved, \add butВҰ346101 rather\add* I'll giveВҰ346122 you as food to the birds and wild animalsВҰ346118.
\v 6 ThenВҰ346125 all of Egypt'sВҰ346129 inhabitantsВҰ346128 will knowВҰ346125 that IВҰ346131 am YahwehВҰ346132, becauseВҰ346133 they've been \add like a brittle\add* reed to the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YisraelВҰ346138.\x + \xo 29:6: \xt Isa 36:6.\x*
\v 7 When \add @Yisrael\add* \add вүҲgrabbed you\add*, you broke and tore open their shoulderВҰ346149, and when they leanedВҰ346150 onВҰ346141 you, you broke and made their legs unsteadyВҰ346153.
\v 8 Therefore the masterВҰ346163 YahwehВҰ346163 saysВҰ346162 this: Listen, I'llВҰ346169 send \add вүҲan army\add* against you that will cut short both people's and animalsВҰ346172' \add lives\add*,
\v 9 andВҰ346174 EgyptВҰ346177 will becomeВҰ346174 a desolateВҰ346178 ruin. ThenВҰ346174 they'll knowВҰ346180 that I am YahwehВҰ346184.
\p Because the sea monster saidВҰ346186, вҖңThe river is mine, becauseВҰ346185 I made it,вҖқ
\v 10 listen: I'm against you and against yourВҰ346197 river, so I'llВҰ346198 give EgyptВҰ346202 over to desolationВҰ346205 and waste, and you'll become a wasteland from the MigdolВҰ346206 to Seveneh and the bordersВҰ346210 of Kush.
\v 11 No person or domestic animalВҰ346220 will pass through it, and it won'tВҰ346221 be inhabited for fortyВҰ346227 years.
\v 12 I'll make EgyptВҰ346234 a desolation in the middle of uninhabited lands, and its cities will become a desolation in the middle of wastedВҰ346243 cities for fortyВҰ346246 years, thenВҰ346230 I'll scatterВҰ346248 \add вүҲthe Egyptian people\add* among the nationsВҰ346252, and I'll disperseВҰ346253 them through the lands.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲBut\add* the masterВҰ346260 YahwehВҰ346260 saysВҰ346259 this: At the end of fortyВҰ346263 years I'llВҰ346265 gatherВҰ346265 EgyptВҰ346268 from the peopleВҰ346271 groups theyВҰ346274 were scatteredВҰ346274 among,
\v 14 and I'llВҰ346281 restoreВҰ346277 EgyptВҰ346281's fortunes and bringВҰ346282 them back to the regionВҰ346284 of PatrosВҰ346285, to theirВҰ346289 nativeВҰ346289 land. ThenВҰ346277 they'll become an insignificantВҰ346293 kingdomВҰ346292 thereВҰ346291.
\v 15 It'll be the least significant kingdomВҰ346297, and it won'tВҰ346300 \add вүҲbecome prominent\add* againВҰ346303 among the nations. I'llВҰ346307 diminish them so that they'll no longer \add вүҲdominate\add* \add other\add* nations.
\v 16 \add Requesting help from\add* \add @Egypt\add* will no longer be a reason for the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YisraelВҰ346317 to be confidentВҰ346318, instead, \add @Egypt\add* will be a reminder of Yisrael's \add вүҲdisobedience\add* when they turnedВҰ346321 to \add @Egypt\add* for help. ThenВҰ346312 they'll knowВҰ346323 thatВҰ346319 I am the masterВҰ346326 YahwehВҰ346326.вҖқ
\s1 Nebuchadnetstsar's defeat of Egypt
\rem /s1 King Nebuchadnezzar Will Conquer Egypt; Nebuchadnezzar to Conquer Egypt; Babylonia Will Plunder Egypt
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲAt the beginning of May\add* inВҰ346331 the 27th yearВҰ346333 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*,\f + \fr 29:17 \ft 571 B.C.\f* YahwehВҰ346340 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ346338:
\v 18 вҖңHumanity's child, the Babylonian KingВҰ346348 Nebuchadnetstsar stationed his army to do hard work against \add the fortified island city of\add* Tsor \add (TyreВҰ346359)\add*. Every headВҰ346362 was rubbed until it was made bald, and everyВҰ346360 shoulderВҰ346366 was made raw. Yet he and his army received no payment from Tsor for the hard work thatВҰ346378 he carried out against it,
\v 19 therefore the masterВҰ346387 YahwehВҰ346387 saysВҰ346386 this, вҖҳListen, I'm giving EgyptВҰ346398 to the Babylonian KingВҰ346392 Nebuchadnetstsar and he'll takeВҰ346403 away its wealthВҰ346400, plunderВҰ346404 its possessions, and carryВҰ346399 off everything he finds thereвҖ”that will be his army's wages.
\v 20 I'veВҰ346414 givenВҰ346414 him the land of EgyptВҰ346419 as the wages for the work theyВҰ346421 did for me. That's the masterВҰ346424 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 21 On that dayВҰ346428 I'll make \add вүҲpower\add* sprout up for the \add вүҲkingdom\add* of YisraelВҰ346433, and I'll \add вүҲput youВҰ346434 amongВҰ346439 them to speak out\add* so they'll knowВҰ346440 that I am YahwehВҰ346444.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 30
\s1 Yahweh's punishment of Egypt
\rem /s1 A Lament for Egypt; Lamentation for Egypt; The Lord Will Punish Egypt; A Sad Day for Egypt
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ346450 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ346448:
\q1
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, prophesyВҰ346457 andВҰ346458 sayВҰ346458 that the masterВҰ346461 YahwehВҰ346461 saysВҰ346460 this:
\q1 вҖҳWail \add now\add* \add вүҲbecause the coming days won't go well\add*.
\q1
\v 3 The day is nearвҖ”the day is near for YahwehВҰ346473.
\q1 It'll be a day of cloudsВҰ346475вҖ”a time of doom for nationsВҰ346477.
\q1
\v 4 ThenВҰ346480 \add вүҲan army\add* will comeВҰ346480 against EgyptВҰ346482,
\q1 and there'll be anguishВҰ346484 in Kush when the peopleВҰ346489 are killed in EgyptвҖ”
\q1 when they takeВҰ346489 its wealthВҰ346490,
\q1 and when its foundationsВҰ346492 get torn apart.
\p
\v 5 Kush and PutВҰ346495, Lydia, all ArabiaВҰ346499, and LibyaВҰ346500, together withВҰ346505 the people belonging to the agreementвҖ”they'll all be killed by the swordВҰ346505.
\v 6 Yahweh saysВҰ346510 this: The ones who supportВҰ346513 Egypt \add militarily\add* will fall, and the prideВҰ346516 of \add @Egypt's\add* strengthВҰ346517 will \add вүҲcollapse\add*. From MigdolВҰ346518 to Seveneh \add @their combined warriors\add* will be killed by the swordВҰ346520. That's the masterВҰ346525 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 7 \add @Those allies\add* will be appalled in the midst of the abandoned landsВҰ346530, andВҰ346528 theirВҰ346532 cities will be among all the \add other\add* ruined cities.
\v 8 ThenВҰ346539 they'll knowВҰ346539 that I am YahwehВҰ346543, when I set fireВҰ346546 to EgyptВҰ346547, andВҰ346548 when all itsВҰ346551 helpersВҰ346551 are destroyed.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, messengersВҰ346556 will go out from in front of me in shipsВҰ346558 to terrorise Kush \add вүҲwhen they think they're secureВҰ346563\add*, and there'llВҰ346570 be anguishВҰ346565 among them onВҰ346558 the day of Egypt'sВҰ346568 doom. \add вүҲYes, take notice,\add* it's comingВҰ346571.
\v 10 The masterВҰ346576 YahwehВҰ346576 saysВҰ346575 this: I'llВҰ346578 \add вүҲuse\add* the Babylonian KingВҰ346585 Nebuchadnetstsar to bring Egypt'sВҰ346582 multitudesВҰ346581 to an endВҰ346578.
\v 11 He and his army with him, the terror of nationsВҰ346593, will be broughtВҰ346594 in to destroyВҰ346595 the land. They'll draw out theirВҰ346598 swordsВҰ346598 against EgyptВҰ346601 and fillВҰ346602 the land with those they killВҰ346595.
\v 12 I'll make the rivers into dry groundВҰ346610, and I'll sell the land into the hands of wickedВҰ346617 men. I'll make the land and itsВҰ346620 abundant \add produce\add* desolateВҰ346618 by the actions of strangersВҰ346623. I, YahwehВҰ346625, have spokenВҰ346626.
\p
\v 13 The masterВҰ346632 YahwehВҰ346632 says this: I'll destroyВҰ346634 idols, and I'll bring an end to the worthlessВҰ346637 idols in MemphisВҰ346638 \add (Heb. вҖҳNofвҖҷВҰ346638)\add*. There won'tВҰ346643 be a princeВҰ346639 in the land of Egypt any longer, and I'll put terror into Egypt.
\v 14 ThenВҰ346652 I'll make \add the\add* PatrosВҰ346655 \add region\add* desolate and set fireВҰ346657 to TsoanВҰ346658 \add city\add*, and I'll executeВҰ346659 judgementВҰ346660 against ThebesВҰ346661 \add (Heb. вҖҳNoВҰ346661вҖҷ, the capital of southern Egypt)\add*.
\v 15 I'llВҰ346663 pour out my fury on Egypt'sВҰ346669 strongholdВҰ346668 Pelusium \add (Heb. вҖҳSinВҰ346667вҖҷ)\add*, andВҰ346670 cut off the crowdВҰ346673 at ThebesВҰ346674.
\v 16 ThenВҰ346676 I'llВҰ346676 set fireВҰ346677 to EgyptВҰ346678: PelusiumВҰ346682 will be inВҰ346678 great agonyВҰ346679, ThebesВҰ346683 will be brokenВҰ346685 up, andВҰ346676 MemphisВҰ346686 will face enemies every day.
\v 17 The youngВҰ346690 menВҰ346690 of Aven and Pi-Veset \add cities\add* will be killed by the swordВҰ346695, and their \add вүҲpopulations will be taken\add* into captivityВҰ346698.
\v 18 In \add Egypt's\add* Tahfanhes, the dayВҰ346703 will hold back its light when I breakВҰ346704 Egypt's \add вүҲpower and control\add* thereВҰ346706, and its prideВҰ346714 inВҰ346701 its strengthВҰ346715 will be finished. There'll be a cloudВҰ346717 coveringВҰ346718 it, and its daughtersВҰ346719 will \add вүҲbe taken away\add* into captivityВҰ346720.
\v 19 I'llВҰ346723 executeВҰ346723 acts of judgementВҰ346724 inВҰ346725 EgyptВҰ346725, thenВҰ346723 they'll knowВҰ346726 that I am YahwehВҰ346730.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Yahweh breaks Egypt's power
\rem /s1 The Broken Arms of Pharaoh; The Broken Power of the King of Egypt; Proclamation against Pharaoh
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲAt the beginning of May\add* in the eleventh yearВҰ346736 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*,\f + \fr 30:20 \ft (Back in time to) 587 B.C.\f* YahwehВҰ346743 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ346741:
\v 21 вҖңHumanity's child, I'veВҰ346757 brokenВҰ346757 the Egyptian kingВҰ346754 Far-oh's arm. Listen, it hasn't been \add вүҲput inВҰ346769 a splint\add*, or set to heal withВҰ346769 a bandageВҰ346765, so that it'll become strongВҰ346767 enough \add again\add* to hold a swordВҰ346769.
\v 22 Therefore the masterВҰ346777 YahwehВҰ346777 saysВҰ346775 this, вҖҳListen, I'm againstВҰ346780 the Egyptian kingВҰ346783 Far-oh and I'll breakВҰ346786 both his strongВҰ346792 arm and the \add previously\add* brokenВҰ346795 one, and I'll make the sword fall from his \add вүҲgrip\add*.
\v 23 ThenВҰ346802 I'llВҰ346807 scatterВҰ346802 EgyptВҰ346805 among the \add other\add* nationsВҰ346806 andВҰ346807 disperseВҰ346807 \add @their people\add* among the landsВҰ346808.
\v 24 I'llВҰ346810 strengthenВҰ346810 the Babylonian king's arms andВҰ346810 place my swordВҰ346819 in his handВҰ346820 so that I can destroy Far-oh's arms. He'll groan in front of the Babylonian king with the groans of a dying man.
\v 25 I'llВҰ346831 strengthenВҰ346831 the arms of the Babylonian king, while Far-oh's arms will fall. ThenВҰ346831 they'll know that I am YahwehВҰ346844, when I put my swordВҰ346846 into the handВҰ346847 of the king of BabylonВҰ346836 andВҰ346831 he \add вүҲuses\add* it againstВҰ346853 EgyptВҰ346856.
\v 26 I'llВҰ346858 scatterВҰ346858 EgyptВҰ346861 among the \add other\add* nationsВҰ346862 andВҰ346858 disperseВҰ346863 \add @their people\add* through the landsВҰ346865. ThenВҰ346858 they'll knowВҰ346866 that I am YahwehВҰ346870.вҖқ
\c 31
\s1 Egypt gets compared to fallen Assyria
\rem /s1 Egypt Is Compared to a Cedar Tree; A Cedar in Lebanon; Egypt Compared to Fallen Assyria; The Lofty Cedar
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAt the end of June\add* inВҰ346874 the eleventh yearВҰ346876 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*,\f + \fr 31:1 \ft 587 B.C.\f* YahwehВҰ346883 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ346881:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲask\add* the Egyptian kingВҰ346894 Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ346893)\add* and his multitudesВҰ346899 around him, вҖҳ\add вүҲWho else is as powerful as youВҰ346903 and yourВҰ346904 peopleВҰ346899\add*?
\v 3 Listen, AssyriaВҰ346907 was \add like\add* a cedarВҰ346908 inВҰ346909 LebanonВҰ346909 withВҰ346909 beautifulВҰ346910 branches, giving shadeВҰ346913 to the forestВҰ346912вҖ”extremely tall, and the branches formed its treetopВҰ346919.
\v 4 \add вүҲA deep water supply\add* made it grow tall. Rivers flowed all aroundВҰ346929 its area, because their channelsВҰ346933 stretched out to all the treesВҰ346938 in the countrysideВҰ346939.
\v 5 It \add вүҲgrew taller\add* than any of the other treesВҰ346947 in the countrysideВҰ346948, and its branchesВҰ346952 grew longВҰ346951 and \add вүҲthick\add* becauseВҰ346954 of \add вүҲhaving plenty of\add* waterВҰ346954 in its shootsВҰ346956.
\v 6 Every \add вүҲkind of\add* bird nested in its branchesВҰ346965, while every living thing in the countrysideВҰ346969 gaveВҰ346966 birthВҰ346966 to its young under the foliage of that tree. All the powerful nationsВҰ346973 lived under its shadeВҰ346970.
\v 7 It was beautifulВҰ346976 inВҰ346977 its greatnessВҰ346977 andВҰ346976 due to the lengthВҰ346978 of its branchesВҰ346979, because its rootsВҰ346983 \add вүҲhad access to\add* many waterВҰ346986 \add sources\add*.
\v 8 CedarВҰ346989 trees in God's garden couldn't equal it. None of the cypress trees matched its branches, nor could its branches be equalled by the planeВҰ347002 tree. There was no other tree in God's garden that could compare to its beautyВҰ347017.\x + \xo 31:8: \xt Gen 2:9.\x*
\v 9 I made it beautiful withВҰ347021 its many branchesВҰ347022, and all the treesВҰ347026 in God's gardenВҰ347030 in EdenВҰ347028 enviedВҰ347023 it.
\p
\v 10 Therefore the masterВҰ347037 YahwehВҰ347037 saysВҰ347036 this: Because it was so tall, and it set its treetopВҰ347044 betweenВҰ347047 its branchesВҰ347048, and \add вүЎbecause\add* it \add вүҲgrew proudВҰ347049\add* of its heightВҰ347051,
\v 11 I \add вүҲhanded it over to\add* a powerful nationВҰ347056 to deal withВҰ347054 it accordingВҰ347060 to what its wickednessВҰ347060 deserves. I've thrownВҰ347061 it out,
\v 12 and foreigners who were the terror of all the nations cut it off and left it to die. Its branchesВҰ347075 fell onto the mountainsВҰ347070 and all the valleysВҰ347073, and lay brokenВҰ347076 inВҰ347078 all the land's ravinesВҰ347079. ThenВҰ347063 all the nations onВҰ347078 earth came out from under its shadeВҰ347082 and went away from it.
\v 13 All the \add вүҲvarious kinds of\add* birds rested on the trunkВҰ347091 of the fallenВҰ347091 tree, and every \add kind of\add* animalВҰ347102 in the countrysideВҰ347103 came to its branchesВҰ347099.
\v 14 That happened so that no other trees that grow by the waters will raise up theirВҰ347129 foliage to the height of the tallest trees, and that no other trees that grow beside the waters will reach up to that height. They've all been assigned to deathВҰ347139, to the earthВҰ347142 below, among humanity'sВҰ347146 childrenВҰ347145, withВҰ347110 thoseВҰ347149 that go down into the pit.
\p
\v 15 The masterВҰ347156 YahwehВҰ347156 says this: On the dayВҰ347158 when the cedar went down to \add вүҲthe place of the dead\add*, I brought mourning to the earth. I coveredВҰ347162 the deep waters over it, and I held back the oceans. I held back the great waters, and I brought mourning to LebanonВҰ347174 for it. So all the treesВҰ347177 in the countrysideВҰ347178 mourned because of it.
\v 16 I broughtВҰ347186 shuddering to the nationsВҰ347185 atВҰ347186 the soundВҰ347182 of its downfallВҰ347183, when I threw it down to \add вүҲthe place of the dead\add*, along withВҰ347186 thoseВҰ347191 who went down into the pit. So I comfortedВҰ347193 all the trees from EdenВҰ347200 inВҰ347186 the lowestВҰ347195 parts of the earth. Those had been the choicestВҰ347201 and best trees from LebanonВҰ347204вҖ”the trees that drank the watersВҰ347208.
\v 17 They also wentВҰ347214 down withВҰ347223 \add @the big tree\add* to \add вүҲthe place of the dead\add*, to the ones who'd been killed by the swordВҰ347220. Those were its strong armвҖ”thoseВҰ347218 nationsВҰ347225 who'd lived inВҰ347223 its shadeВҰ347223.
\p
\v 18 \add Egypt,\add* which of the trees in Eden was your equal in gloryВҰ347232 and greatnessВҰ347233? You'll be broughtВҰ347237 down with Eden'sВҰ347236 trees to the lowestВҰ347247 parts of the earthВҰ347246 amongВҰ347234 the uncircumcisedВҰ347249. You'll live there with thoseВҰ347253 who were killed by the swordВҰ347255.вҖҷ
\m That's \add the fate of\add* Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ347257)\add* and all his multitudesВҰ347260. That's the masterВҰ347263 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 32
\s1 Mourning over Egypt and its king
\rem /s1 A Lament for Pharaoh; A Warning for Pharaoh; The King of Egypt Is Compared to a Crocodile; Lamentation over Pharaoh and Egypt
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAt the beginning of March\add* inВҰ347268 the twelfth yearВҰ347270 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*,\f + \fr 32:1 \ft 585 B.C.\f* YahwehВҰ347280 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ347278:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲsing a loud mourning song\add* aboutВҰ347303 the Egyptian KingВҰ347292 Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ347291)\add* and tell him,
\q1 вҖҳYou're like a youngВҰ347297 lionВҰ347297 among the nationsВҰ347298,
\q1 butВҰ347295 you're like the sea monsterВҰ347301 inВҰ347304 the oceansвҖ”
\q1 you churn up the waterвҖ”
\q1 you stir up the watersВҰ347307 withВҰ347304 your feetВҰ347308, making them muddy.
\q1
\v 3 TheВҰ347315 masterВҰ347314 YahwehВҰ347314 says this:
\q1 I'llВҰ347316 spreadВҰ347316 my net over you in the assemblyВҰ347321 of many peopleВҰ347322 groups,
\q1 and they'll haul you up in my net.
\q1
\v 4 I'll abandonВҰ347327 you in the land.
\q1 I'll throwВҰ347327 you into the countrysideВҰ347332
\q1 and causeВҰ347334 \add вүҲevery kind of\add* bird to settleВҰ347334 on you,
\q1 and animalsВҰ347342 of \add вүҲevery kind of\add* will gorgeВҰ347340 themselves on you.
\q1
\v 5 I'llВҰ347347 \add вүҲdump\add* your fleshВҰ347350 on the hills,
\q1 andВҰ347347 fillВҰ347354 the valleysВҰ347355 with your corpse.
\q1
\v 6 ThenВҰ347358 I'llВҰ347358 drenchВҰ347358 your land with your blood \add across\add* to the hills,
\q1 andВҰ347358 the ravinesВҰ347365 will be filledВҰ347366 with your blood.
\q1
\v 7 ThenВҰ347369 when I \add вүҲeliminate\add* you, I'll cover the heavensВҰ347371 and darkenВҰ347372 theirВҰ347375 starsВҰ347375.
\q1 I'll cover the sun withВҰ347370 cloudsВҰ347377, and the moon won'tВҰ347380 shine its light.\x + \xo 32:7: \xt Mat 24:29; Rev 6:12-13; 8:12.\x*
\q1
\v 8 I'll darkenВҰ347390 all the shining lightsВҰ347388 inВҰ347389 the skiesВҰ347389 over youВҰ347391,
\q1 and I'll put darknessВҰ347393 over yourВҰ347396 land. That's the masterВҰ347398 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 9 I'llВҰ347401 disturbВҰ347401 the heartsВҰ347402 of many peopleВҰ347403 groups inВҰ347405 lands thatВҰ347411 you don'tВҰ347412 know \add about\add*
\q1 when I bringВҰ347405 about yourВҰ347406 destructionВҰ347406 among the nationsВҰ347407вҖ”among lands you haven't knownВҰ347414.
\q1
\v 10 I'll shock many peopleВҰ347418 groups \add вүҲwithВҰ347424 what I'll do to\add* you.
\q1 TheirВҰ347428 kingsВҰ347420 will shudderВҰ347421 inВҰ347424 horror concerning you when I swing my swordВҰ347425 \add вүҲtowards\add* them.
\q1 On the dayВҰ347433 of yourВҰ347422 downfallВҰ347434 they'll be tremblingВҰ347429 \add вүҲcontinuously\add* becauseВҰ347422 of you.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲYes,\add* the masterВҰ347440 YahwehВҰ347440 saysВҰ347439 this \add to you, Egypt\add*:
\q1 The Babylonian king's swordВҰ347442 will comeВҰ347446 against you.
\q1
\v 12 I'llВҰ347450 cause large numbers of you to be killed by warriors' swordsВҰ347448вҖ”each warrior a terror of nationsВҰ347453.
\q1 Those warriors will devastateВҰ347455 the prideВҰ347458 of EgyptВҰ347459 and destroyВҰ347460 all itsВҰ347463 \add вүҲmany peopleВҰ347451\add*.
\q1
\v 13 I'llВҰ347465 destroyВҰ347465 all the livestockВҰ347481 from beside the plentiful waters.
\q1 No humanВҰ347478 footВҰ347476 will stir the waters up againВҰ347479,
\q1 nor will cattleВҰ347470 hoovesВҰ347480 disturb them.
\q1
\v 14 Then I'llВҰ347486 calm their watersВҰ347487 and make their riversВҰ347488 run like oilВҰ347489.
\q1 That's the masterВҰ347492 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 15 When I make Egypt'sВҰ347499 territory into an abandoned place,
\q1 when the land is \add вүҲstripped of all itsВҰ347503 produce\add*,
\q1 when I attack all its inhabitantsВҰ347509, they'll knowВҰ347511 that I am YahwehВҰ347515.
\q1
\v 16 There'll be a \add вүҲfuneral song\add*вҖ”the daughtersВҰ347520 of the nationsВҰ347521 will sing mournful songs about it.
\q1 They'll sing sadly about EgyptВҰ347526вҖ”over all its multitudesВҰ347531 they'll sing dirges.
\q1 That's the masterВҰ347535 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Those in the place of the dead
\rem /s1 The World of the Dead; Egypt Falls into the Pit; Dirge over Egypt
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲIn the middle of that same monthВҰ347545\add*,\f + \fr 32:17 \ft 585 B.C.\f* YahwehВҰ347549 \add вүҲgave me\add* a messageВҰ347547:
\v 18 вҖңHumanity's child, weep for the \add вүҲnumerous Egyptians\add* and bringВҰ347561 them down to the lowestВҰ347569 partsВҰ347569 of the earthВҰ347568. \add вүЎBring\add* \add @Egypt\add* and the daughtersВҰ347563 of majestic nationsВҰ347564 down along with thoseВҰ347572 who've \add already\add* gone down into the pit.
\v 19 \add Ask them: Egypt,\add* are youВҰ347576 really more beautiful than anyone else? Go down andВҰ347578 lie down with the uncircumcisedВҰ347581.
\p
\v 20 They'll fall among thoseВҰ347584 who were killed by the sword. The sword has been drawnВҰ347590. \add @Egypt\add* has been handed over to the swordвҖ”\add @its enemies\add* will seize it and its multitudesВҰ347594.
\v 21 The strongest of the warriors in \add вүҲthe place of the dead\add* will declare about Egypt and its allies, вҖҳThey've comeВҰ347606 down here. They'll lie with the uncircumcisedВҰ347608вҖ”with those who were killed by the swordВҰ347611.вҖҷ
\p
\v 22 AssyriaВҰ347614 is thereВҰ347613 with all its \add вүҲpeople\add*, with its gravesВҰ347619 all aroundВҰ347618 itВҰ347618вҖ”all of them were killed by the swordВҰ347623.
\v 23 Those whose graves are set inВҰ347628 the pit's recesses\x + \xo 32:23 \xt Isa 14:15.\x* are there, along withВҰ347628 all itsВҰ347632 \add вүҲpeople\add*. ItsВҰ347632 graves surround all of those who were killed by the swordВҰ347638вҖ”those who brought terrorВҰ347642 onto the land of the livingВҰ347644.
\p
\v 24 Eylam is thereВҰ347646 with all its multitudesВҰ347650, with its gravesВҰ347652 all aroundВҰ347651 itвҖ”all of them were killed. \add That's the place for\add* thoseВҰ347675 who were killed by the swordВҰ347656, who've gone down uncircumcisedВҰ347660 to the lowestВҰ347665 partsВҰ347665 of the earthВҰ347664, who brought their terrorsВҰ347668 onto the land of the livingВҰ347670, and who carry their own shame, together with the ones going down into the pit.
\v 25 They \add вүҲprepared\add* a bed for Eylam and all its multitudesВҰ347685 among those who were slainвҖ”its gravesВҰ347687 surround it. All of them are uncircumcisedВҰ347689, pierced by the swordВҰ347692, because they brought their terrorsВҰ347696 onto the land of the livingВҰ347698. So they carry their own shame, together with the ones going down into the pit among all those who've been killed, those who are going down into the pit. \add @Eylam\add* is among all those who were killed.
\p
\v 26 MeshekВҰ347710, Tuval, and all their multitudesВҰ347714 are thereВҰ347709 with their gravesВҰ347716 all aroundВҰ347715 them. All of them are uncircumcisedВҰ347718, killed by the swordВҰ347720, because theyВҰ347723 brought their terrorsВҰ347724 onto the land of the livingВҰ347726.
\v 27 TheyВҰ347738 don'tВҰ347728 lie with the fallenВҰ347733 warriors of the uncircumcisedВҰ347734 who've gone down to \add вүҲthe place of the dead\add* with all their weaponsВҰ347739 of war, and with their swordsВҰ347745 placed underВҰ347746 their headsВҰ347747 and their iniquitiesВҰ347749 over their bonesВҰ347752, because they were the terrorВҰ347755 of warriors inВҰ347739 the land of the livingВҰ347758.
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ347760\add* youВҰ347763, \add Egypt,\add* will be brokenВҰ347763 amongst the uncircumcisedВҰ347762. You'll lie alongside thoseВҰ347767 who were pierced by the swordВҰ347769.
\p
\v 29 EdomВҰ347772 is \add also\add* there with its kingsВҰ347773 and all its leaders. \add вүҲDespite theirВҰ347780 strengthВҰ347780\add*, they've been placed with those killed by the swordВҰ347785. They lie there along with the uncircumcisedВҰ347789вҖ”with those who've gone down into the pit.
\p
\v 30 All the northernВҰ347798 leaders are there, along with all the SidoniansВҰ347802 who went down with the ones who'd been pierced. They were powerful and made others afraid, butВҰ347800 now they're there inВҰ347809 shameвҖ”uncircumcisedВҰ347814 along with those who were pierced by the swordВҰ347819. They carry theirВҰ347799 own shame, together with the ones going down into the pit.
\p
\v 31 Far-oh \add (PharaohВҰ347829)\add* will look and be comfortedВҰ347830 about all his multitudesВҰ347835 who were pierced by the swordВҰ347839вҖ”Far-oh and all his army. That's the masterВҰ347845 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲYes,\add* I put him there as my \add вүҲagent to terrify those\add* in the land of the livingВҰ347856, butВҰ347857 Far-oh and all his multitudesВҰ347868 will be laid down among the uncircumcisedВҰ347859вҖ”among those pierced by the swordВҰ347864. That's the masterВҰ347871 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 33
\ms1 The promise of God of his people
\mr (33:1вҖ“37:27)
\s1 Yehezkel as Yisrael's watchman
\rem /s1 Ezekiel as Israel's Watchman; God Appoints Ezekiel as a Lookout; The watchman prepares for the restored kingdom; Ezekiel Israel's Sentry; Ezekiel a Watchman
\r (Eze. 3:16-21)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ347878 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ347876:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's childВҰ347888, tell this to your people: вҖҳWhen I \add вүҲsend an army\add* against any \add вүҲcountry\add*, then the people of that \add вүҲcountry chooseВҰ347899 one of theirВҰ347905 men to become\add* a watchmanВҰ347909 for them.
\v 3 He looks for \add вүҲany attacker comingВҰ347915 onto\add* the land, andВҰ347911 thenВҰ347911 he blowsВҰ347919 his horn to warnВҰ347921 the peopleВҰ347924.
\v 4 If the people hearВҰ347926 the soundВҰ347930 of the horn butВҰ347926 don'tВҰ347932 \add вүҲtake any notice\add*, and if the \add вүҲattacker\add* comesВҰ347934 and kills them, thenВҰ347926 each one's bloodВҰ347937 is onВҰ347938 their own headВҰ347938.
\v 5 \add Yes,\add* if someone heardВҰ347944 the horn \add вүҲbut paid no attention\add*, \add @that person's\add* bloodВҰ347947 is on them, \add вүҲbut\add* if \add @those people\add* \add вүҲdo pay attention\add*, they'll save their own lives.
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the watchman sees the \add вүҲattacker\add* comingВҰ347962, \add вүҲbut\add* doesn't blow the horn, \add вүҲthat is, if\add* the peopleВҰ347967 weren't warnedВҰ347970, and if the \add вүҲattacker approaches\add* and takes anyone'sВҰ347975 life, thenВҰ347955 that person dies inВҰ347966 their own sin, \add вүҲbut\add* I'llВҰ347983 requireВҰ347983 their bloodВҰ347979 from the watchman.вҖҷ
\p
\v 7 Now, \add вүҲtalking to\add* you, humanity'sВҰ347989 child: I'veВҰ347991 made you a watchmanВҰ347990 for the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ347993 people\add*. You'll hearВҰ347994 the words from my mouthВҰ347995 and then warnВҰ347997 them on my behalf.
\v 8 If I say to a wicked person, вҖҳYou wicked person, you're certainly about to die,вҖҷ and if you don'tВҰ348006 announce it so as to warn that wicked \add person\add* about their behaviour, then that wicked \add person\add* will die inВҰ348013 their sin, butВҰ348006 \add вүҲit'll be you that I hold responsible for their death\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ348019\add* if you warn the wickedВҰ348023 person about their behaviour, so that they might turn back from it, andВҰ348019 if that person doesn't turn back from their behaviour, thenВҰ348019 they'll die inВҰ348032 their sin, butВҰ348019 you yourself will have saved your own lifeВҰ348035.
\s1 Each person is responsible for their own deeds
\rem /s1 Individual Responsibility; The Watchman's Message; God's Justice and Mercy
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSo,\add* humanity'sВҰ348042 child, youВҰ348049 tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ348046 people\add*, вҖҳYou're saying this, вҖңOur errors and our disobedience \add вүҲhave come back on us and they're hurting\add* us. How can we go on living \add like this\add*?вҖқ вҖҷ
\v 11 Tell them that this is the masterВҰ348070 Yahweh's declaration: вҖҳAs I live, I don't delight inВҰ348075 the deathВҰ348075 of wicked people. If they turn away from their wicked behaviour, then they'll live! \add вүҲSo turn back\add*, \add yes\add* turn away from your wicked behaviour. Why should you \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ348090 people\add* dieВҰ348089?вҖҷ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSo now\add*, humanity'sВҰ348097 childВҰ348101, you tell your people, вҖҳRighteous people's righteousness won't saveВҰ348107 them if they sin. Wicked people's wickednessВҰ348111 won't cause them to die if they turn away from their sin. \add вүҲNo,\add* the righteous person won't be able to liveВҰ348122 because of his righteousness if he sinsВҰ348125.
\v 13 If I say that a righteous person will surely live, and if they trust inВҰ348145 their righteousness and then commit injusticeВҰ348145, I won'tВҰ348143 call to mind any of \add вүҲthe good things they did\add*вҖ”that person will dieВҰ348150 for the wickedness they committed.
\v 14 \add вүҲAgain,\add* if I say to the wickedВҰ348153, вҖңYou will surelyВҰ348154 die,вҖқ butВҰ348152 if they thenВҰ348152 turn away from their sins and do what's just and rightВҰ348160,
\v 15 \add вүҲlike\add* returningВҰ348163 loan guarantees that were wickedly demanded, or \add вүҲlike\add* making restitution for what they've stolen, and then if they \add вүҲobey the instructions\add* that give lifeВҰ348168 and no longer \add вүҲdisobey\add*, then \add @those formerly wicked people\add* will surely liveвҖ”they won'tВҰ348170 dieВҰ348176.
\v 16 None of the sinsВҰ348180 thatВҰ348182 they've committed will be called to mind against them. Those who've acted justly and rightlyВҰ348188, will certainlyВҰ348190 live.
\p
\v 17 ButВҰ348193 your peopleВҰ348195 say, вҖңThe master'sВҰ348199 way isn'tВҰ348196 fair!вҖқ butВҰ348193 it's your ways that aren'tВҰ348196 fair.
\v 18 When the righteous \add >person\add* turnsВҰ348206 away from \add вүҲdoing what's right\add* and \add вүҲbecomes disobedient\add*, then they'll dieВҰ348212 inВҰ348213 \add @theirВҰ348213 sinВҰ348213\add*.
\v 19 WhenВҰ348215 the wickedВҰ348216 \add >person\add* turnsВҰ348215 away from \add вүҲdoing evil\add* and does what's just and rightВҰ348220, they'll liveВҰ348223 because of those things.
\v 20 \add вүҲYes,\add* you people sayВҰ348225, вҖңThe master'sВҰ348229 wayВҰ348228 isn'tВҰ348226 fair!вҖқ \add butВҰ348225\add* I'llВҰ348232 judgeВҰ348232 each of you \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ348234 people\add* accordingВҰ348231 to \add вүҲyour behaviour\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The demolition of Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Explanation of Jerusalem's Fall; The News of Jerusalem's Fall; The Fall of Jerusalem; Jerusalem's Fall Explained
\p
\v 21 In \add вүҲmid-January\add* of the twelfth yearВҰ348241 of ourВҰ348245 captivity \add inВҰ348239 Babylon\add*, \add вүҲsomeone who'd escapedВҰ348249\add* from YerushalemВҰ348250 \add (Jerusalem)\add* cameВҰ348246 to me andВҰ348238 told me that the cityВҰ348253 had been captured.\x + \xo 33:21: \xt 2Ki 25:3-10; Jer 39:2-8; 52:4-14.\x*
\v 22 YahwehВҰ348257 had \add вүҲheld me inВҰ348260 a vision\add* the eveningВҰ348260 before the fugitiveВҰ348263 came, \add вүҲbutВҰ348255\add* my mouth was opened by the time he came to me atВҰ348260 dawn, \add вүҲso by thenВҰ348255, IВҰ348276 was able to speak againВҰ348277\add*.
\s1 More desolation to come
\rem /s1 The Sins of the People; The Survivors in Judah
\p
\v 23 Then YahwehВҰ348283 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ348281:
\v 24 вҖңHumanity's child, the people inhabitingВҰ348290 those ruinsВҰ348291 \add back\add* in YisraelВҰ348296 \add (IsraelВҰ348296)\add* are sayingВҰ348297, вҖҳAbrahamВҰ348301 was only one person, and he inherited the land, \add вүҲbutВҰ348302 there's lots of us\add* \add now\add*. The land has been givenВҰ348309 to us as an inheritance.вҖҷ
\p
\v 25 Therefore tell them that the masterВҰ348321 YahwehВҰ348321 says this: You eat blood, and you \add вүҲpay your respect to\add* your idolsВҰ348332, then you pour out people's blood. Should you then inherit that land?
\v 26 You \add people\add* \add вүҲrely\add* on your swordsВҰ348341 \add for protection\add*, and you've done disgusting thingsвҖ”each man defilesВҰ348349 his neighbour'sВҰ348348 wifeВҰ348347. Should you \add really\add* possessВҰ348351 that land?вҖҷ
\p
\v 27 Tell them thatВҰ348381 the masterВҰ348361 YahwehВҰ348361 saysВҰ348360 this: As I live, surely the ones in the ruinsВҰ348370 will be killed by swordsВҰ348371, and I'llВҰ348379 giveВҰ348379 those in the countrysideВҰ348377 to the \add вүҲwild animalsВҰ348378\add* as food, and those in fortresses and in cavesВҰ348383 will dieВҰ348385 of plaguesВҰ348384.
\v 28 ThenВҰ348387 I'llВҰ348387 turn the \add вүҲcountry\add* into a desolationВҰ348391 and a horror, and the prideВҰ348394 \add вүҲthat came from itsВҰ348395 power\add* will endВҰ348393, because Yisrael'sВҰ348398 mountainsВҰ348397 will be desertedВҰ348396, and there'll be no one to \add вүҲwalk\add* through them.вҖҷ
\v 29 ThenВҰ348402 they'll knowВҰ348402 thatВҰ348417 I am YahwehВҰ348406, when I make the \add вүҲcountry\add* a desolationВҰ348411 andВҰ348402 a wastelandВҰ348412 because of all the \add вүҲdisgusting things\add* they've done.
\s1 Listening but not obeying
\rem /s1 The Results of the Prophet's Message
\p
\v 30 So now humanity'sВҰ348424 childВҰ348425, yourВҰ348426 peopleВҰ348426 are out besideВҰ348429 the wallsВҰ348430 and the gates of their housesВҰ348432 talkingВҰ348427 about youВҰ348428, and they're all telling each other, вҖҳLet's go and listenВҰ348447 to the prophet's messageВҰ348449 thatВҰ348450 comesВҰ348450 from YahwehВҰ348452.вҖҷ
\v 31 SoВҰ348454 my people will come to you, as they often do, and will sit inВҰ348472 frontВҰ348460 of you and listenВҰ348462 to your words, but they won'tВҰ348467 obey them. The right words are \add вүҲonВҰ348472 their lips\add*, but their heartsВҰ348477 are goingВҰ348478 afterВҰ348475 unjustВҰ348476 profit.
\v 32 \add вүҲYes,\add* you're like a lovely song to them, a beautifulВҰ348484 sound that's played well on a stringed instrument, so they'll listenВҰ348488 to yourВҰ348491 wordsВҰ348491, butВҰ348480 none of them will obey them.
\v 33 SoВҰ348496 when all that happens, watch out, \add because itВҰ348498 will indeed\add* happen. ThenВҰ348496 they'll \add вүҲrealise\add* that a prophetВҰ348501's been amongВҰ348503 them.вҖқ
\c 34
\s1 The вҖҳshepherdsвҖҷ of Yisrael (Israel)
\rem /s1 The Shepherds of Israel; Israel's False Shepherds; Shepherds and Sheep
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ348509 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ348507:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, prophesy against Yisrael's shepherds. Prophesy and tell them that the masterВҰ348529 YahwehВҰ348529 says this to the shepherds: Yisrael's shepherds who are shepherding themselvesВҰ348538 \add вүҲwon'tВҰ348539 end well\add*. Shouldn't shepherds guard the flockВҰ348540?
\v 3 You eatВҰ348547 the \add вүҲbest sheepВҰ348552 meat\add* andВҰ348548 dress in \add вүҲwoollen clothesВҰ348551\add*. You slaughterВҰ348553 the \add вүҲfat lambs\add*. You don'tВҰ348555 shepherdВҰ348556 at all.
\v 4 You haven't \add вүҲtaken care of those\add* with diseases, nor do you heal those who are ill. You don't bandage up the ones \add вүҲwith broken limbs\add*, and you don't restore the outcasts or \add вүҲsearch for those who've gone missing\add*. Instead, you use strengthВҰ348562 and violence to rule over them.
\v 5 ThenВҰ348587 they were scattered without a shepherdВҰ348589, andВҰ348587 after they were scattered, they becameВҰ348590 food for all the \add вүҲwild animalsВҰ348594\add* in the countrysideВҰ348595.\x + \xo 34:5: \xt Num 27:17; 1Ki 22:17; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\v 6 My flock has strayed across all the mountainsВҰ348602 and onto everyВҰ348604 highВҰ348607 hill, and it's dispersed over the entireВҰ348600 surfaceВҰ348611 of the earthВҰ348612, yet no one is searchingВҰ348616 for them.
\p
\v 7 Therefore, you shepherdsВҰ348621, listenВҰ348622 to Yahweh's messageВҰ348625 \add to you\add*:
\v 8 This is the masterВҰ348633 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, my flock has become plunder and food for all the wild animalsВҰ348649 in the countrysideВҰ348650, because thereВҰ348651 wasn't any shepherd and \add вүЎbecause\add* none of my shepherds \add вүҲtried to find any of\add* my flock \add that had gotten lost\add*. \add вүҲInstead it was themselvesВҰ348662 that\add* the shepherds looked after, and they didn'tВҰ348637 shepherd my flock.
\v 9 Therefore, \add you so-called\add* вҖҳshepherdsвҖҷВҰ348671, listenВҰ348672 to Yahweh's messageВҰ348673:
\v 10 The masterВҰ348680 YahwehВҰ348680 says this: Listen, I'm againstВҰ348683 those shepherds. I'll require \add вүҲcompensation from them for\add* my flock, and then I'll dismiss them from shepherding the flock. Those shepherds won't shepherd themselvesВҰ348699 any longer \add either\add*, \add вүҲbecause\add* I'll take my flock away from theirВҰ348702 mouthsВҰ348702, so that my flock won't becomeВҰ348705 food for them any longer.
\s1 The evil shepherds
\rem /s1 God, the True Shepherd; The Good Shepherd
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSo\add* the masterВҰ348713 YahwehВҰ348713 saysВҰ348712 this: Listen, I myself will searchВҰ348718 for \add those lost from\add* my flockВҰ348721, and I \add вүЎmyself\add* will look after them,
\v 12 like a shepherdВҰ348725 searches for his sheepВҰ348732 when he's amongВҰ348730 his scattered flock. So I'll look for my flock and I'll rescueВҰ348739 them from all the placesВҰ348743 whereВҰ348744 theyВҰ348745 were scattered \add вүҲduring the darkВҰ348749 times\add*.
\v 13 I'll bring \add @my peopleВҰ348754\add* out from among the \add вүҲnations\add*. I'll gatherВҰ348755 them from \add foreign\add* landsВҰ348758 and bring them \add back\add* to theirВҰ348762 land. I'll put them in pastures onВҰ348768 Yisrael's mountainsidesВҰ348766, by the streams, and in every settlement in the land.
\v 14 I'llВҰ348776 put them in good pasturesвҖ”Yisrael's high mountainsВҰ348778 will be theirВҰ348783 grazing places. They'll lie down thereВҰ348784 in places good for grazing, in abundant pastures, and they'll grazeВҰ348790 onВҰ348778 Yisrael's hills.
\v 15 I myself will shepherdВҰ348797 my flockВҰ348798, andВҰ348799 I myself will \add вүҲgive them rest\add*. That's the masterВҰ348802 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 16 I'll searchВҰ348808 out the lost and restore the outcast. I'll bandage up those who are broken and heal those who are sickВҰ348817, butВҰ348809 I'll destroyВҰ348825 those who are fat and well. I will shepherdВҰ348826 withВҰ348827 justiceВҰ348827.
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ348829 now this is what the masterВҰ348833 YahwehВҰ348833 says, You, my flockВҰ348830, listen, I'll be a judgeВҰ348836 between one sheep and another, and between rams and billy goatsВҰ348842.
\v 18 Isn't it enoughВҰ348844 to feed onВҰ348852 the good pasture? Do you have to trampleВҰ348851 down \add вүҲany remaining grass\add*? Or drinkВҰ348856 from clearВҰ348853 watersВҰ348855, then muddyВҰ348860 the streams withВҰ348852 your feet?
\v 19 Must my flockВҰ348862 eat what you've trampledВҰ348863 andВҰ348862 drinkВҰ348868 what you've muddied with your feet?
\p
\v 20 Therefore the masterВҰ348874 YahwehВҰ348874 says this to them: Listen, I myself will judgeВҰ348880 between the fat sheep and the thin ones,
\v 21 because you \add shepherds\add* have pushed them with your sides and shouldersВҰ348891, and you've gored all the weak ones with your hornsВҰ348893 untilВҰ348898 you \add succeeded inВҰ348890\add* scatteringВҰ348900 them away from the land.
\v 22 I'll save my flockВҰ348907 and they'll no longer be \add taken as\add* plunder, and I'll judgeВҰ348913 betweenВҰ348914 one sheep and \add вүҲthe next\add*.
\v 23 I'llВҰ348918 set one shepherd over themвҖ”my servantВҰ348925 DavidВҰ348926. He'll \add вүҲlook after\add* them, andВҰ348918 he'll be their shepherd.\x + \xo 34:23: \xt Rev 7:17.\x*
\v 24 ThenВҰ348936 I, Yahweh, will be theirВҰ348944 godВҰ348940, andВҰ348941 my servantВҰ348941 DavidВҰ348942 will be a leader amongВҰ348944 them. I, Yahweh, have declared that.\x + \xo 34:24: \xt Eze 37:24.\x*
\rem /s1 The Lord's Covenant of Peace
\p
\v 25 ThenВҰ348949 I'llВҰ348953 make a peaceВҰ348952 treaty withВҰ348961 them and remove the wild animalsВҰ348954 from the land, so that they'll \add be able to\add* liveВҰ348960 securelyВҰ348962 in the wildernessВҰ348961 and sleepВҰ348963 safely in the forestsВҰ348964.
\p
\v 26 I'llВҰ348966 also \add вүҲbless\add* \add both\add* them and the places aroundВҰ348968 my hill, and sendВҰ348971 out showers inВҰ348973 the right seasonВҰ348973вҖ”they'll be showers of blessing.
\v 27 ThenВҰ348978 the trees in the countrysideВҰ348980 will produce their fruitВҰ348983, the soil will yield itsВҰ348986 produce, and my sheep will be secureВҰ348991 in their land. WhenВҰ348978 I breakВҰ348997 \add вүҲoff the ties holding the yoke\add* \add onto their necks\add*, and when I rescueВҰ349002 them from the \add вүҲcontrol\add* of thoseВҰ349004 who enslavedВҰ349004 them, thenВҰ348978 they'll knowВҰ348992 that I am YahwehВҰ348996.
\v 28 They'll no longer be plunder for the \add other\add* nationsВҰ349012, and the wild animalsВҰ349013 on the land will no longer devourВҰ349016 them. ThenВҰ349007 they'll liveВҰ349017 securelyВҰ349018, and no one will \add вүҲmake them afraid\add*.
\v 29 I'llВҰ349022 provideВҰ349022 a land for them that's known for its crops, so they won't be victims of famineВҰ349031, andВҰ349022 they won't be \add вүҲmocked by\add* \add other\add* nationsВҰ349038.
\v 30 ThenВҰ349040 they'll know that I, Yahweh theirВҰ349044 godВҰ349044, am with them. The \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ349048 people\add* are my people. That's the masterВҰ349051 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 31 You are my sheepВҰ349055, the flockВҰ349056 of my pastureВҰ349057, and my people, and I am yourВҰ349061 godВҰ349061. That's the masterВҰ349063 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 35
\s1 Edom's coming punishment
\rem /s1 A Prophecy Against Edom; God's Punishment of Edom; A Message for Edom; Judgment on Mount Seir
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ349070 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ349068:\x + \xo 35:1-15: \xt Isa 34:5-17; 63:1-6; Jer 49:7-22; Eze 25:12-14; Amos 1:11-12; Oba 1-14; Mal 1:2-5.\x*
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲlook out towards\add* MtВҰ349081. SeirВҰ349082 andВҰ349083 prophesyВҰ349083 against it.
\v 3 Tell it that the masterВҰ349090 YahwehВҰ349090 saysВҰ349089 this: Listen, I'm against you \add Edom, represented by\add* MtВҰ349094. SeirВҰ349096, and I'llВҰ349097 \add вүҲwork against you to\add* make you a desolationВҰ349101 and a wasteВҰ349102.
\v 4 I'llВҰ349106 \add вүҲturn\add* yourВҰ349104 cities into ruins, and you yourself will become desolateВҰ349108. Then you'll knowВҰ349110 that I am YahwehВҰ349114.
\p
\v 5 You'veВҰ349126 always been hostile to the IsraeliВҰ349124 peopleВҰ349124, and when they were distressed you \add вүҲdecided to attack them withВҰ349132 swordsВҰ349131\add*вҖ”atВҰ349132 the time theirВҰ349133 punishmentВҰ349135 was coming to an end.
\v 6 Therefore, this is the masterВҰ349143 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, I'llВҰ349148 prepareВҰ349148 you for bloodshed, and bloodshed will chase after you. Since you didn'tВҰ349153 hate bloodshed, bloodshed will \add вүҲcome to\add* you.
\v 7 I'llВҰ349159 make \add вүҲEdom\add* completely desolateВҰ349165 when I cut \add вүҲit off so that no one will want to pass throughВҰ349168 it\add*.
\v 8 I'llВҰ349171 fillВҰ349171 its mountainВҰ349174 \add ranges\add* withВҰ349185 people who were killedвҖ”thoseВҰ349181 killed by the swordВҰ349183 will fall onВҰ349185 your high hillsВҰ349176 and valleysВҰ349177 and inВҰ349185 all your streams.
\v 9 I'llВҰ349189 make \add вүҲyourВҰ349190 land perpetuallyВҰ349188 desolate\add*. Your citiesВҰ349190 won'tВҰ349191 be inhabited, and then you'll knowВҰ349194 that I am YahwehВҰ349198.
\p
\v 10 You've saidВҰ349201, вҖңThese two nationsВҰ349205 and these two landsВҰ349209 will become mine, and we'll possessВҰ349212 them,вҖқ even when YahwehВҰ349213 was thereВҰ349214 with them.
\v 11 Therefore, this is the masterВҰ349222 Yahweh's declaration: As I live, I'll act according to your angerВҰ349225 and according to your jealousyВҰ349226 thatВҰ349227 you had inВҰ349230 your hatredВҰ349229 of Yisrael, and I'll show myselfВҰ349231 to them when I judgeВҰ349234 youвҖ”
\v 12 thenВҰ349236 you'll knowВҰ349236 thatВҰ349248 I am YahwehВҰ349240. I'veВҰ349241 heardВҰ349241 all the insults you spoke against Yisrael's \add вүҲhill country\add*, when you saidВҰ349249, вҖңThey've been destroyedвҖ”they've been givenВҰ349259 over to us to devour.вҖқ
\v 13 You raised yourselvesВҰ349262 up against me withВҰ349264 what you said, and you multipliedВҰ349265 the wordsВҰ349267 you said against me, and I heardВҰ349269 all of them.
\p
\v 14 TheВҰ349275 masterВҰ349274 YahwehВҰ349274 saysВҰ349273 this: I'llВҰ349281 make youВҰ349283 \add вүҲinto a desolateВҰ349280 place\add* while the \add вүҲrest of the world cheers\add*.
\v 15 Just like you rejoicedВҰ349285 over the IsraeliВҰ349287 people's inheritanceВҰ349286 \add вүҲwhen it was made desolate\add*, I'llВҰ349295 do the same to you. You'll become a desolation, MtВҰ349300. SeirВҰ349302 and all of EdomВҰ349305вҖ”all of it. Then they'll knowВҰ349307 that I am YahwehВҰ349311.вҖқ
\c 36
\s1 God's blessing for Yisrael (Israel)
\rem /s1 Blessing on Israel; A Prophecy to the Mountains of Israel; Restoration for Israel; God's Blessing on Israel
\p
\v 1 вҖңNow, humanity'sВҰ349317 child, prophesyВҰ349318 to Yisrael's mountains and sayВҰ349323, вҖҳMountains of Yisrael, listenВҰ349326 to Yahweh's messageВҰ349327.
\v 2 The masterВҰ349333 YahwehВҰ349333 saysВҰ349332 this: The enemyВҰ349337 has saidВҰ349336, вҖңAha,вҖқ \add when talking\add* about youВҰ349338, andВҰ349340 вҖңThe ancient \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* have becomeВҰ349343 ours.вҖқ вҖҷ
\p
\v 3 Therefore prophesyВҰ349347 and tell them that the masterВҰ349351 YahwehВҰ349351 saysВҰ349350 this: Because of your desolationВҰ349355 and becauseВҰ349353 of the attacks that came onВҰ349354 you from all sidesВҰ349358, you've \add вүҲended up belonging to\add* other nationsВҰ349362вҖ”you've been the subject of slanderousВҰ349368 lips and tonguesВҰ349367, and of people'sВҰ349370 stories.
\v 4 Therefore, mountains of YisraelВҰ349374, listenВҰ349375 to the messageВҰ349376 from the master Yahweh: The master Yahweh says this to the mountains and the high hillsВҰ349386, to the streambeds and valleysВҰ349388, to the \add вүҲplacesВҰ349389 that have been destroyed and are now uninhabited\add*, and to the forsaken citiesВҰ349391 that have becomeВҰ349394 plunderВҰ349395 and a subject of mocking for the other nationsВҰ349398 that surround themвҖ”
\v 5 the masterВҰ349407 YahwehВҰ349407 saysВҰ349406 this: I'veВҰ349414 certainly spokenВҰ349414 in the \add вүҲheat\add* of my anger against the other nationsВҰ349418, against EdomВҰ349421 and everyoneВҰ349433 who took my land for themselves as a possessionВҰ349431вҖ”against all those who had both celebration in their heartВҰ349435 and disdain in their spirit as they seized my land so they could claim itsВҰ349439 pasturelandsВҰ349439 for themselves.вҖҷ
\p
\v 6 Therefore, prophesyВҰ349443 to YisraelВҰ349447 and tell the mountainsВҰ349449 and the high hillsВҰ349450, the streambeds and the valleysВҰ349452, that the masterВҰ349457 YahwehВҰ349457 saysВҰ349455 this: Listen, in my fury and in my angerВҰ349461 I'm declaring this becauseВҰ349463 you'veВҰ349466 endured insultsВҰ349464 from \add other\add* nationsВҰ349465.
\v 7 Therefore, the masterВҰ349471 YahwehВҰ349471 saysВҰ349470 this: I myself will \add вүҲtake action and promise\add* that the nationsВҰ349481 that surround youВҰ349483 will certainly \add be made to\add* carry theirВҰ349486 own shame.
\v 8 ButВҰ349490 you Israeli mountainsВҰ349491, you'll grow branchesВҰ349493 andВҰ349495 bear fruitВҰ349495 for my Israeli peopleВҰ349497, since they'll soon comeВҰ349501 back to you,
\v 9 because, listen, I'mВҰ349504 for you, and I'llВҰ349506 treat you favourablyвҖ”you'll be ploughed and sown \add with seed\add*.
\v 10 I'llВҰ349511 multiplyВҰ349511 \add вүҲyour populationвҖ”all the IsraeliВҰ349517 people\add*. The citiesВҰ349520 will be inhabitedВҰ349519 \add again\add* andВҰ349511 the ruinsВҰ349521 rebuiltВҰ349522.
\v 11 I'll increaseВҰ349528 \add both\add* people and animalsВҰ349527 on you \add вүЎmountains\add* so that they'll multiplyВҰ349524 and be fruitfulВҰ349529. ThenВҰ349524 I'll causeВҰ349530 you to be inhabitedВҰ349530 like you were previously, and I'll make you prosper more than you did in the past \add вүҲso that\add* you'll knowВҰ349535 that I am YahwehВҰ349539.
\v 12 I'llВҰ349541 bring my Israeli peopleВҰ349546 to walkВҰ349541 on you. They'll possessВҰ349548 you, and you'll be their inheritanceВҰ349551, and you'll no longer causeВҰ349541 their children to die.
\p
\v 13 The masterВҰ349561 YahwehВҰ349561 saysВҰ349560 this: They're telling you, вҖңYou \add вүЎmountains\add* devourВҰ349566 peopleВҰ349564, bereavingВҰ349570 your nationВҰ349571 of children,вҖқ
\v 14 therefore you won'tВҰ349577 consume people any longer, and you'll no longer make your nationВҰ349581 mourn their deaths. That's the masterВҰ349589 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 15 I won'tВҰ349592 allow you to hear the insultsВҰ349597 from the \add other\add* nationsВҰ349598 any longerвҖ”you'll no longer have to bear the peopleВҰ349600 groups shaming you, andВҰ349592 you won't causeВҰ349609 your nationВҰ349605 to stumbleВҰ349609. That's the masterВҰ349612 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Renewal of Israel; Israel's New Life
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ349619 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ349617:
\v 17 вҖңHumanity's child, when the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ349626 people\add* inhabited their land, they defiledВҰ349632 it withВҰ349634 their customs and their activities. \add вүҲIn myВҰ349640 eyes,\add* their customs were like the uncleannessВҰ349636 of a woman's menstruationВҰ349637,
\v 18 \add вүҲso\add* I poured out my fury against them for the bloodВҰ349647 thatВҰ349648 they'd poured out onВҰ349654 the land, andВҰ349642 for how they'd polluted itВҰ349655 withВҰ349654 theirВҰ349654 idolsВҰ349654.
\v 19 I scatteredВҰ349657 them among the nationsВҰ349659вҖ”theyВҰ349660 were dispersedВҰ349660 through the landsВҰ349661. I judgedВҰ349664 them according to their customs andВҰ349657 their actions.
\v 20 ThenВҰ349666 they went to those \add other\add* nationsВҰ349669, andВҰ349666 whereverВҰ349670 they went, they profanedВҰ349674 my holy nameВҰ349677 when people asked about them, вҖҳAre theseВҰ349684 really Yahweh's people? After all, they've been thrown out of his land.вҖҷ
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ349688\add* IВҰ349696 had compassion for my holy nameВҰ349691 thatВҰ349693 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ349695 people\add* had defiled amongВҰ349697 the \add other\add* nationsВҰ349697, when theyВҰ349700 went thereВҰ349701.
\p
\v 22 Therefore tell the \add вүҲIsraeli people\add* thatВҰ349725 the masterВҰ349711 YahwehВҰ349711 saysВҰ349710 this: I'm not doing this for the sake of you \add вүҲIsraeli people\add*, but for my sacredВҰ349724 nameВҰ349722, whichВҰ349725 you've profanedВҰ349726 amongВҰ349727 the nationsВҰ349727 everywhere you've gone.
\v 23 My greatВҰ349737 nameВҰ349736, whichВҰ349740 you \add people\add* have profaned among the nations, I'llВҰ349733 make holy \add even\add* among the nations \add where\add* you profaned it. ThenВҰ349733 the nations will know thatВҰ349740 I am Yahweh, when they see you recognise my holinessВҰ349733. That's the masterВҰ349750 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 24 I'll takeВҰ349756 you \add back\add* out of those nationsВҰ349760 and gatherВҰ349761 you from every land, and I'll bringВҰ349766 you into your land.
\v 25 ThenВҰ349772 I'll sprinkleВҰ349772 pure waterВҰ349774 on you so you'll be cleanedВҰ349776 from all of your impuritiesВҰ349778, andВҰ349772 I'll purifyВҰ349782 you from all your idolsВҰ349781.
\v 26 I'll give you \add people\add* a new heart and a new spiritВҰ349789 inВҰ349792 your innermostВҰ349792 partsВҰ349792, and I'll take the stony heart away from your \add вүҲbodies\add* and \add вүҲreplace it withВҰ349792\add* a heart of flesh.\x + \xo 36:26-28: \xt Eze 11:19-20.\x*
\v 27 I'llВҰ349807 put my spirit inВҰ349808 you and enable you \add IsraelisВҰ349809\add* to \add вүҲfollow my instructions and keepВҰ349816 my regulationsВҰ349813\add*.
\v 28 ThenВҰ349819 you'll inhabit the land thatВҰ349821 I gaveВҰ349822 to your ancestorsВҰ349823вҖ”you'll be my peopleВҰ349826 andВҰ349819 I'llВҰ349828 be your godВҰ349830.
\v 29 I'll saveВҰ349832 you from all of your uncleannessВҰ349835, and thenВҰ349832 I'll summonВҰ349836 the grainВҰ349839 and multiply itвҖ”I'll no longer \add вүҲassign\add* famineВҰ349846 to you.
\v 30 I'llВҰ349848 multiply the \add #fruit onВҰ349862 the trees\add* andВҰ349853 the produceВҰ349853 \add вүҲfrom the soil\add* so that you'll no longer \add вүҲbe shamed by other nationsВҰ349862 seeing you suffering\add* famineВҰ349861.
\v 31 ThenВҰ349864 you'll think about your wicked customsВҰ349867 and your activities thatВҰ349870 weren't goodВҰ349873, and \add вүҲyour facesВҰ349875 will display your loathingВҰ349874 of your own sins and your disgusting habits\add*.
\v 32 ButВҰ349892 make sure you know this: I'm not doing all that for \em your\em* sake, \add вүҲso you IsraeliВҰ349894 people\add* shouldВҰ349889 be ashamedВҰ349891 andВҰ349892 disgraced because of your \add вүҲbehaviour\add*. That's the masterВҰ349887 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 33 The masterВҰ349900 YahwehВҰ349900 saysВҰ349899 this: \add вүҲWhen\add* I purify you from all your disobedience, I'llВҰ349907 enable you to inhabitВҰ349907 the citiesВҰ349910 \add again\add* and to rebuildВҰ349911 the ruined placesВҰ349912,
\v 34 andВҰ349914 the idle land will be tilledВҰ349916 until it's no longer a wasteland for everyoneВҰ349922 to see as they go past.
\v 35 ThenВҰ349926 \add instead\add* they'll say, вҖңThis land was desolateВҰ349935, butВҰ349926 it's becomeВҰ349930 like the gardenВҰ349931 of EdenВҰ349933вҖ”the abandoned cities and the uninhabited ruins that were torn down are now fortifiedВҰ349938 and inhabited.вҖқ
\v 36 ThenВҰ349941 the other nationsВҰ349942 aroundВҰ349945 youВҰ349945 will knowВҰ349941 thatВҰ349943 I am Yahweh, because I built up the ruins and replanted the abandoned placesВҰ349953. I, Yahweh, have declared it and I will do it.
\p
\v 37 The masterВҰ349962 YahwehВҰ349962 \add also\add* saysВҰ349961 this: The \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ349969 people\add* will againВҰ349964 ask me to do this for them: to increaseВҰ349972 \add вүҲtheir population like sheep\add*.
\v 38 Just like the flock \add вүҲthat's kept separate to be used\add* for sacrifices (like the flock inВҰ349981 YerushalemВҰ349980 atВҰ349981 itsВҰ349981 scheduled feastsВҰ349981), so too the ruinedВҰ349985 citiesВҰ349984 will be filled withВҰ349981 flocks of people andВҰ349989 theyВҰ349983 will knowВҰ349989 that I am YahwehВҰ349993.вҖқ
\c 37
\s1 The valley with bleached bones
\rem /s1 A Valley of Dry Bones; The Valley of Dry Bones
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOneВҰ350003 day YahwehВҰ350000 gave me another vision\add*, and he took me out by his spiritВҰ350002 and put me down inВҰ350002 the middleВҰ350005 of a valleyВҰ350006 that was full of bonesВҰ350009.
\v 2 ThenВҰ350011 he led me all around them, and wow, there were so many bonesВҰ350017 in the valleyВҰ350022, and they were totally dried out!
\v 3 вҖңHumanity's child,вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңcan theseВҰ350034 bonesВҰ350033 become living \add people\add* again?вҖқ
\p вҖңMy masterВҰ350036 YahwehВҰ350036,вҖқ I \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add вүҲonly you would knowВҰ350039 that\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ350041 he told me, вҖңProphesy over theseВҰ350047 bones andВҰ350041 tell them, вҖҳDry bones. Listen to Yahweh's messageВҰ350053.
\v 5 The masterВҰ350059 YahwehВҰ350059 saysВҰ350058 this to theseВҰ350062 bonesВҰ350061: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ350065 to put breathВҰ350067 into you, andВҰ350068 you'll liveВҰ350068.
\v 6 I'll \add вүҲconnect\add* sinews to you and put fleshВҰ350075 onto you. I'll coverВҰ350076 you withВҰ350080 skin and put breathВҰ350081 into you so you'll liveВҰ350082. ThenВҰ350070 you'll knowВҰ350083 that I am YahwehВҰ350087.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 7 SoВҰ350089 I prophesiedВҰ350089 as I was instructedВҰ350091, andВҰ350089 wow, a soundВҰ350094 like something rattlingВҰ350098 started as the bonesВҰ350100 moved togetherВҰ350099вҖ”bone against bone!
\v 8 I lookedВҰ350106 and, wow, the bones now had sinews onВҰ350119 them, and fleshВҰ350111 grew up \add over that\add*, and thenВҰ350106 skin coveredВҰ350113 them! \add вүҲButВҰ350106\add* thereВҰ350118 was still no breath inВҰ350119 them.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ350121 Yahweh told me, вҖңProphesy to the wind. Humanity's child, prophesy and tell the air, вҖҳThe masterВҰ350140 Yahweh \add вүҲcommands\add* this: Breath, come from the four \add вүҲcompass points\add*, and breatheВҰ350146 into theseВҰ350148 who've been killedВҰ350147, so they'll \add вүҲcome to life\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ350151\add* I prophesiedВҰ350151 just like I was commandedВҰ350153. Then breathВҰ350156 came into them andВҰ350151 they \add вүҲcame to lifeВҰ350157\add*. Then they stoodВҰ350158 on theirВҰ350161 feetВҰ350161вҖ”a very large army.
\p
\v 11 Then Yahweh \add вүҲinformed\add* me, вҖңHumanity's child, theseВҰ350175 bones are the entireВҰ350176 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ350178 population\add*. Listen, they're sayingВҰ350182, вҖҳOur bones have driedВҰ350183 up and our hope is gone. We've been cut off.вҖҷ
\v 12 Therefore prophesyВҰ350191 and tell them, вҖҳThe masterВҰ350197 YahwehВҰ350197 says this: Listen, I'll open your graves and lift you, my peopleВҰ350208, out from them, then I'll bring you back to YisraelВҰ350214.
\v 13 Then, my peopleВҰ350229, when I open your graves and bringВҰ350226 you out of them, you'll knowВҰ350217 that I am YahwehВҰ350221.
\v 14 I'll placeВҰ350235 my spirit within you so you'll liveВҰ350234, and I'll cause you to rest inВҰ350233 your land when you knowВҰ350240 that I am Yahweh. I declare it, and I will do it. That is Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 The two sticks indicating unity of Yisrael and Yehudah
\rem /s1 One Nation Under One King; The Two Sticks; Reunion of Israel and Judah; Judah and Israel in One Kingdom
\p
\v 15 Then YahwehВҰ350255 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ350253:
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ350259 now\add*, humanity'sВҰ350262 child, take a stick for yourselfВҰ350265 and write on it, вҖҳFor YehudahВҰ350270 and for all their associated people.вҖҷ ThenВҰ350259 take another stick and write on it, вҖҳFor \add YisraelВҰ350272\add* (\add represented by\add* YosefВҰ350280 \add (Joseph)\add*, the branch of EfrayimВҰ350282), and for all their associated people.вҖҷ
\v 17 ThenВҰ350290 hold both of them together so that theyВҰ350299 \add вүҲseem like\add* one stickВҰ350297 inВҰ350301 yourВҰ350301 handВҰ350301.
\v 18 WhenВҰ350303 your peopleВҰ350307 \add вүҲask you andВҰ350303 insist\add*, вҖҳAren't you going to tell us what theseВҰ350315 props of yours mean?вҖҷ
\v 19 then tell them, вҖҳThe masterВҰ350323 YahwehВҰ350323 says this: Look, I'm taking Yosef's branch that's in Efrayim'sВҰ350335 hand along withВҰ350333 the tribesВҰ350336 of YisraelВҰ350337 hisВҰ350338 companionsВҰ350338, and joining it to YehudahВҰ350346's branch, so that they'll make one branch, and they'll become one in my hand.вҖҷ
\p
\v 20 Hold the branches inВҰ350360 yourВҰ350360 handВҰ350360 thatВҰ350356 youВҰ350358 wrote onВҰ350360 \add вүҲwhile theyВҰ350354 watched\add*.
\v 21 Tell \add @the people\add*, вҖҳThe masterВҰ350368 YahwehВҰ350368 says this: Look, I'm aboutВҰ350372 to take the IsraeliВҰ350375 people out from the nationsВҰ350378 whereВҰ350379 they went. I'llВҰ350383 gatherВҰ350383 them from the surrounding lands andВҰ350363 bringВҰ350386 them \add back\add* to theirВҰ350390 land.
\v 22 I'llВҰ350392 \add вүҲunite them as a single\add* nation inВҰ350397 the land, onВҰ350397 the mountainsВҰ350397 of YisraelВҰ350398, and there'll be one king as king over all of them, and they'll no longer be two nationsвҖ”they'll no longer be dividedВҰ350412 into two kingdomsВҰ350415.
\v 23 ThenВҰ350418 they'll no longer defile themselvesВҰ350419 with their idolsВҰ350421, with their disgusting thingsВҰ350422, or with any of their other sins. I'll saveВҰ350425 them from all of their faithless actions\f + \fr 37:23 \ft The Hebrew text has вҖҳliving placesвҖҷ rather than вҖҳfaithless actionsвҖҷ (from the Septuagint), but it's difficult to make sense of the Hebrew.\f* with whichВҰ350429 they've sinnedВҰ350430, and I'll purify them so they'll be my peopleВҰ350437 and I'll be their godВҰ350441.
\v 24 My servantВҰ350443 DavidВҰ350444 will be kingВҰ350445 over them, \add вүҲso\add* there'll be one shepherdВҰ350447 over them all, and they'll \add вүҲfollow\add* my instructions and keepВҰ350454 my regulationsВҰ350453 and obey them.\x + \xo 37:24: \xt Eze 34:24.\x*
\v 25 They'll live in the land thatВҰ350462 I've given to my servant Yakov \add (Jacob, also called Yisrael/Israel)\add*, where your ancestorsВҰ350470 had stayed. They'll live in it foreverВҰ350484вҖ”they, their childrenВҰ350474, and their grandchildren, and my servant DavidВҰ350480 will be their \add вүҲpermanent\add* leader.
\v 26 I'll establish a peaceВҰ350489 treaty with themвҖ”a never-ending agreement with them. I'll establish them and multiplyВҰ350495 them and put my sacred place amongВҰ350501 them foreverВҰ350502.
\v 27 My residence will be with themвҖ”I'llВҰ350507 be their godВҰ350509, andВҰ350504 they'll be my peopleВҰ350514.\x + \xo 37:27: \xt 2Cor 6:16; Rev 21:3.\x*
\v 28 ThenВҰ350516 the \add other\add* nationsВҰ350517 will knowВҰ350516 that IВҰ350519 am YahwehВҰ350520 who sets YisraelВҰ350524 apart, when my sacred place is \add вүҲpermanently\add* amongВҰ350527 them.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 38
\ms1 The defeat of all of Yisrael's opponents
\mr (38:1вҖ“39:29)
\s1 Invasion by Gog and his army
\rem /s1 Gog as the Instrument of God; A Message for Gog; A Prophecy Against Gog; Invasion by Gog
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ350534 \add вүҲgave\add* me \add another\add* messageВҰ350532:
\v 2 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲlook\add* toward the land of MagogВҰ350547 \add ?where King\add* GogВҰ350545 is the main leader of MeshekВҰ350550 and Tuval, and prophesyВҰ350552 againstВҰ350543 him.\x + \xo 38:2: \xt Rev 20:8.\x*
\v 3 Tell him that the masterВҰ350558 YahwehВҰ350558 saysВҰ350557 this: Listen, I'm againstВҰ350561 youВҰ350561, GogВҰ350562, leader of MeshekВҰ350565 andВҰ350566 Tuval,
\v 4 \add вүҲso\add* I'll turnВҰ350568 you aroundВҰ350568 and put hooksВҰ350570 into your jaws. ThenВҰ350568 I'll bringВҰ350572 you out with all your army, horsesВҰ350580, and horsemen, all of them dressed inВҰ350571 full armourвҖ”a hugeВҰ350586 group with large and small shields, all of them holding swordsВҰ350590.
\v 5 Persia, \add Ethiopia\add* (Kush), and Libya are with them, all of them with shieldsВҰ350598 and helmetsВҰ350599,
\v 6 \add as well as\add* GomerВҰ350601 and all its troops, and Beyt-TogarmahВҰ350606, from the far partsВҰ350607 of the northВҰ350608, and all its troops. Many peopleВҰ350614 groups are with you.
\v 7 \add Tell Gog to\add* \add вүҲget ready as commander, and to assembleВҰ350624 and prepareВҰ350618 his troops\add*.
\v 8 You'll be \add вүҲsummoned many daysВҰ350631 later\add*, then after some yearsВҰ350635 you'll goВҰ350636 to a land that's recovered from war and \add вүҲwhere the people have come back from many nations\add*вҖ”gatheredВҰ350644 back to Yisrael's mountainsВҰ350648 that had continuouslyВҰ350654 been a ruin. ButВҰ350655 the land's people will \add indeed\add* be broughtВҰ350657 out of the nations, and they'll all live \add there\add* safely \add again\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ350662 you'll goВҰ350664 \add вүҲin like a stormВҰ350663 with yourВҰ350672 large army\add*вҖ”you'll all be like a cloudВҰ350665 coveringВҰ350666 the land.
\p
\v 10 TheВҰ350681 masterВҰ350680 YahwehВҰ350680 saysВҰ350679 this: \add ButВҰ350682\add* plans will \add start to\add* form in yourВҰ350690 heartВҰ350690 on that dayВҰ350684 and you'll deviseВҰ350691 wicked schemes.
\v 11 ThenВҰ350695 you'll \add вүҲthink\add*, вҖҳI'llВҰ350696 \add take my army\add* up onto the open groundвҖ”\add вүҲwe'll attack\add* the people living quietly \add вүҲand peacefullyВҰ350702\add*вҖ”all of them living where thereВҰ350711 are no walls or barriers, and no city gatesВҰ350710.
\v 12 I'll capture booty and steal plunder \add вүҲand use my forces\add* against those ruins thatВҰ350727 have been newly inhabitedВҰ350723, and against those people who've returned from the nationsВҰ350728вҖ”people who are gaining livestockВҰ350730 and propertyВҰ350731, and who are living at the centreВҰ350735 of the world.вҖҷ
\v 13 \add People from\add* Sheva and DedanВҰ350739, and tradersВҰ350740 from TarshishВҰ350741 and itsВҰ350744 villagesВҰ350744 will \add вүҲask\add* you, вҖҳHave you come to plunder? Have you assembledВҰ350753 your armies to take away spoilВҰ350752, to carryВҰ350755 off goldВҰ350758 and silverВҰ350757, to take their livestockВҰ350760 and propertyВҰ350761 and to haul away plenty of plunder?вҖҷ
\p
\v 14 Therefore, humanity'sВҰ350771 child, prophesyВҰ350768 andВҰ350772 tell GogВҰ350773 that the masterВҰ350776 YahwehВҰ350776 saysВҰ350775 this: On that dayВҰ350780, when my peopleВҰ350783 YisraelВҰ350784 are livingВҰ350782 securelyВҰ350785\add вүҲвҖ”butВҰ350772 youВҰ350786 won'tВҰ350778 take notice of thatвҖ”\add*
\v 15 you'll comeВҰ350788 from yourВҰ350789 placeВҰ350789 far away in the northВҰ350791 with a large armyвҖ”all of them riding on horsesВҰ350797, \add yes,\add* \add вүҲa very numerous force\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ350804 you'll attack my \add вүҲIsraeli peopleВҰ350807\add* like a cloudВҰ350809 that coversВҰ350810 the land. I'llВҰ350815 send you against my land \add вүҲnear the end of the era\add*, so that the nationsВҰ350821 might knowВҰ350820 me when I show myselfВҰ350823 through you, GogВҰ350826вҖ”\add вүҲthey'll see withВҰ350823 theirВҰ350825 own eyesВҰ350825 that I always demand what's right\add*.
\rem /s1 Judgment on Gog
\v 17 The masterВҰ350832 YahwehВҰ350832 saysВҰ350831 this: Aren't you the one that I spokeВҰ350839 about in the past \add вүҲthrough\add* my servantsВҰ350843, the IsraeliВҰ350844 prophets who prophesied for yearsВҰ350849 in their own times, that I would bringВҰ350850 you againstВҰ350852 them?
\s1 Yahweh's punishment of Gog
\rem /s1 God's Punishment of Gog
\p
\v 18 This is the masterВҰ350867 Yahweh's declaration: When GogВҰ350861 attacks YisraelВҰ350865, my fury will mount up \add вүҲinto a rageВҰ350870\add*.
\v 19 In my zeal andВҰ350873 in the fireВҰ350874 of my angerВҰ350876, I declare that onВҰ350873 that dayВҰ350882 there'll be a terrible earthquakeВҰ350885 in YisraelВҰ350889,
\v 20 and the fish in the seaВҰ350894 and the birds in the skiesВҰ350896, the wild animalsВҰ350897 in the countrysideВҰ350898 includingВҰ350895 all the creatures thatВҰ350908 crawl on the earth, and every person who's on the surfaceВҰ350911 of the land will trembleВҰ350891 in front of me. The mountainsВҰ350914 will be thrownВҰ350913 down and the cliffsВҰ350916 will fall, until every wall falls to the groundВҰ350920.
\v 21 I'llВҰ350923 summonВҰ350923 \add вүҲan army\add* against \add @Gog\add* onВҰ350934 all my mountainsВҰ350927. Every man's sword will be against his brotherВҰ350934. That's the masterВҰ350930 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 22 ThenВҰ350937 I'll \add вүҲpunish\add* \add @Gog\add* with plaguesВҰ350939 and bloodshedВҰ350940, as well as overwhelming rain and hailstones and burningВҰ350945 sulfurВҰ350946 that I'll rain down onВҰ350939 him and his troopsВҰ350951 and the many nations that \add вүҲjoined\add* with him.
\v 23 \add Yes,\add* I'll displayВҰ350959 my greatnessВҰ350959 and \add вүҲpurityВҰ350960\add*, and I'll make myself knownВҰ350961 to \add &those\add* many nationsВҰ350963, \add вүҲso\add* they'll knowВҰ350965 that I am YahwehВҰ350969.
\c 39
\s1 The defeat of Gog
\rem /s1 The Defeat of Gog; The Slaughter of Gog's Armies; Gog's Armies Destroyed
\p
\v 1 вҖңNow, humanity'sВҰ350975 child, prophesyВҰ350976 against Gog and sayВҰ350980 that the masterВҰ350983 YahwehВҰ350983 saysВҰ350982 this: Listen, I'm against youВҰ350986, Gog, leader of MeshekВҰ350990 and Tuval.
\v 2 I'll turn you aroundВҰ350993 and drag you alongВҰ350994вҖ”I'll bring you from the far northВҰ350997 and take you up to Yisrael's mountainsВҰ351001,
\v 3 ThenВҰ351004 I'llВҰ351011 knock your bow out of your left hand andВҰ351004 make the arrowsВҰ351008 fall out of your rightВҰ351010 hand.
\v 4 You and all your troopsВҰ351021 and soldiers who are with you will \add вүҲdie\add* on Yisrael's mountainsВҰ351015. I'llВҰ351032 giveВҰ351032 you to the birdsВҰ351025 of prey and the wild animalsВҰ351030 in the countrysideВҰ351031 for food.
\v 5 You'll die \add вүҲthere\add* in the countrysideВҰ351038, because I myself declare it. That's the masterВҰ351044 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 6 ThenВҰ351047 I'llВҰ351047 sendВҰ351047 fireВҰ351049 out onto MagogВҰ351050 and onВҰ351050 thoseВҰ351051 living in safetyВҰ351053 in the \add вүҲcoastalВҰ351052 regions\add*, and thenВҰ351047 they'll knowВҰ351054 that I am YahwehВҰ351058.
\v 7 I'll make my holy name knownВҰ351064 among my peopleВҰ351066 Yisrael, andВҰ351060 I'll no longer allow my holy name to be profanedВҰ351070вҖ”the nationsВҰ351078 will know that I am YahwehВҰ351082, the holy One inВҰ351084 Yisrael.
\p
\v 8 Listen, the dayВҰ351093 is comingВҰ351087, andВҰ351088 \add @all thatВҰ351094\add* will take place. That's the masterВҰ351090 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 9 The people living inВҰ351104 Yisrael's citiesВҰ351100 will goВҰ351097 out and they'll use \add those\add* weaponsВҰ351104 to kindle and make fires and burn themвҖ”small shields, large shields, bows, arrowsВҰ351108, the clubsВҰ351109 and spearsВҰ351111вҖ”they'll make fires withВҰ351104 them for sevenВҰ351115 yearsВҰ351116.
\v 10 They won'tВҰ351118 \add need to\add* gather firewood from the countrysideВҰ351124 or cut down trees from the forestsВҰ351129, since they'll burn the weaponsВҰ351131. They'll take from those \add invaders\add* who wanted to take from them, andВҰ351118 plunder those who wanted to plunder them. That's the masterВҰ351144 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\s1 Gog's burial
\rem /s1 The Burial of Gog
\p
\v 11 Then \add вүҲatВҰ351149 that time\add*, I'llВҰ351151 make a grave for Gog there inВҰ351149 YisraelВҰ351158вҖ”a valley for those who journey to the east of the seaВҰ351162. They'll buryВҰ351168 Gog there withВҰ351149 all his multitudesВҰ351177, and they'll call it the вҖҳHamon-GogвҖҷ \add (or, вҖҳGog'sВҰ351152 hordeВҰ351177вҖҷ)\add* valley. \add @That mass grave\add* will blockВҰ351163 peopleВҰ351168 who want to cross over.
\v 12 It'llВҰ351186 take sevenВҰ351192 monthsВҰ351193 for the IsraelisВҰ351185 to buryВҰ351184 them to make the area cleanВҰ351188вҖ”
\v 13 all the land's peopleВҰ351198 will buryВҰ351195 them. It'll be a memorable dayВҰ351203 for them when I'm \add вүҲhonouredВҰ351202\add*. That's the masterВҰ351206 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 14 At the endВҰ351226 of the sevenВҰ351227 monthsВҰ351229, they'll designate menВҰ351209 to continuallyВҰ351210 go through the \add вүҲregion\add* to find peopleВҰ351209 who were travelling through, butВҰ351209 who died andВҰ351209 their bodies remainedВҰ351220 \add вүҲabove the ground\add*, so that they can buryВҰ351214 them to make the land cleanВҰ351225.
\v 15 As those men passВҰ351232 through the land, when they seeВҰ351235 any humanВҰ351237 bone, they'll put a markerВҰ351240 by it, untilВҰ351241 gravediggers come andВҰ351232 buryВҰ351244 it in the Hamon-GogВҰ351248 valley.
\v 16 There'll even be a cityВҰ351254 there named вҖҳHamonahВҰ351255вҖҷ \add (which means, вҖҳhordeвҖҷ or вҖҳmultitudeвҖҷ)\add*. In that way, they'll make the land cleanВҰ351256 \add again\add*.
\p
\v 17 Now, humanity's child, the masterВҰ351268 YahwehВҰ351268 says this to you: Tell all the winged birdsВҰ351271 and all the wild animalsВҰ351277 in the countrysideВҰ351278, вҖҳGather together and comeВҰ351280. Gather from all aroundВҰ351282 to the sacrifice that I myself am making for youвҖ”a large sacrifice on Yisrael's mountainsВҰ351293, so that you can eat \add human\add* fleshВҰ351296 and drinkВҰ351297 bloodВҰ351298.\x + \xo 39:17-20: \xt Rev 19:17-18.\x*
\v 18 You'll eatВҰ351302 warriorsВҰ351301' fleshВҰ351300 and drinkВҰ351307 the bloodВҰ351303 of the \add вүҲworld's leaders\add* as if they were rams, lambsВҰ351309, goatsВҰ351310, and bullsВҰ351311 that were all fattened in BashanВҰ351313.
\v 19 ThenВҰ351316 you'll eatВҰ351316 fat until \add you're\add* full \add and\add* drinkВҰ351320 bloodВҰ351321 until \add you're\add* drunkВҰ351322вҖ”that'll be the sacrificeВҰ351323 that I'llВҰ351326 slaughter for you \add birds and animals\add*.
\v 20 You'll be satisfiedВҰ351329 at my tableВҰ351332 with \add #horses, chariotВҰ351334 drivers, warriorsВҰ351335,\add* andВҰ351329 every manВҰ351338 of war. That's the masterВҰ351341 Yahweh's declaration.вҖҷ
\s1 Yisrael's restoration
\rem /s1 Israel Restored to the Land; The Restoration of Israel
\p
\v 21 I'll \add вүҲdisplayВҰ351344 my power\add* amongВҰ351348 the nations, and all the nations will see \add вүҲmy judgementВҰ351355 that I'll put into process\add* and \add вүҲhow I'll put that into action\add* against them.
\v 22 ThenВҰ351366 from that \add вүҲtime\add* onwardsВҰ351377, the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ351368 people\add* will knowВҰ351366 that IВҰ351370 am theirВҰ351372 godВҰ351372 YahwehВҰ351371.
\v 23 The nationsВҰ351380 will knowВҰ351379 that the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ351386 people\add* wentВҰ351383 into captivity because of how they betrayed me withВҰ351382 their \add вүҲdisobedience\add*, so I \add вүҲdistanced myself\add* from them andВҰ351379 \add вүҲhanded them over to\add* their adversariesВҰ351397 so that they all \add вүҲdied inВҰ351382 the battle\add*.
\v 24 When I \add вүҲdistanced myself\add* from them, I \add вүҲtreated them exactly as their defilement and rebellion deserved\add*.
\rem /s1 Restoration for God's People
\p
\v 25 Therefore the masterВҰ351414 YahwehВҰ351414 saysВҰ351413 this: Now I'll restore Yakov's fortunes, and I'll have compassionВҰ351423 on all of Yisrael'sВҰ351427 \add вүҲdescendants\add*, when I act with zeal \add вүҲto protect my pureВҰ351430 reputation\add*.
\v 26 ThenВҰ351432 they'll bear their shame andВҰ351432 all the treason in whichВҰ351441 they betrayed me. They'll forgetВҰ351432 all thatВҰ351441 when they rest in their land in safetyВҰ351449, withВҰ351444 no one to terrifyВҰ351451 them
\v 27 \add when\add* I restore them from the peopleВҰ351457 groups and gatherВҰ351458 them from theirВҰ351461 enemies'ВҰ351461 landsВҰ351460, and I show myselfВҰ351462 inВҰ351463 the sightВҰ351464 of many nationsВҰ351465 \add вүҲto always do what's right\add*.
\v 28 ThenВҰ351468 they'll know that I am YahwehВҰ351471 their godВҰ351472, becauseВҰ351473 I sent them into captivity among the \add other\add* nations, butВҰ351468 thenВҰ351468 I'llВҰ351484 gatherВҰ351478 them back to their \add own\add* land. I won'tВҰ351482 leaveВҰ351484 any of them among the nations.
\v 29 I'llВҰ351491 no longer \add вүҲdistance myself\add* from them when I pour out my spirit on the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ351502 people\add*. That's the masterВҰ351505 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 40
\ms1 The revelation concerning the coming temple and nation
\mr (40:1вҖ“48:35)
\s1 Yehezkel is taken to Yerushalem
\rem /s1 Ezekiel Is Taken to Jerusalem; The Vision of the New Temple; The new temple; The New Temple Area
\p
\v 1 In \add вүҲmid-April\add* of the twenty-fifth year of our captivity (the fourteenth year afterВҰ351520 \add @Yerushalem\add* was captured), YahwehВҰ351532 \add вүҲused his power to take\add* me thereВҰ351535,
\v 2 \add yes,\add* GodВҰ351538 took me to YisraelВҰ351543 in visionsВҰ351537. He put me on a very highВҰ351548 mountainВҰ351547 \add where\add* there seemed to be cityВҰ351553 buildings towards the southВҰ351554,\x + \xo 40:2: \xt Rev 21:10.\x*
\v 3 and he took me there. ThenВҰ351556 wow, there was a manВҰ351561 standingВҰ351572 inВҰ351573 the city gatewayВҰ351573 who \add вүҲlooked like\add* bronzeВҰ351564! \add вүҲHe was holding\add* a linenВҰ351567 cord and a measuringВҰ351570 rod.\x + \xo 40:3: \xt Rev 11:1; 21:15.\x*
\p
\v 4 The manВҰ351577 told me, вҖңHumanity's child, look with your eyesВҰ351582 and listenВҰ351584 with your earsВҰ351583, and fix your mindВҰ351586 onВҰ351582 everything that I'm revealing to you, because you were broughtВҰ351596 here so I could reveal them to you. Report everything you see \add here\add* to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ351607 people\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The eastern gateway
\rem /s1 The East Gateway; The East Gate to the Outer Court; The East Gate
\p
\v 5 There was a wall surrounding the temple area. The measuring rod inВҰ351617 the man's handВҰ351617 was \add вүҲjust over three metresВҰ351623 long\add*. (It was sixВҰ351621 long cubitsвҖ”each long cubit was a cubit long plusВҰ351617 a handbreadthВҰ351625.) \add вүҲSoВҰ351610\add* he measured the wall, and it was one measuring rod thick and one high.\x + \xo 40:5вҖ“42:20: \xt 1Ki 6:1-38; 2Ch 3:1-9.\x*
\v 6 ThenВҰ351637 he went to the temple gate thatВҰ351641 faced east. He went up its stepsВҰ351646 andВҰ351637 measuredВҰ351648 the gate's thresholdвҖ”one rod across.
\v 7 The guard chambersВҰ351672 were each one rod \add вүҲlong and deep, and just under three metresВҰ351674 wide\add*. The temple gate thresholdВҰ351675 by the temple porchВҰ351678 was one rod across.
\v 8 He measuredВҰ351684 the porchВҰ351687 insideВҰ351689 the gateВҰ351688 andВҰ351684 it was one rod long,
\v 9 andВҰ351693 the porch over the gate was one rod deep. The doorposts were \add each\add* a metre wide. (This was the porch at the gate facing the temple.)
\v 10 There were three guard chambersВҰ351708 on either side of the east gateВҰ351709, and each of them \add вүҲwas the same size\add*, and the walls that separated them \add вүҲwere the same size\add*.
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ351725 the man measuredВҰ351725 the width of the gateway entrance \add вүҲand it was five metres\add*, and the lengthВҰ351734 of the gateway entrance \add вүҲwas almost seven metres\add*.
\v 12 He measured the wall that \add вүҲran along\add* the frontВҰ351741 of the chambers at half a metre high. The chambers measured three metresВҰ351753 on each side.
\v 13 ThenВҰ351759 he measuredВҰ351759 the gateway from the roof of one chamber to that of the next chamber, \add вүҲandВҰ351759 it was thirteen metresВҰ351769\add* from the entrance of the first chamber to that of the second.
\v 14 ThenВҰ351774 he measured the wall that went between the guard chambers, \add вүҲandВҰ351774 it was over thirty metres long\add* as far as the gate's porch.
\v 15 The entranceВҰ351792 from the frontВҰ351796 of the gate to the other end of the gate's porchВҰ351797 was twenty-seven metres.
\v 16 There were closedВҰ351804 windows facing the chambersВҰ351807 and toward theirВҰ351809 pillarsВҰ351824 within the gates all around, and likewise for the porchesВҰ351816. There were windows all around the inside, and each of the door jambs was decorated with \add carvings of\add* palm treesВҰ351825.
\s1 The temple courtyard
\rem /s1 The Outer Courtyard; The Outer Court
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ351827 the man broughtВҰ351827 me to the outerВҰ351831 courtyard of the temple. Look, there were rooms, andВҰ351827 the courtyard \add вүҲwas paved\add*, with thirtyВҰ351840 rooms next to the pavement.
\v 18 The pavement \add вүҲreached\add* to the side of the gates, andВҰ351846 its width was the same as the gates' lengthВҰ351852. That was the lowerВҰ351855 pavement.
\v 19 ThenВҰ351857 the man measuredВҰ351857 the distance from the front of the lowerВҰ351861 gate to the front of the innerВҰ351864 gate: it was \add вүҲjust over fifty metres\add* on the easternВҰ351868 side, andВҰ351869 the same on the northernВҰ351869 side.
\s1 The northern gateway
\rem /s1 The North Gateway; The North Gate
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ351871 he measuredВҰ351878 the lengthВҰ351879 andВҰ351871 widthВҰ351880 of the gateВҰ351871 thatВҰ351872 was at the northernВҰ351875 \add end\add* of the outerВҰ351877 courtyardВҰ351876.
\v 21 There were three chambersВҰ351882 onВҰ351902 each side of that gate, and the gate withВҰ351902 its porchВҰ351890 measuredВҰ351893 the same as the main gate: \add вүҲtwenty-seven metres long and thirteen metres wide\add*.
\v 22 Its windowsВҰ351904, porch, chambers, and its palm treesВҰ351908 matched the easternВҰ351915 gateВҰ351911. Seven stepsВҰ351916 went up to it and to its porch.
\v 23 There was a gate to the innerВҰ351927 courtyardВҰ351926 in front of the northernВҰ351930 gate, just as there was at the easternВҰ351931 gate. The man measuredВҰ351932 from one gate to the other gate, \add вүҲandВҰ351925 it was fifty-four metres\add*.
\s1 The southern gateway
\rem /s1 The South Gate; The South Gateway
\p
\v 24 Next the man took me to the gateway at the southern entrance, and its walls and porchВҰ351951 measuredВҰ351948 the same as the other outer gates.
\v 25 There were closed windows in the gateway and its porch just \add вүҲlike the other gates\add*. The southern gate with its porch \add вүҲwas twenty-seven metres long and thirteen metres wideВҰ351968\add*.
\v 26 There were sevenВҰ351974 stepsВҰ351973 up to the gate and itsВҰ351975 porchВҰ351977, and \add carvings of\add* palm treesВҰ351980 on the walls on each side.
\v 27 There was a gate to the innerВҰ351993 courtyardВҰ351992 on the southern side, andВҰ351996 the man measuredВҰ351996 fifty-four metresВҰ352004 from that gate to the gate at the southern entrance.
\s1 The gateways to the inner courtyard
\rem /s1 Gates to the Inner Court; Gateways to the Inner Courtyard; The Inner Courtyard: The South Gate
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ352006 the man broughtВҰ352006 me to the innerВҰ352010 courtyardВҰ352009 by way of its southern gate, which had the same measurementsВҰ352013 as the other gates.
\v 29 Its chambersВҰ352021, walls, and porches measuredВҰ352027 the same as the other gatesвҖ”there were windowsВҰ352029 all around in the porch. The inner gate with its porch \add вүҲwas twenty-seven metres long and thirteen metres wideВҰ352039\add*.
\v 30 There were also porchesВҰ352044 all around the inner wallвҖ”they were \add all\add* \add вүҲthirteen metres long andВҰ352044 almost three metres wideВҰ352052\add*.
\v 31 The porchВҰ352056 facing the outerВҰ352061 courtyardВҰ352060 had \add carved\add* palm treesВҰ352062 on its walls, andВҰ352056 eightВҰ352068 stepsВҰ352067 going up to it.
\s1 The eastern gate to the inner courtyard
\rem /s1 The Inner Courtyard: The East Gate
\p
\v 32 ThenВҰ352072 the man broughtВҰ352072 me to the innerВҰ352076 courtyardВҰ352075 by the easternВҰ352078 side andВҰ352079 measured the gateВҰ352082, which had the same measurements as the other gates.
\v 33 Its chambersВҰ352086, walls, and porches measuredВҰ352092 the same as the other gates, and there were windowsВҰ352094 all around. The inner gate with its porch \add вүҲwas twenty-seven metres long and thirteen metres wideВҰ352104\add*.
\v 34 Its porchВҰ352109 \add that\add* facedВҰ352111 the outerВҰ352112 courtyardВҰ352111 had \add carved\add* palm treesВҰ352113 on each side of it, andВҰ352109 eightВҰ352120 stepsВҰ352121 going up it.
\s1 The northern gate to the inner courtyard
\rem /s1 The Inner Courtyard: The North Gate
\p
\v 35 Next the man broughtВҰ352125 me to the northernВҰ352129 gateВҰ352128 and measured it, \add and\add* it measured the same as the other gates.
\v 36 Its chambers, walls, and porch measured the same as the other gates, and there were windowsВҰ352140 all around. The gateway with its porch \add вүҲwas twenty-seven metres long and thirteen metres wideВҰ352148\add*.
\v 37 Its porch \add that\add* facedВҰ352155 the outerВҰ352156 courtyardВҰ352155 had \add carved\add* palm treesВҰ352157 on each side of it, andВҰ352153 eightВҰ352164 stepsВҰ352165 going up it.
\s1 Rooms for preparing sacrifices
\rem /s1 Rooms for Preparing Sacrifices; Buildings Near the North Gate; The Rooms for Preparing Sacrifices
\p
\v 38 There was a roomВҰ352169 withВҰ352171 a door by each of the inner gateways which was where they rinsedВҰ352174 the burntВҰ352177 offeringsВҰ352177.
\v 39 There were two tables onВҰ352179 each side of each porchВҰ352179, whichВҰ352188 were for slaughteringВҰ352187 \add the offerings:\add* the burntВҰ352189 offering, the sinВҰ352190 offering, andВҰ352179 the guiltВҰ352191 offering.
\v 40 By the wall of the courtyard, going up to the gate to the northВҰ352200, there were two tables. Also on the otherВҰ352206 side there were two tables at the gate's porchВҰ352208.
\v 41 There were four tables by the gateВҰ352220 on each sideвҖ”they slaughteredВҰ352224 animals on those eightВҰ352221 tables.
\v 42 There were four cut-stone tables for the burnt offerings, \add вүҲeach just under a metre long and wide, and standing half a metre tall\add*. They kept the tools whichВҰ352247 they used to slaughterВҰ352248 the burnt offerings for the sacrificesВҰ352253 onВҰ352252 those \add stone\add* tables.
\v 43 Some two-pronged hooksВҰ352255 a handbreadth in length were fastened all around in the porch, andВҰ352255 the fleshВҰ352266 of the offeringsВҰ352267 would be put onВҰ352259 the tablesВҰ352265.
\s1 The priests' rooms
\rem /s1 Rooms for the Priests
\p
\v 44 Within the inner courtyardВҰ352274 \add butВҰ352269\add* on the outsideВҰ352269 of the inner gate were singers' roomsВҰ352272вҖ”one on the northern side facing south, andВҰ352269 the other on the southern side facing north.
\v 45 ThenВҰ352295 the man told me, вҖңThis roomВҰ352298 facing southВҰ352302 is for the priestsВҰ352303 who are on duty in the temple.
\v 46 The roomВҰ352308 facing northВҰ352312 is for the priestsВҰ352313 on duty at the altarВҰ352316, thatВҰ352309 is, for Tsadok'sВҰ352320 descendantsвҖ”they're the \add only\add* Levites who approachВҰ352321 YahwehВҰ352327 to serveВҰ352328 himВҰ352328.вҖқ
\s1 The inner courtyard
\rem /s1 The Inner Courtyard and the Temple Building; The Inner Courtyard and Temple
\p
\v 47 Next he measuredВҰ352330 the squareВҰ352341 courtyardВҰ352333 at fifty-four metres long andВҰ352330 wideВҰ352338, with the altarВҰ352342 in frontВҰ352343 of the temple.
\s1 The temple entrance
\rem /s1 The Temple
\p
\v 48 ThenВҰ352346 the man took me to the temple porch and measuredВҰ352351 its doorpostsвҖ”they were each two and a half metres thick. The entryway itself was seven metresВҰ352355 wide,\f + \fr 40:48 \ft Following the LXX, as the 1.5m (three cubits) in the Hebrew appears likely to be a copying mistake.\f* and the walls on each side of it were one and a half metres wide.
\v 49 The porchВҰ352370 was eleven metres wide and six metres deep, \add withВҰ352377\add* stepsВҰ352377 going up to it and pillarsВҰ352381 standing onВҰ352377 each side of it.
\c 41
\s1 Inside the temple
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ352390 the man took me into the temple'sВҰ352393 holy place andВҰ352390 measuredВҰ352394 the doorposts \add at\add* three metresВҰ352400 thick on each side.
\v 2 The doorway was five metres wide \add and\add* the wall on each side was two and a half metres long. ThenВҰ352413 the man measuredВҰ352425 the dimensions of the holy placeвҖ”twenty-one metres long and eleven metres wide.
\v 3 ThenВҰ352433 the man wentВҰ352433 into the \add very sacred\add* innerВҰ352434 place and measuredВҰ352435 the door at one metre wide, and the doorway was three metres wide. The walls on either side were nearly four metres wide.
\v 4 Then he measured the square room's lengthВҰ352452 andВҰ352449 widthВҰ352455 of eleven metres, \add measuring\add* to the templeВҰ352461 hallway. Then he saidВҰ352462 to me, вҖңThis is the most sacredВҰ352465 area.вҖқ
\s1 The temple rooms
\rem /s1 The Rooms Built against the Temple Walls
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ352468 the man measuredВҰ352468 the wall of the house at three metres thick. The widthВҰ352474 of each side room around the house was two metres.
\v 6 There were side rooms on threeВҰ352489 levels, one room above another, thirtyВҰ352490 rooms on each level. There were ledgesВҰ352492 around the temple wall to support all the side rooms, as the supports weren't built into the temple wall.
\v 7 SoВҰ352510 the side rooms widened and went around going up, because the house went around higher and higher all aroundвҖ”the rooms widened \add вүҲon each higher level\add*, and a stairway went up through the middleВҰ352538 level to the highest level.
\v 8 ThenВҰ352540 I sawВҰ352540 a raised part all around the temple, the foundationВҰ352546 for the side roomsВҰ352548. It measured a full rod in heightВҰ352542вҖ”\add вүҲjust over three metresВҰ352552\add*.
\rem /s1 The Building on the West
\v 9 The width of the wall of the side rooms on the outside was two andВҰ352565 a half metresВҰ352564. There was an open spaceВҰ352566 outside those rooms in the temple.
\v 10 On the other side of that open space were the priests' outer side roomsВҰ352573. That space was eleven metres wide all around the temple.
\v 11 There were doors into the side rooms from another open spaceВҰ352585 with one doorwayВҰ352590 on the northВҰ352589 side, andВҰ352583 the other on the southВҰ352592. The widthВҰ352593 of that open area was two and a half metresВҰ352597 all around.
\s1 The western side
\p
\v 12 The building thatВҰ352603 faced the courtyard on the western side was thirty-six metres wide. Its wall was two and a half metres thick all around, andВҰ352602 it was forty-seven metres long.
\s1 The temple building measurements
\rem /s1 The Total Measurements of the Temple Building
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ352628 the man measured the temple as being fifty-four metres long. The separateВҰ352635 buildingВҰ352636, itsВҰ352637 wall, andВҰ352628 the courtyard \add combined\add* also measured fifty-four metres \add вүҲacross\add*.
\v 14 The widthВҰ352642 of the front of the courtyard in front of the temple was also fifty-four metres.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ352650 the man measuredВҰ352650 the lengthВҰ352651 of the buildingВҰ352653 behindВҰ352661 the templeВҰ352668, to itsВҰ352662 west, and includingВҰ352662 the galleriesВҰ352662 on either side, itВҰ352661 came to fifty-four metres.
\rem /s1 Details of the Temple Building
\p The sacred innerВҰ352669 placeВҰ352657 and the porchВҰ352670,
\v 16 the inner walls and the windows, includingВҰ352674 the narrowВҰ352675 windows, and the galleriesВҰ352676 all around on threeВҰ352679 levels, were all panelledВҰ352682 in wood.
\v 17 Above the entryway to the innerВҰ352701 sanctuary and spaced along the walls there was a \add вүҲrepeating\add* pattern.
\v 18 It was decorated with winged creatures and palm treesВҰ352717вҖ”with a palm treeВҰ352718 betweenВҰ352719 each winged creature, and each winged creature had twoВҰ352723 facesВҰ352724:
\v 19 the humanВҰ352728 face looked toward a palm tree on one side, andВҰ352727 the youngВҰ352735 lion face looked toward a palm tree on the other side. They were carved all around the entireВҰ352743 temple.
\v 20 From the groundВҰ352750 to above the doorway, winged creatures and palm treesВҰ352756 were carved on the outer wall of the templeВҰ352759.
\v 21 The door posts of the \add вүҲmain templeВҰ352762 roomВҰ352766\add* were squareВҰ352764, all with the same appearance.
\rem /s1 The Wooden Altar
\v 22 The wooden altarВҰ352770 was one metre on each side and stood one and a half metresВҰ352773 highВҰ352774. Its cornerВҰ352779 posts, base, and frame were \add all\add* made of wood.
\p Then the man said to me, вҖңThis is the tableВҰ352787 thatВҰ352788 stands \add вүҲin Yahweh's presence\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The temple doorways
\rem /s1 The Doors
\p
\v 23 Both the main roomВҰ352795 andВҰ352795 the sacred placeВҰ352795 had doubleВҰ352792 doorsВҰ352793вҖ”
\v 24 each consisting of two parts that swung on hinges.
\v 25 There were carvings of winged creatures and palm treesВҰ352817 on the doorsВҰ352814, just like on the wallsВҰ352820, and there was a wooden roof over the frontВҰ352825 porchВҰ352826.
\v 26 There were narrow windowsВҰ352829 and palm treesВҰ352831 on either side of the porchВҰ352837, like the side roomsВҰ352838 of the temple, and they also had overhanging roofs.
\c 42
\s1 Two buildings near the temple
\rem /s1 Rooms for the Priests; The Holy Chambers and the Outer Wall; Two Buildings Near the Temple
\p
\v 1 Next the man sent me out to the outer courtyard on the northern side, and he broughtВҰ352850 me to rooms in front of the outer courtyard and the northern outer wall.
\v 2 That building with a north-facing entranceВҰ352872 was fifty-four metres long andВҰ352874 twenty-seven metres wide.
\v 3 Some of those rooms faced the innerВҰ352882 courtyard and were eleven metres away from the sanctuary. There were threeВҰ352894 levels of rooms, and the ones above looked down onВҰ352894 the ones below and were open to them, having a walkway. Some of the rooms looked out onto the outerВҰ352887 courtyard.
\v 4 A five metre wide passageВҰ352898 ran in frontВҰ352896 of the rooms andВҰ352908 was fifty-four\f + \fr 42:4 \ft The Hebrew text seemed to be missing a word here (as it didn't make sense), so the word from the (approx. 300 B.C.) Septuagint translation was used.\f* metresВҰ352900 long. The rooms' doors \add вүҲfaced\add* northВҰ352909.
\v 5 ButВҰ352911 the upperВҰ352912 halls were smaller, because the walkways \add вүҲthere used\add* more space than theyВҰ352916 did in the bottom andВҰ352920 middleВҰ352920 levels of the building.
\v 6 \add @The third storey halls\add* had no pillarsВҰ352929 (unlike the courtyardsВҰ352930), so \add @the rooms at the highest level\add* were smaller than those on the bottom and middleВҰ352936 levels.
\v 7 The outsideВҰ352942 wall ran along the rooms toward the outerВҰ352947 courtyardВҰ352946 thatВҰ352940 was in frontВҰ352950 of the rooms, \add andВҰ352939\add* was twenty-seven metres longВҰ352952.
\v 8 The \add row of\add* rooms along the outerВҰ352962 courtyardВҰ352961 was twenty-seven metres long, andВҰ352965 the \add row of\add* rooms facing the sanctuary was fifty-four metres long.
\v 9 There was an entrance to the lowest rooms from the easternВҰ352979 side, coming from the outerВҰ352983 courtyardВҰ352982.
\v 10 There was \add also a set of\add* roomsВҰ352999 along the outer courtyard wall on the easternВҰ352990 side of the outer courtyard, in frontВҰ352993 of the sanctuary's inner courtyard,
\v 11 with a walkway in frontВҰ353002 of them. They \add вүҲlooked similar to\add* the roomsВҰ353004 on the northernВҰ353007 side and had the same \add вүҲmeasurements\add*, as well as the same exitsВҰ353012 and arrangementsВҰ353013 and doors.
\v 12 There were also doorways into rooms on the southВҰ353020 side thatВҰ353018 were similarВҰ353016 to what was on the north side. There was an inside passage withВҰ353022 an outer doorвҖ”the passage had doors into all the rooms. At the easternВҰ353029 end of the passage there was a door from the outside.
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ353032 the man told me, вҖңThe northernВҰ353035 rooms and the southernВҰ353037 rooms thatВҰ353038 are in frontВҰ353041 of the outer courtyardВҰ353042 are sacred rooms whereВҰ353047 the priestsВҰ353051 who work nearest to YahwehВҰ353055 may eat the very sacred food. They'll put the very sacred things thereвҖ”the food offering, the sin offering, and the guiltВҰ353065 offeringвҖ”because it's a very sacred area.
\v 14 When the priestsВҰ353071 enterВҰ353070 it, they must not goВҰ353074 \add back\add* out of the sacred area to the outerВҰ353079 courtВҰ353078, without laying aside the clothes in which they servedВҰ353085, since those \add вүЎclothes\add* are sacred. So they must dress in otherВҰ353094 clothes before going \add вүҲback into the public areas\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Measuring outside the temple
\rem /s1 The Measurements of the Temple Area
\p
\v 15 The man completedВҰ353101 measuring the temple interior and thenВҰ353101 took me out to the easternВҰ353113 gateВҰ353109 and measured all the surrounding area there.
\v 16-19 He measured each side \add of the wall\add* withВҰ353122 \add &his\add* measuring rod, \add and it was\add* 270m\f + \fr 42:16 \ft Following the Septuagint here, which seems more accurate (unless he now has a shorter measuring rod).\f* long onВҰ353122 each of the easternВҰ353121, northern, southern, and western sides.
\v 20 \add вүҲSo\add* the fourВҰ353168 sidesВҰ353169 that were measuredВҰ353170 (and thus the wall around it) was 270m on each side, and the wall separatedВҰ353182 the sacredВҰ353184 area from the \add вүҲpublic area\add*.
\c 43
\s1 The powerful splendour of God there to temple
\rem /s1 The Lord Returns to the Temple; The Divine Glory Returns to the Temple; The Lord's Glory Returns; The Glory Returns to the Temple
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ353187 the man took me to the gate thatВҰ353192 opened to the east.
\v 2 Wow! The splendour of Yisrael'sВҰ353200 godВҰ353199 \add вүҲappeared towards\add* the east. His voiceВҰ353204 was like the \add вүҲroar of rushing waterВҰ353206\add*, andВҰ353197 the land shone with his \add вүҲbrilliance\add*.\x + \xo 43:2: \xt Eze 10:3-4,18-19; 11:22-23; Rev 1:15.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲWhat I saw in this vision was like what I'd seen in my earlier\add* visionsВҰ353225, first by the KebarВҰ353233 Canal, thenВҰ353212 later when he\f + \fr 43:3 \ft It's only one letter difference, but the Hebrew has вҖҳIвҖҷ here which seems wrong and is adjusted in some later manuscripts.\f* came to destroyВҰ353221 \add @Yerushalem\add*. I fell to \add my knees withВҰ353220\add* my faceВҰ353237 \add to the ground\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ353239\add* Yahweh'sВҰ353240 \add вүҲbrightness\add* entered into the temple via the easternВҰ353250 entrance.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ353252 the spiritВҰ353253 liftedВҰ353252 me up and broughtВҰ353254 me into the innerВҰ353258 courtВҰ353257, and wow, Yahweh'sВҰ353263 brilliance was filling the temple.
\v 6 ThenВҰ353266 as the manВҰ353270 was standingВҰ353272 \add there\add* besideВҰ353273 me, I heardВҰ353266 someone speak to me from inside the temple,
\v 7 and \add @the voice\add* told me, вҖңHumanity's child, this is the placeВҰ353311 \add where I'll sit onВҰ353308\add* my throneВҰ353283 and \add вүҲrest\add* my feetВҰ353288вҖ”whereВҰ353289 I'll live inВҰ353308 the middleВҰ353293 of the IsraeliВҰ353294 peopleВҰ353294 foreverВҰ353297. Yisrael's \add вүҲdescendants\add* and their kings will no longer profane my sacredВҰ353305 name with their faithlessness or with the corpsesВҰ353309 of their kings atВҰ353308 their \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add*.
\v 8 They'll no longer profane my sacred name by putting their \add вүҲentrance\add* next to my \add вүҲentrance\add*, and their doorposts next to my doorposts, with nothing butВҰ353318 a wall between me and them. They profaned my sacred name with their disgusting actions, so I \add вүҲdestroyedВҰ353333\add* them with my angerВҰ353335.
\v 9 Now they're to remove their prostitutionВҰ353341 and \add ?their kings' corpsesВҰ353342\add* from inВҰ353346 front of me, and I'llВҰ353345 live \add вүҲamongВҰ353346 them\add* foreverВҰ353347.
\p
\v 10 вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲdescribe that temple to the IsraeliВҰ353357 people\add* so they'll be ashamedВҰ353363 of theirВҰ353364 \add вүҲdisobedience\add* andВҰ353365 \add ?вүҲthink about those plans\add*.
\v 11 If they're ashamedВҰ353372 of everything they've done, then reveal the design of that temple to themвҖ”its details, its entrancesВҰ353381 and exitsВҰ353380, its complete design, and all its decrees and rules. ThenВҰ353370 \add right\add* \add вүҲin front of them,\add* writeВҰ353400 that down so they'll see its complete design and all its rules, and then obey them.
\v 12 This is the regulation for the temple: From the peak of the hillВҰ353422 to all the surrounding border around it, it'll be very sacredВҰ353429. Listen, that's the regulation for the temple.
\s1 The altar dimensions
\rem /s1 The Altar
\p
\v 13 These are the altar's measurements, using the same kind of measuring rod that was used for the temple area: There's a gutterВҰ353444 around the altar that's \add both\add* half a metre deep andВҰ353437 wide. There's a rim around it that's 23cm wide. That'll be the base for \add the rest of\add* the altar.\x + \xo 43:13-17: \xt Exo 27:1-2; 2Ch 4:1.\x*
\v 14 The lower part of the gutterВҰ353460 is one metre high to the lower ledge that surrounds the altar. The lower ledge is half a metre wide. From that ledge to the upper ledge, it's twoВҰ353466 metresВҰ353467. That ledge is also half a metre wide.
\v 15 The altarВҰ353482 body \add at the top\add* is another two metresВҰ353484 high andВҰ353482 has a \add вүҲhornlike projection\add* jutting up \add from each of its corners\add*.
\v 16 The sidesВҰ353503 of the squareВҰ353500 body are six metres long.
\v 17 The upper ledgeВҰ353505 that bordersВҰ353515 the altar body is also a square, eight metres long onВҰ353509 each side, andВҰ353505 has a rim all around that's 27cm wide. There's a gutterВҰ353520 measuring half a metre atВҰ353509 the bottom of the altar. There are stepsВҰ353525 leading up to the east side of the altar.вҖқ
\s1 The purification of the new altar
\rem /s1 The Consecration of the Altar
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ353529 \add @the man\add* told me, вҖңHumanity's child, the masterВҰ353536 YahwehВҰ353536 saysВҰ353535 that those are the dimensions for when they make the altarВҰ353540 for presenting the burntВҰ353545 offeringВҰ353543 on, andВҰ353546 for sprinklingВҰ353546 bloodВҰ353548 onto.\x + \xo 43:18-27: \xt Exo 29:35-37.\x*
\v 19 You must giveВҰ353550 a bullВҰ353565 from the cattle as a sinВҰ353569 offeringВҰ353569 for the LeviticalВҰ353554 priestsВҰ353553 who are Tsadok'sВҰ353558 descendantsвҖ”those who approach me to serveВҰ353564 me. That's the masterВҰ353562 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 20 ThenВҰ353571 you'll takeВҰ353571 some of \add @the bull's\add* bloodВҰ353572 and place it on the altar's вҖҳhornsВҰ353577вҖҷ and on the four top edges and the surrounding rim. You'll purifyВҰ353587 it and \add вүҲmake it allowable in my presence\add*.
\v 21 ThenВҰ353591 takeВҰ353591 that sinВҰ353594 offeringВҰ353594 bullВҰ353593 andВҰ353595 burnВҰ353595 itВҰ353595 inВҰ353596 the designated part of the temple area outsideВҰ353598 the sanctuaryВҰ353599.
\v 22 ThenВҰ353601 onВҰ353601 the secondВҰ353602 dayВҰ353601, you'll get from the goatsВҰ353606 a male goatВҰ353604 without any blemishes, andВҰ353601 offer it as a sin offeringвҖ”the priests will purify the altarВҰ353612 just as they purified it withВҰ353601 the bullВҰ353615.
\v 23 When you finishВҰ353617 that purificationВҰ353618, offer an unblemished bullВҰ353620 from the cattle and an unblemished ram from the flockВҰ353628,
\v 24 and offer them to \add me,\add* Yahweh. The priestsВҰ353635 will throwВҰ353634 salt onto them and presentВҰ353631 them as a burntВҰ353640 offering to Yahweh.
\v 25 Then every dayВҰ353649 for \add the next\add* seven daysВҰ353644 youВҰ353645 must bring a billy goatВҰ353646 to the priest to be sacrificed for an offeringВҰ353648, so I'll accept the altar. You must also sacrifice a youngВҰ353651 bullВҰ353650 and a ram, each without any defect, that the priests will provide.
\v 26 They must atoneВҰ353663 for the altarВҰ353666 for seven daysВҰ353662 and purifyВҰ353667 it, and in that way they must consecrate it \add to me\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲAfter doing all that\add*, from the eighthВҰ353680 dayВҰ353679 onwardВҰ353681 the priestsВҰ353683 will prepare you \add people\add*'s burntВҰ353689 offerings and your peaceВҰ353692 offerings onВҰ353679 the altarВҰ353686, and I'llВҰ353693 acceptВҰ353693 youВҰ353694. That's the masterВҰ353696 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 44
\s1 The locked doorway
\rem /s1 The Prince, the Levites, the Priests; The Use of the East Gate; The Prince, Levites, and Priests; The Closed Gate
\p
\v 1 Then the man took me back to the outerВҰ353705 sanctuaryВҰ353704 gateВҰ353703 facing east, \add вүҲbutВҰ353700\add* it was shut,
\v 2 andВҰ353711 Yahweh told me, вҖңThis gateВҰ353714 has been sealed shutвҖ”it won'tВҰ353718 be openedВҰ353719. No person will goВҰ353723 through it, because Yisrael's godВҰ353727 Yahweh entered through it, so it's \add now\add* closed.
\v 3 \add Only Yisrael's\add* ruler will sit by it to eat food \add вүҲin frontВҰ353748 of\add* YahwehВҰ353749, \add butВҰ353754\add* he'll enter via the gate's porchВҰ353751, and leave the same way.вҖқ
\s1 Foreigners disallowed in the temple
\rem /s1 Rules for Admission to the Temple; Admission to the Temple
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ353757 he took me to the frontВҰ353764 of the temple by way of the northernВҰ353761 gate, and I lookedВҰ353766, and wow, Yahweh's brilliance filledВҰ353768 \add *his\add* temple, and I fell to \add my knees with\add* my face \add bowed towards the ground\add*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ353781 Yahweh told me, вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲpay attention\add* and lookВҰ353789 with your eyesВҰ353790 and listenВҰ353792 with your earsВҰ353791 to everything that I'm declaring to you: all the instructions about Yahweh's temple and all its regulationsВҰ353802. \add вүҲTake special note of\add* the temple's entranceВҰ353812 and exitsВҰ353815.
\v 6 ThenВҰ353818 tell the rebelliousВҰ353821 \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ353824\add* that the masterВҰ353828 YahwehВҰ353828 saysВҰ353827 this: Let all yourВҰ353835 disgusting actions be enoughВҰ353830 for youВҰ353832 IsraeliВҰ353824 peopleвҖ”
\v 7 that you broughtВҰ353839 foreignersВҰ353842 with uncircumcised heartsВҰ353845 and uncircumcised fleshВҰ353847 to be inВҰ353849 my sanctuaryВҰ353849, profaningВҰ353850 my temple, while you \add people\add* were offeringВҰ353854 me food, fat, and bloodВҰ353859. You \add people\add* have brokenВҰ353860 my agreement with all your disgusting actions.
\v 8 You haven't carried out your duties regarding my sacred thingsВҰ353872, butВҰ353869 \add instead,\add* you \add people\add* appointedВҰ353873 others to take up your duties, andВҰ353873 you assigned them to care for my sacred place.
\p
\v 9 вҖңThe masterВҰ353882 YahwehВҰ353882 saysВҰ353881 this: No foreigner, from any of those who live among the IsraeliВҰ353906 peopleВҰ353905, may enter my sacred place if they're not physically circumcised or if they \add вүҲhaven't declared themself to be one of my people\add*.
\s1 Demotion of the Levites
\rem /s1 The Levites Are Excluded from the Priesthood
\p
\v 10 TheВҰ353916 LevitesВҰ353911 went far from meвҖ”wandering away from me \add and\add* going afterВҰ353920 their idolsВҰ353921, butВҰ353922 they'll be punishedВҰ353923.
\v 11 They're \add still\add* servants in my sanctuaryВҰ353926, watching the temple gatesВҰ353931 and serving inside, and they slaughterВҰ353938 the burntВҰ353941 offeringsВҰ353941 and the people's sacrificesВҰ353944, and they'll standВҰ353947 in front of the people and serveВҰ353949 them.
\v 12 \add However,\add* because they sacrificed to their idolsВҰ353956, they became sinful stumblingВҰ353961 blocksВҰ353961 for the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ353958 people\add*, thereforeВҰ353963 I've \add вүҲpromised to take action\add* against them, and they'll \add вүҲpay for their disobedience\add*. That's the masterВҰ353970 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 13 They mustn't come near to me to act as my priestsВҰ353979 or to approach any of my sacred things, the most sacred things. Instead, they'll bear their shameВҰ353992 andВҰ353975 their guilt for the disgusting things they've done,
\v 14 butВҰ353997 I'llВҰ353997 place them as housekeepersВҰ354001 in the templeвҖ”for all its \add mundane\add* duties andВҰ353997 \add вүҲall the menial workВҰ354003\add* that's done in it.
\s1 The priests descendants of Saduk
\rem /s1 The Levitical Priests; The Priests
\p
\v 15 Then the LeviticalВҰ354011 priestsВҰ354010, those descendants of TsadokВҰ354013 who fulfilled the duties of my sanctuaryВҰ354019 when the IsraeliВҰ354021 peopleВҰ354021 were wandering away from me, they'll approach me to worship me. They'll standВҰ354029 inВҰ354020 front of me to offerВҰ354031 me the fat and the bloodВҰ354034. That's the masterВҰ354036 Yahweh's declaration.
\v 16 They'll comeВҰ354040 to my sanctuaryВҰ354043 and approach my tableВҰ354048 to worship me and to fulfill their duties to me.
\v 17 WhenВҰ354055 they come to the gates of the inner courtyard, they'll have to dress in linenВҰ354063 clothingВҰ354062, because they mustn't \add вүҲwear\add* wool insideВҰ354074 the courtyard gates or in the temple.\x + \xo 44:17-18: \xt Exo 28:39-43; Lev 16:4.\x*
\v 18 \add вүҲThey must wear\add* linen turbans onВҰ354090 their headsВҰ354081 and linen underclothesВҰ354082 around their waistsВҰ354087. They mustn't dress inВҰ354090 clothing that makes them sweatВҰ354090.
\v 19 WhenВҰ354092 they go \add back\add* out to the outer courtyardВҰ354095 to go \add back again\add* to the people, they must take off the clothes they wore when they servedвҖ”they must take them off andВҰ354092 lay them down inВҰ354092 a sacred room, so they don'tВҰ354120 make otherВҰ354119 people sacred by contact withВҰ354092 their special clothing.\x + \xo 44:19: \xt Lev 16:23.\x*
\p
\v 20 \add @The priests\add* mustn't shaveВҰ354130 their heads or allow their hair to hang loosely, butВҰ354128 they must \add вүҲkeep the hair on their heads neatly trimmed\add*.
\v 21 No priestВҰ354146 should drinkВҰ354143 wine \add вүҲbefore\add* he comes to the innerВҰ354151 courtВҰ354150.\x + \xo 44:21: \xt Lev 10:9.\x*
\v 22 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ354166, priests can'tВҰ354155 marry widows of men who weren't priests, or women who've been divorcedВҰ354154вҖ”they're permitted to marry only IsraeliВҰ354165 women who've never been married, or widows of other priests\add*.
\p
\v 23 They must teach the peopleВҰ354176 the difference between things that are sacredВҰ354179 and things that are not, and teach them how to know what things are acceptable to me and what things are not.\x + \xo 44:23: \xt Lev 10:10.\x*
\v 24 In a disputeВҰ354189 they must judgeВҰ354192 inВҰ354194 accordance withВҰ354194 my instructions and regulationsВҰ354203. They must keep my law and my statutes atВҰ354194 every religious celebration, and they must observeВҰ354207 my sacred rest days.
\p
\v 25 \add @Priests\add* mustn't defile themselves by going near a person's dead body. However, if the dead person was his fatherВҰ354223 or motherВҰ354224, son or daughterВҰ354226, or brotherВҰ354227 or unmarried sisterВҰ354228, thenВҰ354213 they can defile themselves,
\v 26 andВҰ354237 afterВҰ354237 they've been purifiedВҰ354238, they must \add вүҲwait\add* for sevenВҰ354239 daysВҰ354240.
\v 27 ThenВҰ354245 \add after that\add*, \add вүҲwhen\add* he goesВҰ354246 into the innerВҰ354253 courtyardВҰ354252 to serveВҰ354254 inВҰ354245 the sacredВҰ354249 place, he must bringВҰ354256 a sinВҰ354257 offeringВҰ354257 for himself. That's the masterВҰ354259 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲThe priests must not ownВҰ354267 any land\add*вҖ”I am their inheritance andВҰ354262 I'll be their property.\x + \xo 44:28: \xt Num 18:20.\x*
\v 29 They'll have the food offerings, the sinВҰ354277 offerings, and the guiltВҰ354278 offerings to eatВҰ354280, plusВҰ354277 everything inВҰ354284 YisraelВҰ354284 that's devotedВҰ354283 to Yahweh will be theirs.\x + \xo 44:29-30: \xt Num 18:8-19.\x*
\v 30 The best of the firstfruits \add вүҲfrom every harvest\add* and every contributionВҰ354295 \add from the people\add* will belongВҰ354300 to the priests, and you \add Israelis\add* will give the first of your \add bread\add* doughВҰ354302\f + \fr 44:30 \ft Probably after it's cooked???\f* to the priests so that blessingВҰ354306 may rest on your home.
\v 31 Priests must not eatВҰ354322 \add вүҲthe meat of any bird or animal that's found dead or that's been killed by any other\add* animal.\x + \xo 44:31: \xt Lev 22:8.\x*
\c 45
\s1 Yahweh's section of land
\rem /s1 Division of the Land; The Holy District; The Lord's Portion of the Country
\p
\v 1 When you throw dice to divide up the land as an inheritanceВҰ354330 \add for the tribes\add*, you must make an offering of land to YahwehВҰ354333. That offering will become a sacred part of the land: \add вүҲthirteen kilometres by ten kilometres inВҰ354326 size\add*.\f + \fr 45:1 \ft The вҖҳten kilometresвҖҷ (twenty thousand cubits) from the Septuagint appears to correct the Hebrew which has half of that, but then v3 and v4 wouldn't make sense.\f* \add вүҲThat entireВҰ354350 area\add* will become sacred.
\v 2 \add вүҲWithin that area,\add* a 270m wide squareВҰ354364 area that'll surround the sacredВҰ354359 placeВҰ354359 \add вүҲwill be left empty\add*, withВҰ354362 a further border around it twenty-seven metres wide.
\v 3 Inside that \add first, larger\add* area, measureВҰ354376 a \add rectangle\add* thirteen kilometres by fiveВҰ354378 kilometres for the sanctuaryВҰ354388вҖ”the most sacredВҰ354389 placeВҰ354389.
\v 4 It'll be a sacred place in the nation for the priestsВҰ354397 who serve Yahweh, who come near Yahweh to serve him. It'll be a place for their housesВҰ354409 and a sacred area for the sacred place.
\v 5 The \add other half\add*, which is \add also\add* thirteen kilometres long andВҰ354413 fiveВҰ354413 kilometres wide, will be for towns for the LevitesВҰ354422 who serveВҰ354423 in the temple.
\p
\v 6 You'll designate an area thirteen kilometres long by half a kilometre wide for the city that will be next to the area reserved for the holy place. This city will belongВҰ354447 to all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ354445 people\add*.
\s1 The leader's section of land
\rem /s1 Land for the Prince
\p
\v 7 The leader's land will be on both sides of the area reserved for the holy place and the cityвҖ”on the west and the east. Its lengthВҰ354475 will \add вүҲbe the same as those portionsВҰ354478 that it's parallelВҰ354476 to\add*.
\v 8 That area will belongВҰ354487 to Yisrael's leader \add so\add* the leaders won'tВҰ354492 keep oppressingВҰ354494 my peopleВҰ354499, \add вүҲbutВҰ354492 rather\add* they'll giveВҰ354501 the rest of the land to \add вүҲbe divided among the tribesВҰ354505\add*.
\rem /s1 Rules for the Prince
\v 9 The master Yahweh says this: \add вүҲThat's plenty\add* for you, leaders of YisraelВҰ354517! \add вүҲReplace your\add* violenceВҰ354519 and strife \add вүҲwith\add* justiceВҰ354521 and righteousnessВҰ354522. Quit your evictionsВҰ354525 of my peopleВҰ354527. That's the master Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 Dealing with produce and animals
\rem /s1 Weights and Measures
\p
\v 10 You \add Israelis\add* must \add вүҲuse accurate scales and measuring containers\add*.\x + \xo 45:10: \xt Lev 19:36.\x*
\v 11 \add вүҲThe baskets for measuring dry things and containersВҰ354549 for measuring liquids (called an вҖҳefahвҖҷ for dry things and a вҖҳbathвҖҷ for liquids, both a tenth of the large 220 litre вҖҳhomerвҖҷ) must be the same volumeвҖ”each must hold twenty-two litres\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲFor weights, the shekel weight must be tenВҰ354570 grams. (Twenty вҖҳgerahsВҰ354564вҖҷ makes one shekel, thenВҰ354562 sixty shekels makes one вҖҳminaвҖҷ.)\add*
\rem /s1 Special Offerings and Celebrations; Offerings; Offerings and Holy Days
\p
\v 13 You \add Israelis\add* must present \add to the leader\add* \add вүҲone measure of wheatВҰ354584 or barleyВҰ354588 for every sixty measures\add* \add thatВҰ354579 youВҰ354580 harvest\add*,
\v 14 \add вүҲone measure of oliveВҰ354593 oil for every one hundred measures\add* \add that you produce\add*,
\v 15 plusВҰ354620 one sheepВҰ354608 or goat from the flockВҰ354613 for every twoВҰ354616 hundredВҰ354616 animals from the watered regionsВҰ354617 of YisraelВҰ354618, to be used for any burntВҰ354620 offering or peaceВҰ354621 offering to make atonementВҰ354622 for the people. That's the masterВҰ354625 Yahweh's declaration.
\p
\v 16 All the peopleВҰ354629 inВҰ354637 the country will give that contributionВҰ354634 to Yisrael's leader.
\v 17 It'll be the leader's responsibility to supply the animals for the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and the drinkВҰ354645 offerings atВҰ354646 the festivals and the new moon celebrations, and onВҰ354646 the rest daysвҖ”all the \add вүҲIsraeli people's\add* scheduled festivals. He'll provideВҰ354656 for the sin offerings, the grain offerings, the burnt offerings, and the peaceВҰ354668 offerings \add вүҲto make the Israeli people right\add* \add withВҰ354646 God\add*.
\s1 The festivals
\rem /s1 Festivals; The Festivals
\r (Exo. 12:1-20; Lev. 23:33-43)
\p
\v 18 The masterВҰ354679 YahwehВҰ354679 saysВҰ354678 this: On the first \add dayВҰ354682\add* of the first monthВҰ354683 \add of the year\add*, youВҰ354684 must takeВҰ354684 an unblemishedВҰ354690 bullВҰ354685 from the herd andВҰ354691 perform a sinВҰ354691 offering \add to purifyВҰ354691\add* the temple.
\v 19 The priestВҰ354697 will takeВҰ354696 some of the bloodВҰ354698 of that sinВҰ354699 offeringВҰ354699 and place it on the doorposts of the temple and on the fourВҰ354707 cornersВҰ354708 of the border of the altarВҰ354710, and on the doorposts of the gateВҰ354714 to the innerВҰ354716 courtВҰ354715.
\v 20 You'll do this \add again\add* onВҰ354720 the seventhВҰ354720 \add dayВҰ354720\add* of that monthВҰ354721 for each person'sВҰ354724 accidental sin, or sin by ignoranceВҰ354724. \add In that way you'll\add* \add вүҲmake the temple pure\add* \add inВҰ354720 God's sight\add*.
\p
\v 21 Then onВҰ354731 the fourteenth day of that firstВҰ354730 monthВҰ354734, you \add Israelis\add* will have a seven-day celebration, \add вүҲwhen you'll eat breadВҰ354741 made without any raising agent\add*.\x + \xo 45:21: \xt Exo 12:1-20; Num 28:16-25.\x*
\v 22 That same dayВҰ354746, the leader will prepare a bullВҰ354754 as a sinВҰ354755 offeringВҰ354755 for himselfВҰ354748 andВҰ354744 for all the peopleВҰ354752 in the country.
\v 23 For the seven days of the celebration, the leader will prepare a burntВҰ354762 offering for YahwehВҰ354763: Seven bullsВҰ354765 and seven unblemishedВҰ354768 rams each day for seven days, and a male goat each day as a sin offering.
\v 24 ThenВҰ354777 the leader will perform a food offeringВҰ354777 of twenty-two litres \add of flour\add* with seven litres of \add olive\add* oilВҰ354783 for each bullВҰ354779 andВҰ354777 each ram.
\p
\v 25 On the fifteenth dayВҰ354790 of the seventh monthВҰ354791 \add of the year\add*, atВҰ354788 the \add вҖҳtemporary sheltersвҖҷ\add* celebration, the leader will perform offerings onВҰ354788 those sevenВҰ354795 daysВҰ354796: Sin offerings, burntВҰ354798 offerings, food offerings, and offerings of oilВҰ354800.\x + \xo 45:25: \xt Lev 23:33-36; Num 29:12-38.\x*
\c 46
\s1 The leader and the festivals
\rem /s1 Miscellaneous Regulations; The Prince and the Festivals
\p
\v 1 The masterВҰ354806 YahwehВҰ354806 says this: The easternВҰ354812 gate of the innerВҰ354810 courtyardВҰ354809 will be shut for the six days of work, butВҰ354818 it'll be opened on rest days and on the day of the new moon.
\v 2 The leader will enterВҰ354825 the outer courtyard by the pathВҰ354827 to that gate and its outsideВҰ354830 porchВҰ354828, and he'll standВҰ354831 at the doorpostsВҰ354834 of the inner gate while the priestsВҰ354837 perform his burntВҰ354840 offering and peaceВҰ354843 offering. ThenВҰ354825 he'll worshipВҰ354844 \add вүҲright there\add* at the inner gate and \add вүҲthenВҰ354825 leave again\add*, butВҰ354825 the gate won'tВҰ354851 be shut untilВҰ354854 eveningВҰ354856.
\v 3 The peopleВҰ354859 will also worship inВҰ354865 frontВҰ354867 of YahwehВҰ354868 atВҰ354865 the entranceВҰ354862 to that gateВҰ354863 onВҰ354865 rest days andВҰ354858 new moonsВҰ354866.
\v 4 The burntВҰ354870 offering thatВҰ354871 the leader offers to YahwehВҰ354875 on the rest dayВҰ354876 will be sixВҰ354878 unblemished lambsВҰ354879 andВҰ354881 an unblemished ram.
\v 5 The grain offering that he gives with the ram is twenty-two litres \add of flour\add*, andВҰ354884 with the lambsВҰ354887 it should be as much as he pleases, along with one litre of \add olive\add* oil for every twenty-two litres of flour.
\v 6 On the dayВҰ354895 of the new moonВҰ354896 he must offer a bullВҰ354897, sixВҰ354902 lambsВҰ354903, andВҰ354895 a ramвҖ”\add вүҲall without any defects\add*.
\v 7 He must \add also\add* provideВҰ354912 a grainВҰ354913 offeringВҰ354913 of twenty-two litres of flour with the bullВҰ354909, the same with the ram, andВҰ354908 as much as heВҰ354912 wants with the lambsВҰ354914, along with a litre of \add olive\add* oilВҰ354918 with every twenty-two litres of flour.
\v 8 The leader entersВҰ354922 by the path to the gateВҰ354926 and its porchВҰ354925, and he must leave by the same path.
\p
\v 9 ButВҰ354931 when the land's peopleВҰ354932 come inВҰ354931 frontВҰ354935 of YahwehВҰ354936 atВҰ354931 the scheduledВҰ354937 festivals, anyone entering through the north gate to worshipВҰ354943 must leave through the south gate, andВҰ354931 anyone entering through the south gate must leave through the north gate. No one is allowed to turn back to the gate through whichВҰ354963 they entered, because everyoneВҰ354932 must keep going straight ahead until they get out.
\v 10 The leader must be amongstВҰ354973 them in theirВҰ354973 midstВҰ354973вҖ”when they go in, he must go in, andВҰ354972 when they leave, he must leave.
\v 11 During the festivalsВҰ354979 \add that you hold for me\add*, the king must present twenty-two litres of flour along with a bullВҰ354984 or a ram, andВҰ354979 as much flour as he wants to with the lambsВҰ354987, along with a litre of \add olive\add* oilВҰ354990 with every twenty-two litres of flour.
\p
\v 12 When the leader gives a voluntary offering to YahwehВҰ355005 (either a burnt offering or a peace offering), the easternВҰ355012 gate will be openedВҰ355006 for him. He'll offer his burnt offering or his peace offering just like he does on the rest dayВҰ355022. Then he must go out, and afterВҰ355029 he's gone out, the gate will be shut.
\s1 The daily sacrifice
\rem /s1 The Daily Offering
\p
\v 13 In addition, \add вүҲevery morning someone\f + \fr 46:13 \ft Some of the earliest translations (the Septuagint and the Vulgate) have вҖҳheвҖҷ here, suggesting it must be the leader.\f* must provide\add* a one yearВҰ355035 old lamb withВҰ355041 noВҰ355036 defectsВҰ355036 to be \add вүҲcompletely burntВҰ355038 up as an\add* offeringВҰ355038 to YahwehВҰ355040.
\v 14 \add AlsoВҰ355061\add* \add вүҲevery morning\add* someone must provide an offeringВҰ355047 of four litres of flourВҰ355059 mixed withВҰ355049 a litre of \add olive\add* oilВҰ355053, \add andВҰ355053\add* \add вүҲthat's a permanent requirement\add*.
\v 15 They'll prepare the lamb, the grainВҰ355073 offering, andВҰ355066 the oilВҰ355076, \add вүҲevery morning\add*вҖ”a permanent \add daily\add* burntВҰ355079 offering.
\s1 The leader and the country
\rem /s1 The Prince and the Land
\p
\v 16 The masterВҰ355086 YahwehВҰ355086 says this: If the leader gives a giftВҰ355092 to any of his sons, it becomes his inheritanceвҖ”that is, it'll become his sons' propertyВҰ355099 \add because\add* it's an inheritance.
\v 17 \add вүҲButВҰ355103\add* if he gives a giftВҰ355106 from his inheritance to one of his servantsВҰ355109, then it'll belongВҰ355122 to that servant untilВҰ355112 the yearВҰ355114 of libertyВҰ355115, andВҰ355103 then it'll returnВҰ355116 to the leader. His inheritance must definitely be for his \add own\add* sonsВҰ355120.\x + \xo 46:17: \xt Lev 25:10.\x*
\v 18 The leader mustn't take the people's inheritance away from them, evicting them from their own propertyвҖ”he must provide for his sons from his own property so that my people won'tВҰ355124 be \add вүҲforced off their own inherited land\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The temple kitchens
\rem /s1 The Temple Kitchens
\p
\v 19 Next the man broughtВҰ355146 me through the entranceВҰ355147 atВҰ355147 the gateВҰ355152 to the sacredВҰ355156 roomsВҰ355155 for the priestsВҰ355159 whichВҰ355148 were north-facing, andВҰ355162 what's more, thereВҰ355164 was a placeВҰ355165 towardВҰ355168 the west.
\v 20 He told me, вҖңThat's the placeВҰ355174 where the priestsВҰ355179 must boil the guiltВҰ355182 offering and the sinВҰ355185 offering and where they must bake the grainВҰ355190 offering. They mustn't bring the offerings into the outerВҰ355196 courtyardВҰ355195, because then the peopleВҰ355200 would become sacredВҰ355197 \add (and not be able to leave)\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ355202 he broughtВҰ355202 me to the outerВҰ355206 courtyard and led me past the four corners of that courtyard, and I saw that inВҰ355215 every corner of the courtyard there was \add another\add* \add вүҲenclosed area\add*,
\v 22 and each was twenty-two metres long andВҰ355228 sixteen metres wide.
\v 23 Around the inside of each of those enclosed areas was a stone ledge, with cooking hearthsВҰ355241 \add all around\add* underВҰ355243 the ledge.
\v 24 The man told me, вҖңThose are the places whereВҰ355252 the temple workers will boil the people'sВҰ355261 sacrificesВҰ355260.вҖқ
\c 47
\s1 The healing river
\rem /s1 The Stream Flowing from the Temple; The River From the Temple; The River of Healing; Water Flowing from the Temple
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ355263 the man took me back to the temple entranceВҰ355266, and there was water flowing out from under the \add вүҲfrontВҰ355278 edge of the building\add* towardВҰ355275 the east, and the water was flowing down the south side of the temple, to the right of the altarВҰ355288.\x + \xo 47:1: \xt Zech 14:8; Yhn 7:38; Rev 22:1.\x*
\v 2 SoВҰ355290 he took me out through the northernВҰ355294 gate and led me aroundВҰ355295 \add the outsideВҰ355297\add* to the easternВҰ355304 gate, and look, the waterВҰ355307 was flowing from this gate on its southВҰ355312 side.
\v 3 As the manВҰ355316 \add вүҲstarted walking\add* toward the east holding his measuring line inВҰ355322 his handВҰ355319, he measured off five hundred metresВҰ355322 and led me through the waterВҰ355324, which was ankle-deep.
\v 4 ThenВҰ355328 he measured another five hundred metres and led me throughВҰ355336 the waterВҰ355331, which was \add now\add* knee-deep, and thenВҰ355328 after another five hundred metres it was \add вүҲup to the waist\add*.
\v 5 FinallyВҰ355346 he measuredВҰ355340 off another five hundred metres, butВҰ355340 the water had become deep enough to swim in andВҰ355340 too deep to crossВҰ355347вҖ”it was \add now\add* a river thatВҰ355343 couldn't be walked throughВҰ355358.
\v 6 The man \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңHumanity's child, \add вүҲhave you taken note of all\add* this?вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ355360 he led me out andВҰ355360 had me \add вүҲreturn\add* along the riverbankВҰ355369.
\v 7 As I walked back, wow, \add now\add* the riverbankВҰ355376 had many trees on each side.
\v 8 The man told me, вҖңThis water \add вүҲflows eastward and down into the Rift Valley\add*. \add *It'll\add* flow into the Dead Sea and will make it into freshВҰ355402 water.
\v 9 \add вүҲAs a result,\add* every kind of livingВҰ355410 creatureВҰ355409 that swarmsВҰ355414 will live where that water flows. There'll be lots of fishВҰ355424 when that water flows \add @into the Dead Sea\add* as it causes the salty water to becomeВҰ355432 freshВҰ355432 waterвҖ”everything will live wherever that riverВҰ355439 goes.
\v 10 ThenВҰ355441 the fishermenВҰ355445 from Eyn-Gedi will stand \add there\add* by the water, andВҰ355441 there'll be a placeВҰ355452 to dry out the fishing nets near Eyn-Eglaim. There'll be many kindsВҰ355455 of fish in the Dead SeaвҖ”plentiful just like the fish in the Mediterranean Sea.
\v 11 \add However,\add* the Dead Sea's swamps and marshesВҰ355466 won'tВҰ355467 be made freshвҖ”they'll be for providing salt.
\v 12 Beside that riverВҰ355474 on both banksВҰ355478, all kinds of fruit trees will grow. Their leaves will never wilt, and \add вүҲthey'll never fail to fruit\add*вҖ”\add in fact\add* \add *they'll\add* bear fruit everyВҰ355483 monthВҰ355496 because that waterВҰ355499 from the temple flows to them. Their fruit will be \add вүҲgood to eat\add*, and theirВҰ355499 leaves will \add вүҲhelp with\add* healingВҰ355510.\x + \xo 47:12: \xt Rev 22:2.\x*
\s1 Land boundaries
\rem /s1 Division of the land among the tribes; Boundaries for the Land; The New Boundaries of the Land; The Boundaries of the Land
\p
\v 13 The masterВҰ355515 YahwehВҰ355515 saysВҰ355514 that this will be the way that youВҰ355520 divide the land up for Yisrael's twelve tribesВҰ355526: YosefВҰ355528 \add (Joseph)\add* will have \add вүҲa double allocation\add*.
\v 14 You're to equally divideВҰ355531 \add the land\add* that I \add вүҲtook action\add* to giveВҰ355540 to yourВҰ355541 ancestorsВҰ355541вҖ”\add from now onВҰ355546\add* that land will come to youВҰ355545 \add Israelis\add* as an inheritanceВҰ355546.
\p
\v 15 \add #These will be the land boundariesВҰ355549\add*: On the northВҰ355552 side, it'll extend from the Mediterranean Sea east along the road towards Hetlon, andВҰ355548 thenВҰ355548 on to TsedadВҰ355560,
\v 16 to BerotahВҰ355564, and then on to Sivrayim, which is on the border between DamascusВҰ355570 and HamatВҰ355573. The boundary will run as far as Hatser-Hattikon, which is on the border of the Havran \add region\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ355582\add* the boundary will extend from the Mediterranean Sea to Hatsar-Enan on the borderВҰ355589 between HamatВҰ355595 to the north andВҰ355582 DamascusВҰ355590 \add to the south\add*. \add вүҲThat'll be the northern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 18 On the eastern side, the boundary will extend between Havran and DamascusВҰ355606, south along the YordanВҰ355612 \add River\add* between the GileadВҰ355608 \add regionВҰ355610\add* and YisraelВҰ355611's territory, along the Dead Sea as far as Tamar.\f + \fr 47:18 \ft Tamar: the Hebrew has вҖҳthe Eastern SeaвҖҷ.\f* \add вүҲThat'll be the eastern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 19 On the southern side, the boundary will extend from TamarВҰ355626 to the springs near Merivat-KadeshВҰ355631. ThenВҰ355623 it'll extend \add west\add* along the brook of Egypt to the Mediterranean Sea. \add вүҲThat'll be the southern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 20 On the western side, the boundaryВҰ355648 will be the Mediterranean Sea, \add north\add* to a point near Levo-HamatВҰ355653.
\p
\v 21 This is how you'll divideВҰ355659 this land for yourselves among Yisrael's tribesВҰ355665:
\v 22 You must assign the land as a permanent possession for yourselves and also for any foreigners who are living and raising their childrenВҰ355679 among you. You must consider them to be like nativeВҰ355683 born IsraelisВҰ355684, and they must be assigned land among Yisrael's tribesВҰ355690.
\v 23 Wherever foreigners are living, youВҰ355701 must giveВҰ355701 them some land \add вүҲto belong to them permanently\add*. That's the masterВҰ355704 Yahweh's declaration.вҖқ
\c 48
\s1 Land allocated to Yisrael's tribes
\rem /s1 Division of the Land; The Division of the Land; The Division of the Land among the Tribes; The Tribal Portions
\p
\v 1 Here's a list of Yisrael's tribes and the territory that each tribe is to receive. The northern boundary of Yisrael will start at the Mediterranean Sea and go \add east\add* to Hetlon \add city\add*, then to Levo-Hamat, and farther on to Hatsar-EnanВҰ355724, which is \add south\add* of DamascusВҰ355726, and it'll continue to Hamat. Each tribe will receive land that will extend from the easternВҰ355737 boundary of Yisrael west to the Mediterranean Sea.
\rem /s1 The Special Section in the Center of the Land
\p The tribe of DanВҰ355739 will receive land alongside Yisrael's northern borderВҰ355725.
\v 2 \add вүҲSouthВҰ355745 of their area\add* will be the territory for the tribe of AsherВҰ355753.
\v 3 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Asher'sВҰ355759 land will be territory for the tribe of NaftaliВҰ355767.
\v 4 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Naftali'sВҰ355773 land will be territory for the tribe of Menashsheh.
\v 5 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Menashsheh's land will be territory for the tribe of EfrayimВҰ355795.
\v 6 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Efrayim'sВҰ355801 land will be territory for the tribe of Reuven.
\v 7 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Reuven's land will be territory for the tribe of YehudahВҰ355823 \add (Judah)\add*.
\s1 The chosen place
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Yehudah'sВҰ355828 land will be an area thatВҰ355838 the entireВҰ355840 nation will give to meвҖ”you \add Israelis\add* will set it apart for special use. The temple will be inВҰ355857 the middleВҰ355857 of the area thatВҰ355838's thirteen kilometres wide andВҰ355826 as long as the other land allocations.
\p
\v 9 The specialВҰ355859 area thatВҰ355860 you \add Israelis\add* will give to YahwehВҰ355862 will be thirteen kilometres long and fiveВҰ355864 kilometres wide.
\v 10 This special area will be allocated to the priestsВҰ355876: you'll assign them an area of land measuring thirteen kilometres on the northernВҰ355877 and southernВҰ355889 sides, and five kilometres on the westernВҰ355881 and easternВҰ355885 sides. Yahweh's temple will be inВҰ355898 the middleВҰ355898 of that special area.
\v 11 The temple area will be for the priestsВҰ355900, Tsadok'sВҰ355903 descendants, who are dedicated to serving me. (They're the ones who served me faithfully and didn'tВҰ355908 turn away \add from me\add* like the LevitesВҰ355916 \add вүҲand the others\add* did.)
\v 12 The \add вүҲpriests' allocation\add* will be a portionВҰ355922 of that very sacredВҰ355922 land, extending to the Levites' borderВҰ355928.
\v 13 The land assigned to the Levites will be the same size as the land that the priestsВҰ355934 will receive. (SoВҰ355931 together, these two portions of land will be thirteen kilometres long andВҰ355931 about ten kilometres wide.)
\v 14 They mustn't sell or barter itвҖ”none of this best part of Yisrael's land must ever be \add вүҲused for any other purpose\add*, because it's all sacredВҰ355965 to YahwehВҰ355966.
\p
\v 15 Another strip of land thirteen kilometres long and almost three kilometres wide will be allotted for other people livingВҰ355982 in the special area to use. They may build homes and have pasturelands there, and there'll be a city in the middleВҰ355986 of thatВҰ355970 area.
\v 16 The city \add вүҲwill be square, over two kilometres long on each side\add*,
\v 17 with an open area around itВҰ356020, within the special area, that will be about 130m wide in each direction.
\v 18 Outside the city, there'll be two strips that'll extend five kilometres onВҰ356037 each of the east and west sides, and the produceВҰ356053 from \add @those strips\add* will be food for the people working inВҰ356037 the city.
\v 19 \add вүҲThoseВҰ356064 who come from the various tribesВҰ356063 to work in the cityВҰ356060 may also work in this farmland\add*.
\v 20 That entireВҰ356076 special area, includingВҰ356070 the land given for Yahweh's use and the cityВҰ356084, will be a square that's thirteen kilometres long onВҰ356072 each side.
\p
\v 21 The tracts of land to the east and to the west of Yahweh's area and the cityВҰ356096 will belong to the leader. One area will extend thirteen kilometres east to Yisrael's easternВҰ356108 boundary, and the other will extend thirteen kilometres west \add to the Mediterranean Sea\add*. Yahweh's area, whichВҰ356086 contains the temple, will be inВҰ356128 the middleВҰ356128.
\rem /s1 Land for the Other Tribes
\v 22 TheВҰ356132 area that belongsВҰ356137 to the leader (that surrounds the LevitesВҰ356132' property and the cityВҰ356134 in the middleВҰ356135 of it) will be between the tribe of YehudahВҰ356142 \add to the north\add* and the tribe of BenyaminВҰ356145 \add to the south\add*.
\p
\v 23 South of Yahweh's area, each of the other tribes will receive one section of land that extends from the easternВҰ356152 \add boundary of Yisrael\add* west \add all the way to the Mediterranean Sea.\add*
\p Just south of Yahweh's area will be territory for the tribe of BenyaminВҰ356158.
\v 24 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Benyamin'sВҰ356164 land will be the land for the tribe of Shimeon.
\v 25 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Shimeon's land will be the land for the tribe of Yissakar.
\v 26 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Yissakar's land will be the land for the tribe of Zevulun.
\v 27 \add вүҲSouth of\add* Zevulun's land will be the land for the tribe of GadВҰ356214.
\v 28 Gad'sВҰ356219 southern boundary will extend from TamarВҰ356227 \add south\add* to the watersВҰ356228 of Merivah-KadeshВҰ356230, and farther \add west\add* to the brook \add of Egypt\add*, and thenВҰ356217 on to the Mediterranean Sea.
\p
\v 29 That \add describes\add* the territory you'llВҰ356241 allocate to Yisrael's tribesВҰ356243 to become theirВҰ356246 permanent inheritanceВҰ356242. That's the masterВҰ356248 Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 The city gateways
\rem /s1 The Gates of the City; The Gates of Jerusalem
\p
\v 30 These will be the exitsВҰ356253 from the cityВҰ356254: On the northernВҰ356256 side (which will be just over two kilometres long),\x + \xo 48:30-34: \xt Rev 21:12-13.\x*
\v 31 there'll be threeВҰ356271 gates named after the tribesВҰ356268 of Reuven, YehudahВҰ356277, andВҰ356263 LeviВҰ356280.
\v 32 On the easternВҰ356286 side (the same length) there'll be threeВҰ356292 gatesВҰ356291 named after the tribes of YosefВҰ356294, BenyaminВҰ356297, andВҰ356283 DanВҰ356300.
\v 33 On the southernВҰ356305 side (the same length) there'll be threeВҰ356312 gatesВҰ356311 named after the tribes of Shimeon, Yissakar, andВҰ356303 Zevulun.
\v 34 On the western side (the same length) there'll be threeВҰ356331 gatesВҰ356330 named after the tribes of GadВҰ356333, AsherВҰ356336, and NaftaliВҰ356339.
\v 35 The \add вүҲdistance around the cityВҰ356348\add* will be nine kilometres.
\p From that time onwards, the city's nameВҰ356346 will be вҖҳYahweh is thereВҰ356352вҖҷ \add (Yahweh-Shammah)\add*.
